obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (90366)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90366&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person shall be liable to punishment under this Sanhita and not otherwise for every act or`
  line `omission contrary to the provisions thereof, of which he shall be guilty within India.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person liable, by any law for the time being in force in India, to be tried for an offence`
  line `committed beyond India shall be dealt with according to the provisions of this Sanhita for any act`
  line `committed beyond India in the same manner as if such act had been committed within India.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of this Sanhita shall also apply to any offence committed by--`
  line
  line `(a) any citizen of India in any place without and beyond India;`
  line
  line `(b) any person on any ship or aircraft registered in India wherever it may be;`
  line
  line `(c) any person in any place without and beyond India committing offence targeting a computer`
  line `resource located in India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the word "offence" includes every act committed outside India which,`
  line `if committed in India, would be punishable under this Sanhita.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, who is a citizen of India, commits a murder in any place without and beyond India.`
  line
  line `He can be tried and convicted of murder in any place in India in which he may be found.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this Sanhita shall affect the provisions of any Act for punishing mutiny and desertion`
  line `of officers, soldiers, sailors or airmen in the service of the Government of India or the provisions of any`
  line `special or local law.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st July, 2024, except the provision of sub-section (2) of section 106, vide notification No. S.O. 850(E), dated, 23rd day of`
  line `February, 2024, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (90367)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90367&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Sanhita, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(1) "act" denotes as well a series of acts as a single act;`
  line
  line `(2) "animal" means any living creature, other than a human being;`
  line
  line `(3) "child" means any person below the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(4) "counterfeit".---A person is said to "counterfeit" who causes one thing to resemble another`
  line `thing, intending by means of that resemblance to practise deception, or knowing it to be likely that`
  line `deception will thereby be practised.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---It is not essential to counterfeiting that the imitation should be exact..`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---When a person causes one thing to resemble another thing, and the resemblance`
  line `is such that a person might be deceived thereby, it shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved,`
  line `that the person so causing the one thing to resemble the other thing intended by means of that`
  line `resemblance to practise deception or knew it to be likely that deception would thereby be practised;`
  line
  line `(5) "Court" means a Judge who is empowered by law to act judicially alone, or a body of Judges`
  line `which is empowered by law to act judicially as a body, when such Judge or body of Judges is acting`
  line judicially;
  line
  line `(6) "death" means the death of a human being unless the contrary appears from the context;`
  line
  line `(7) "dishonestly" means doing anything with the intention of causing wrongful gain to one`
  line `person or wrongful loss to another person;`
  line
  line `(8) "document" means any matter expressed or described upon any substance by means of letters,`
  line `figures or marks, or by more than one of those means, and includes electronic and digital record,`
  line `intended to be used, or which may be used, as evidence of that matter.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---It is immaterial by what means or upon what substance the letters, figures or`
  line `marks are formed, or whether the evidence is intended for, or may be used in a Court or not.`
  line
  line `(a) A writing expressing the terms of a contract, which may be used as evidence of the contract,`
  line `is a document..`
  line
  line `(b) A cheque upon a banker is a document.`
  line
  line `(c) A power-of-attorney is a document.`
  line
  line `(d) A map or plan which is intended to be used or which may be used as evidence, is a document.`
  line
  line `(e) A writing containing directions or instructions is a document.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---Whatever is expressed by means of letters, figures or marks as explained by`
  line `mercantile or other usage, shall be deemed to be expressed by such letters, figures or marks within`
  line `the meaning of this section, although the same may not be actually expressed.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A writes his name on the back of a bill of exchange payable to his order. The meaning of the`
  line `endorsement, as explained by mercantile usage, is that the bill is to be paid to the holder. The`
  line `endorsement is a document, and shall be construed in the same manner as if the words"pay to the`
  line `holder" or words to that effect had been written over the signature;`
  line
  line `(9) "fraudulently" means doing anything with the intention to defraud but not otherwise;.`
  line
  line `(10) "gender".---The pronoun "he" and its derivatives are used of any person, whether male,`
  line `female or transgender.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---"transgender" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (k) of section 2 of`
  line `the Transgender Persons (Protection of Rights) Act, 2019 (40 of 2019);`
  line
  line `(11) "good faith".---Nothing is said to be done or believed in "good faith" which is done or`
  line `believed without due care and attention;`
  line
  line `(12) "Government" means the Central Government or a State Government;`
  line
  line `(13) "harbour" includes supplying a person with shelter, food, drink, money, clothes, arms,`
  line `ammunition or means of conveyance, or the assisting a person by any means, whether of the same`
  line `kind as those enumerated in this clause or not, to evade apprehension;`
  line
  line `(14) "injury" means any harm whatever illegally caused to any person, in body, mind, reputation`
  line `or property;`
  line
  line `(15) "illegal" and "legally bound to do".---The word "illegal" is applicable to everything which is`
  line `an offence or which is prohibited by law, or which furnishes ground for a civil action; and a person is`
  line `said to be "legally bound to do" whatever it is illegal in him to omit;`
  line
  line `(16) "Judge" means a person who is officially designated as a Judge and includes a person,---`
  line
  line `(i) who is empowered by law to give, in any legal proceeding, civil or criminal, a`
  line `definitive judgment, or a judgment which, if not appealed against, would be definitive, or a`
  line `judgment which, if confirmed by some other authority, would be definitive; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is one of a body or persons, which body of persons is empowered by law to give`
  line `such a judgment.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A Magistrate exercising jurisdiction in respect of a charge on which he has power to sentence to`
  line `fine or imprisonment, with or without appeal, is a Judge;`
  line
  line `(17) "life" means the life of a human being, unless the contrary appears from the context;`
  line
  line `(18) "local law" means a law applicable only to a particular part of India;`
  line
  line `(19) "man" means male human being of any age;`
  line
  line `(20) "month" and "year".---Wherever the word "month" or the word "year" is used, it is to be`
  line `understood that the month or the year is to be reckoned according to the Gregorian calendar;`
  line
  line `(21) "movable property" includes property of every description, except land and things attached`
  line `to the earth or permanently fastened to anything which is attached to the earth;`
  line
  line `(22) "number".---Unless the contrary appears from the context, words importing the singular`
  line `number include the plural number, and words importing the plural number include the singular`
  line number;
  line
  line `(23) "oath" includes a solemn affirmation substituted by law for an oath, and any declaration`
  line `required or authorised by law to be made before a public servant or to be used for the purpose of`
  line `proof, whether in a Court or not;`
  line
  line `(24) "offence".---Except in the Chapters and sections mentioned in sub-clauses (a) and (b), the`
  line `word "offence" means a thing made punishable by this Sanhita, but---`
  line
  line `(a) in Chapter III and in the following sections, namely, sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (5) of`
  line `section 8, sections 9, 49, 50, 52, 54, 55, 56, 57, 58, 59, 60, 61, 119, 120, 123, sub-sections (7) and`
  line `(8) of section 127, 222, 230, 231, 240, 248, 250, 251, 259, 260, 261, 262, 263, sub-sections (6)`
  line `and (7) of section 308 and sub-section (2) of section 330, the word offence means a thing`
  line `punishable under this Sanhita, or under any special law or local law; and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (1) of section 189, sections 211, 212, 238, 239, 249, 253 and`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 329, the word "offence" shall have the same meaning when the act`
  line `punishable under the special law or local law is punishable under such law with imprisonment for`
  line `a term of six months or more, whether with or without fine;`
  line
  line `(25) "omission" denotes as well as a series of omissions as a single omission;`
  line
  line `(26) "person" includes any company or association or body of persons, whether incorporated or`
  line not;
  line
  line `(27) "public" includes any class of the public or any community;`
  line
  line `(28) "public servant" means a person falling under any of the descriptions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) every commissioned officer in the Army, Navy or Air Force;`
  line
  line `(b) every Judge including any person empowered by law to discharge, whether by`
  line `himself or as a member of any body of persons, any adjudicatory functions;`
  line
  line `(c) every officer of a Court including a liquidator, receiver or commissioner whose duty`
  line `it is, as such officer, to investigate or report on any matter of law or fact, or to make,`
  line `authenticate, or keep any document, or to take charge or dispose of any property, or to`
  line `execute any judicial process, or to administer any oath, or to interpret, or to preserve order in`
  line `the Court, and every person specially authorised by a Court to perform any of such duties;`
  line
  line `(d) every assessor or member of a panchayat assisting a Court or public servant;`
  line
  line `(e) every arbitrator or other person to whom any cause or matter has been referred for`
  line `decision or report by any Court, or by any other competent public authority;`
  line
  line `(f) every person who holds any office by virtue of which he is empowered to place or`
  line `keep any person in confinement;`
  line
  line `(g) every officer of the Government whose duty it is, as such officer, to prevent offences,`
  line `to give information of offences, to bring offenders to justice, or to protect the public health,`
  line `safety or convenience;`
  line
  line `(h) every officer whose duty it is, as such officer, to take, receive, keep or expend any`
  line `property on behalf of the Government, or to make any survey, assessment or contract on`
  line `behalf of the Government, or to execute any revenue-process, or to investigate, or to report,`
  line `on any matter affecting the pecuniary interests of the Government, or to make, authenticate`
  line `or keep any document relating to the pecuniary interests of the Government, or to prevent the`
  line `infraction of any law for the protection of the pecuniary interests of the Government;`
  line
  line `(i) every officer whose duty it is, as such officer, to take, receive, keep or expend any`
  line `property, to make any survey or assessment or to levy any rate or tax for any secular common`
  line `purpose of any village, town or district, or to make, authenticate or keep any document for`
  line `the ascertaining of the rights of the people of any village, town or district;`
  line
  line `(j) every person who holds any office by virtue of which he is empowered to prepare,`
  line `publish, maintain or revise an electoral roll or to conduct an election or part of an election;`
  line
  line `(k) every person---`
  line
  line `(i) in the service or pay of the Government or remunerated by fees or commission for`
  line `the performance of any public duty by the Government;.`
  line
  line `(ii) in the service or pay of a local authority as defined in clause (31) of section 3 of`
  line `the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), a corporation established by or under a`
  line `Central or State Act or a Government company as defined in clause (45) of section 2 of`
  line `the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)..`
  line
  line Explanation.---
  line
  line `(a) persons falling under any of the descriptions made in this clause are public servants,`
  line `whether appointed by the Government or not;`
  line
  line `(b) every person who is in actual possession of the situation of a public servant, whatever`
  line `legal defect there may be in his right to hold that situation is a public servant;`
  line
  line `(c) "election" means an election for the purpose of selecting members of any legislative,`
  line `municipal or other public authority, of whatever character, the method of selection to which`
  line `is by, or under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A Municipal Commissioner is a public servant;`
  line
  line `(29) "reason to believe".---A person is said to have "reason to believe" a thing, if he has`
  line `sufficient cause to believe that thing but not otherwise;`
  line
  line `(30) "special law" means a law applicable to a particular subject;`
  line
  line `(31) "valuable security" means a document which is, or purports to be, a document whereby any`
  line `legal right is created, extended, transferred, restricted, extinguished or released, or whereby any`
  line `person acknowledges that he lies under legal liability, or has not a certain legal right.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A writes his name on the back of a bill of exchange. As the effect of this endorsement is to`
  line `transfer the right to the bill to any person who may become the lawful holder of it, the endorsement is`
  line `a "valuable security";`
  line
  line `(32) "vessel" means anything made for the conveyance by water of human beings or of property;`
  line
  line `(33) "voluntarily".---A person is said to cause an effect "voluntarily" when he causes it by means`
  line `whereby he intended to cause it, or by means which, at the time of employing those means, he knew`
  line `or had reason to believe to be likely to cause it.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A sets fire, by night, to an inhabited house in a large town, for the purpose of facilitating a`
  line `robbery and thus causes the death of a person. Here, A may not have intended to cause death; and`
  line `may even be sorry that death has been caused by his act; yet, if he knew that he was likely to cause`
  line `death, he has caused death voluntarily;.`
  line
  line `(34) "will" means any testamentary document;`
  line
  line `(35) "woman" means a female human being of any age;`
  line
  line `(36) "wrongful gain" means gain by unlawful means of property to which the person gaining is`
  line `not legally entitled;`
  line
  line `(37) "wrongful loss" means the loss by unlawful means of property to which the person losing it`
  line `is legally entitled;`
  line
  line `(38) "gaining wrongfully" and "losing wrongfully".---A person is said to gain wrongfully when`
  line `such person retains wrongfully, as well as when such person acquires wrongfully. A person is said to`
  line `lose wrongfully when such person is wrongfully kept out of any property, as well as when such`
  line `person is wrongfully deprived of property; and`
  line
  line `(39) words and expressions used but not defined in this Sanhita but defined in the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) and the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act and Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (90368)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `General explanations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90368&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Throughout this Sanhita every definition of an offence, every penal`
  line `provision, and every Illustration of every such definition or penal provision, shall be understood subject`
  line `to the exceptions contained in the Chapter entitled General Exceptions, though those exceptions are not`
  line `repeated in such definition, penal provision, or Illustration.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) The sections in this Sanhita, which contain definitions of offences, do not express that a child`
  line `under seven years of age cannot commit such offences; but the definitions are to be understood subject to`
  line `the general exception which provides that nothing shall be an offence which is done by a child under`
  line `seven years of age.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a police officer, without warrant, apprehends Z, who has committed murder. Here A is not`
  line `guilty of the offence of wrongful confinement; for he was bound by law to apprehend Z, and therefore the`
  line `case falls within the general exception which provides that "nothing is an offence which is done by a`
  line `person who is bound by law to do it".`
  line
  line `(2) Every expression which is explained in any Part of this Sanhita, is used in every Part of this`
  line `Sanhita in conformity with the explanation.`
  line
  line `(3) When property is in the possession of a person's spouse, clerk or servant, on account of that`
  line `person, it is in that person's possession within the meaning of this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---A person employed temporarily or on a particular occasion in the capacity of a clerk`
  line `or servant, is a clerk or servant within the meaning of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) In every Part of this Sanhita, except where a contrary intention appears from the context, words`
  line `which refer to acts done extend also to illegal omissions.`
  line
  line `(5) When a criminal act is done by several persons in furtherance of the common intention of all,`
  line `each of such persons is liable for that act in the same manner as if it were done by him alone.`
  line
  line `(6) Whenever an act, which is criminal only by reason of its being done with a criminal knowledge or`
  line `intention, is done by several persons, each of such persons who joins in the act with such knowledge or`
  line `intention is liable for the act in the same manner as if the act were done by him alone with that knowledge`
  line `or intention.`
  line
  line `(7) Wherever the causing of a certain effect, or an attempt to cause that effect, by an act or by an`
  line `omission, is an offence, it is to be understood that the causing of that effect partly by an act and partly by`
  line `an omission is the same offence.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A intentionally causes Zs death, partly by illegally omitting to give Z food, and partly by beating Z.`
  line `A has committed murder.`
  line
  line `(8) When an offence is committed by means of several acts, whoever intentionally cooperates in the`
  line `commission of that offence by doing any one of those acts, either singly or jointly with any other person,`
  line `commits that offence.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A and B agree to murder Z by severally and at different times giving him small doses of poison.`
  line `A and B administer the poison according to the agreement with intent to murder Z. Z dies from the`
  line `effects the several doses of poison so administered to him. Here A and B intentionally cooperate in the`
  line `commission of murder and as each of them does an act by which the death is caused, they are both guilty`
  line `of the offence though their acts are separate.`
  line
  line `(b) A and B are joint jailors, and as such have the charge of Z, a prisoner, alternatively for six hours`
  line `at a time. A and B, intending to cause Z's death, knowingly cooperate in causing that effect by illegally`
  line `omitting, each during the time of his attendance, to furnish Z with food supplied to them for that purpose.`
  line `Z dies of hunger. Both A and B are guilty of the murder of Z.`
  line
  line `(c) A, a jailor, has the charge of Z, a prisoner. A, intending to cause Z's death, illegally omits to`
  line `supply Z with food; in consequence of which Z is much reduced in strength, but the starvation is not`
  line `sufficient to cause his death. A is dismissed from his office, and B succeeds him. B, without collusion or`
  line `cooperation with A, illegally omits to supply Z with food, knowing that he is likely thereby to cause Z's`
  line `death. Z dies of hunger. B is guilty of murder, but, as A did not cooperate with B. A is guilty only of an`
  line `attempt to commit murder.`
  line
  line `(9) Where several persons are engaged or concerned in the commission of a criminal act, they may be`
  line `guilty of different offences by means of that act.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A attacks Z under such circumstances of grave provocation that his killing of Z would be only`
  line `culpable homicide not amounting to murder. B, having ill-will towards Z and intending to kill him, and`
  line `not having been subject to the provocation, assists A in killing Z. Here, though A and B are both engaged`
  line `in causing Z's death, B is guilty of murder, and A is guilty only of culpable homicide.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (90369)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Punishments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90369&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The punishments to which offenders are liable under the provisions of this`
  line `Sanhita are—`
  line
  line `(a) Death;`
  line
  line `(b) Imprisonment for life;`
  line
  line `(c) Imprisonment, which is of two descriptions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(1) Rigorous, that is, with hard labour;`
  line
  line `(2) Simple;`
  line
  line `(d) Forfeiture of property;`
  line
  line `(e) Fine;`
  line
  line `(f) Community Service.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (90370)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Commutation of sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90370&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, without the consent of the`
  line `offender, commute any punishment under this Sanhita to any other punishment in accordance`
  line `with section 474 of the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section the expression "appropriate Government" means, ---`
  line
  line `(a) in cases where the sentence is a sentence of death or is for an offence against any law relating`
  line `to a matter to which the executive power of the Union extends, the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in cases where the sentence (whether of death or not) is for an offence against any law`
  line `relating to a matter to which the executive power of the State extends, the Government of the State`
  line `within which the offender is sentenced.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (90371)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Fractions of terms of punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90371&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `In calculating fractions of terms of punishment,`
  line `imprisonment for life shall be reckoned as equivalent to imprisonment for twenty years unless otherwise`
  line provided.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (90372)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Sentence may be (in certain cases of imprisonment) wholly or partly rigorous or simple.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90372&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line In
  line `every case in which an offender is punishable with imprisonment which may be of either description, it`
  line `shall be competent to the Court which sentences such offender to direct in the sentence that such`
  line `imprisonment shall be wholly rigorous, or that such imprisonment shall be wholly simple, or that any part`
  line `of such imprisonment shall be rigorous and the rest simple.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (90373)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Amount of fine, liability in default of payment of fine, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90373&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where no sum is expressed to`
  line `which a fine may extend, the amount of fine to which the offender is liable is unlimited, but shall not be`
  line excessive.
  line
  line `(2) In every case of an offence---`
  line
  line `(a) punishable with imprisonment as well as fine, in which the offender is sentenced to a fine,`
  line `whether with or without imprisonment;`
  line
  line `(b) punishable with imprisonment or fine, or with fine only, in which the offender is sentenced to`
  line `a fine,`
  line
  line `it shall be competent to the Court which sentences such offender to direct by the sentence that, in default`
  line `of payment of the fine, the offender shall suffer imprisonment for a certain term, in which imprisonment`
  line `shall be in excess of any other imprisonment to which he may have been sentenced or to which he may be`
  line `liable under a commutation of a sentence.`
  line
  line `(3) The term for which the Court directs the offender to be imprisoned in default of payment of a fine`
  line `shall not exceed one-fourth of the term of imprisonment which is the maximum fixed for the offence, if`
  line `the offence be punishable with imprisonment as well as fine.`
  line
  line `(4) The imprisonment which the Court imposes in default of payment of a fine or in default of`
  line `community service may be of any description to which the offender might have been sentenced for the`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(5) If the offence is punishable with fine or community service, the imprisonment which the Court`
  line `imposes in default of payment of the fine or in default of community service shall be simple, and the term`
  line `for which the Court directs the offender to be imprisoned, in default of payment of fine or in default of`
  line `community service, shall not exceed,---`
  line
  line `(a) two months when the amount of the fine does not exceed five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) four months when the amount of the fine does not exceed ten thousand rupees; and`
  line
  line `(c) one year in any other case.`
  line
  line `(6) (a) The imprisonment which is imposed in default of payment of a fine shall terminate whenever`
  line `that fine is either paid or levied by process of law;`
  line
  line `(b) If, before the expiration of the term of imprisonment fixed in default of payment, such a`
  line `proportion of the fine be paid or levied that the term of imprisonment suffered in default of payment is`
  line `not less than proportional to the part of the fine still unpaid, the imprisonment shall terminate.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A is sentenced to a fine of one thousand rupees and to four months imprisonment in default of`
  line `payment. Here, if seven hundred and fifty rupees of the fine be paid or levied before the expiration of one`
  line `month of the imprisonment, A will be discharged as soon as the first month has expired. If seven hundred`
  line `and fifty rupees be paid or levied at the time of the expiration of the first month, or at any later time while`
  line `A continues in imprisonment, A will be immediately discharged. If five hundred rupees of the fine be`
  line `paid or levied before the expiration of two months of the imprisonment, A will be discharged as soon as`
  line `the two months are completed. If five hundred rupees be paid or levied at the time of the expiration of`
  line `those two months, or at any later time while A continues in imprisonment, A will be immediately`
  line discharged.
  line
  line `(7) The fine, or any part thereof which remains unpaid, may be levied at any time within six years`
  line `after the passing of the sentence, and if, under the sentence, the offender be liable to imprisonment for a`
  line `longer period than six years, then at any time previous to the expiration of that period; and the death of`
  line `the offender does not discharge from the liability any property which would, after his death, be legally`
  line `liable for his debts.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (90374)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Limit of punishment of offence made up of several offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90374&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where anything which is an`
  line `offence is made up of parts, any of which parts is itself an offence, the offender shall not be punished`
  line `with the punishment of more than one of such his offences, unless it be so expressly provided.`
  line
  line `(2) Where---`
  line
  line `(a) anything is an offence falling within two or more separate definitions of any law in force for`
  line `the time being by which offences are defined or punished; or`
  line
  line `(b) several acts, of which one or more than one would by itself or themselves constitute an`
  line `offence, constitute, when combined, a different offence,`
  line
  line `the offender shall not be punished with a more severe punishment than the Court which tries him could`
  line `award for any one of such offences.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A gives Z fifty strokes with a stick. Here A may have committed the offence of voluntarily`
  line `causing hurt to Z by the whole beating, and also by each of the blows which make up the whole beating.`
  line `If A were liable to punishment for every blow, he might be imprisoned for fifty years, one for each blow.`
  line `But he is liable only to one punishment for the whole beating.`
  line
  line `(b) But, if, while A is beating Z, Y interferes, and A intentionally strikes Y, here, as the blow given to`
  line `Y is no part of the act whereby A voluntarily causes hurt to Z, A is liable to one punishment for`
  line `voluntarily causing hurt to Z, and to another for the blow given to Y.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (90724)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Punishment of person guilty of one of several offences, judgment stating that it is doubtful of which.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90724&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `In all cases in which judgment is given that a person is guilty of one of several offences`
  line `specified in the judgment, but that it is doubtful of which of these offences he is guilty, the offender shall`
  line `be punished for the offence for which the lowest punishment is provided if the same punishment is not`
  line `provided for all.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (90376)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Solitary confinement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90376&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is convicted of an offence for which under this`
  line `Sanhita the Court has power to sentence him to rigorous imprisonment, the Court may, by its sentence,`
  line `order that the offender shall be kept in solitary confinement for any portion or portions of the`
  line `imprisonment to which he is sentenced, not exceeding three months in the whole, according to the`
  line `following scale, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) a time not exceeding one month if the term of imprisonment shall not exceed six months;`
  line
  line `(b) a time not exceeding two months if the term of imprisonment shall exceed six months and`
  line `shall not exceed one year;`
  line
  line `(c) a time not exceeding three months if the term of imprisonment shall exceed one year.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (90377)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Limit of solitary confinement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90377&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `In executing a sentence of solitary confinement, such`
  line `confinement shall in no case exceed fourteen days at a time, with intervals between the periods of solitary`
  line `confinement of not less duration than such periods; and when the imprisonment awarded shall exceed`
  line `three months, the solitary confinement shall not exceed seven days in any one month of the whole`
  line `imprisonment awarded, with intervals between the periods of solitary confinement of not less duration`
  line `than such periods.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (90378)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Enhanced punishment for certain offences after previous conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90378&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having been`
  line `convicted by a Court in India, of an offence punishable under Chapter X or Chapter XVII of this Sanhita`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term of three years or upwards, shall be guilty of any`
  line `offence punishable under either of those Chapters with like imprisonment for the like term, shall be`
  line `subject for every such subsequent offence to imprisonment for life, or to imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to ten years.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (90379)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Act done by a person bound, or by mistake of fact believing himself bound, by law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90379&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by a person who is, or who by reason of a mistake of fact and not by`
  line `reason of a mistake of law in good faith believes himself to be, bound by law to do it.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, a soldier, fires on a mob by the order of his superior officer, in conformity with the`
  line `commands of the law. A has committed no offence.`
  line
  line `(b) A, an officer of a Court, being ordered by that Court to arrest Y, and, after due enquiry,`
  line `believing Z to be Y, arrests Z. A has committed no offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (90380)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Act of Judge when acting judicially.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90380&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by a Judge when`
  line `acting judicially in the exercise of any power which is, or which in good faith he believes to be, given to`
  line `him by law.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (90381)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Act done pursuant to judgment or order of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90381&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Nothing which is done in pursuance of, or`
  line `which is warranted by the judgment or order of, a Court; if done whilst such judgment or order remains in`
  line `force, is an offence, notwithstanding the Court may have had no jurisdiction to pass such judgment or`
  line `order, provided the person doing the act in good faith believes that the Court had such jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (90382)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Act done by a person justified, or by mistake of fact believing himself justified, by law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90382&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by any person who is justified by law, or who by reason of a mistake`
  line `of fact and not by reason of a mistake of law in good faith, believes himself to be justified by law, in`
  line `doing it.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A sees Z commit what appears to A to be a murder. A, in the exercise, to the best of his judgment`
  line `exerted in good faith, of the power which the law gives to all persons of apprehending murderers in the`
  line `fact, seizes Z, in order to bring Z before the proper authorities. A has committed no offence, though it`
  line `may turn out that Z was acting in self-defence.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (90383)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Accident in doing a lawful act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90383&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by accident or misfortune,`
  line `and without any criminal intention or knowledge in the doing of a lawful act in a lawful manner by lawful`
  line `means and with proper care and caution.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A is at work with a hatchet; the head flies off and kills a man who is standing by. Here, if there was`
  line `no want of proper caution on the part of A, his act is excusable and not an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (90384)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Act likely to cause harm, but done without criminal intent, and to prevent other harm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90384&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence merely by reason of its being done with the knowledge that it is likely to cause`
  line `harm, if it be done without any criminal intention to cause harm, and in good faith for the purpose of`
  line `preventing or avoiding other harm to person or property.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—It is a question of fact in such a case whether the harm to be prevented or avoided was`
  line `of such a nature and so imminent as to justify or excuse the risk of doing the act with the knowledge that`
  line `it was likely to cause harm.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, the captain of a vessel, suddenly and without any fault or negligence on his part, finds himself`
  line `in such a position that, before he can stop his vessel, he must inevitably run down a boat B, with twenty`
  line `or thirty passengers on board, unless he changes the course of his vessel, and that, by changing his`
  line `course, he must incur risk of running down a boat C with only two passengers on board, which he may`
  line `possibly clear. Here, if A alters his course without any intention to run down the boat C and in good faith`
  line `for the purpose of avoiding the danger to the passengers in the boat B, he is not guilty of an offence,`
  line `though he may run down the boat C by doing an act which he knew was likely to cause that effect, if it be`
  line `found as a matter of fact that the danger which he intended to avoid was such as to excuse him in`
  line `incurring the risk of running down the boat C.`
  line
  line `(b) A, in a great fire, pulls down houses in order to prevent the conflagration from spreading. He does`
  line `this with the intention in good faith of saving human life or property. Here, if it be found that the harm to`
  line `be prevented was of such a nature and so imminent as to excuse A’s act, A is not guilty of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (90385)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Act of a child under seven years of age.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90385&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by a child under`
  line `seven years of age.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (90386)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Act of a child above seven and under twelve years of age of immature understanding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90386&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by a child above seven years of age and under twelve years of age,`
  line `who has not attained sufficient maturity of understanding to judge of the nature and consequences of his`
  line `conduct on that occasion.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (90387)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Act of a person of unsound mind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90387&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by a person who, at the`
  line `time of doing it, by reason of unsoundness of mind, is incapable of knowing the nature of the act, or that`
  line `he is doing what is either wrong or contrary to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (90388)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Act of a person incapable of judgment by reason of intoxication caused against his will.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90388&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done by a person who, at the time of doing it, is, by reason of intoxication,`
  line `incapable of knowing the nature of the act, or that he is doing what is either wrong, or contrary to law;`
  line `provided that the thing which intoxicated him was administered to him without his knowledge or against`
  line `his will.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (90389)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Offence requiring a particular intent or knowledge committed by one who is intoxicated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90389&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `In cases where an act done is not an offence unless done with a particular knowledge or intent, a person`
  line `who does the act in a state of intoxication shall be liable to be dealt with as if he had the same knowledge as he would have had if he had not been intoxicated, unless the thing which intoxicated him was`
  line `administered to him without his knowledge or against his will.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (90390)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Act not intended and not known to be likely to cause death or grievous hurt, done by consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90390&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Nothing which is not intended to cause death, or grievous hurt, and which is not known by the`
  line `doer to be likely to cause death or grievous hurt, is an offence by reason of any harm which it may cause,`
  line `or be intended by the doer to cause, to any person, above eighteen years of age, who has given consent,`
  line `whether express or implied, to suffer that harm; or by reason of any harm which it may be known by the`
  line `doer to be likely to cause to any such person who has consented to take the risk of that harm..`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A and Z agree to fence with each other for amusement. This agreement implies the consent of each to`
  line `suffer any harm which, in the course of such fencing, may be caused without foul play; and if A, while`
  line `playing fairly, hurts Z, A commits no offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (90391)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Act not intended to cause death, done by consent in good faith for person's benefit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90391&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Nothing, which is not intended to cause death, is an offence by reason of any harm which it may cause, or`
  line `be intended by the doer to cause, or be known by the doer to be likely to cause, to any person for whose`
  line `benefit it is done in good faith, and who has given a consent, whether express or implied, to suffer that`
  line `harm, or to take the risk of that harm.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, a surgeon, knowing that a particular operation is likely to cause the death of Z, who suffers under`
  line `the painful complaint, but not intending to cause Zs death, and intending, in good faith, Zs benefit,`
  line `performs that operation on Z, with Zs consent. A has committed no offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (90725)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Act done in good faith for benefit of child or person of unsound mind, by, or by consent of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90725&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Nothing which is done in good faith for the benefit of a person under twelve years of age, or`
  line `person of unsound mind, by, or by consent, either express or implied, of the guardian or other person`
  line `having lawful charge of that person, is an offence by reason of any harm which it may cause, or be`
  line `intended by the doer to cause or be known by the doer to be likely to cause to that person:`
  line
  line `Provided that this exception shall not extend to---`
  line
  line `(a) the intentional causing of death, or to the attempting to cause death;`
  line
  line `(b) the doing of anything which the person doing it knows to be likely to cause death, for any`
  line `purpose other than the preventing of death or grievous hurt, or the curing of any grievous disease or`
  line infirmity;
  line
  line `(c) the voluntary causing of grievous hurt, or to the attempting to cause grievous hurt, unless it be`
  line `for the purpose of preventing death or grievous hurt, or the curing of any grievous disease or`
  line infirmity;
  line
  line `(d) the abetment of any offence, to the committing of which offence it would not extend.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, in good faith, for his child's benefit without his child's consent, has his child cut for the stone by a`
  line `surgeon knowing it to be likely that the operation will cause the child's death, but not intending to cause`
  line `the child's death. A is within the exception, in as much as his object was the cure of the child.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (90393)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Consent known to be given under fear or misconception.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90393&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `A consent is not such a consent as`
  line `is intended by any section of this Sanhita,—.`
  line
  line `(a) if the consent is given by a person under fear of injury, or under a misconception of fact, and`
  line `if the person doing the act knows, or has reason to believe, that the consent was given in consequence`
  line `of such fear or misconception; or.`
  line
  line `(b) if the consent is given by a person who, from unsoundness of mind, or intoxication, is unable`
  line `to understand the nature and consequence of that to which he gives his consent; or.`
  line
  line `(c) unless the contrary appears from the context, if the consent is given by a person who is under`
  line `twelve years of age.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (90394)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Exclusion of acts which are offences independently of harm caused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90394&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The exceptions in`
  line `sections 25, 26 and 27 do not extend to acts which are offences independently of any harm which they`
  line `may cause, or be intended to cause, or be known to be likely to cause, to the person giving the consent, or`
  line `on whose behalf the consent is given.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `Causing miscarriage (unless caused in good faith for the purpose of saving the life of the woman) is`
  line `an offence independently of any harm which it may cause or be intended to cause to the woman.`
  line `Therefore, it is not an offence "by reason of such harm"; and the consent of the woman or of her guardian`
  line `to the causing of such miscarriage does not justify the act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (90395)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Act done in good faith for benefit of a person without consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90395&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence by`
  line `reason of any harm which it may cause to a person for whose benefit it is done in good faith, even`
  line `without that person's consent, if the circumstances are such that it is impossible for that person to signify`
  line `consent, or if that person is incapable of giving consent, and has no guardian or other person in lawful`
  line `charge of him from whom it is possible to obtain consent in time for the thing to be done with benefit:`
  line
  line `Provided that this exception shall not extend to--`
  line
  line `(a) the intentional causing of death, or the attempting to cause death;`
  line
  line `(b) the doing of anything which the person doing it knows to be likely to cause death, for any`
  line `purpose other than the preventing of death or grievous hurt, or the curing of any grievous disease or`
  line infirmity;
  line
  line `(c) the voluntary causing of hurt, or to the attempting to cause hurt, for any purpose other than`
  line `the preventing of death or hurt;`
  line
  line `(d) the abetment of any offence, to the committing of which offence it would not extend.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(1) Z is thrown from his horse, and is insensible. A, a surgeon, finds that Z requires to be trepanned.`
  line
  line `A, not intending Zs death, but in good faith, for Z's benefit, performs the trepan before Z recovers his`
  line `power of judging for himself. A has committed no offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Z is carried off by a tiger. A fires at the tiger knowing it to be likely that the shot may kill Z, but`
  line `not intending to kill Z, and in good faith intending Z's benefit. A's bullet gives Z a mortal wound. A has`
  line `committed no offence.`
  line
  line `(3) A, a surgeon, sees a child suffer an accident which is likely to prove fatal unless an operation be`
  line `immediately performed. There is no time to apply to the child's guardian. A performs the operation in`
  line `spite of the entreaties of the child, intending, in good faith, the child's benefit. A has committed no`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(4) A is in a house which is on fire, with Z, a child. People below hold out a blanket. A drops the`
  line `child from the house top, knowing it to be likely that the fall may kill the child, but not intending to kill`
  line `the child, and intending, in good faith, the child's benefit. Here, even if the child is killed by the fall, A`
  line `has committed no offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---Mere pecuniary benefit is not benefit within the meaning of sections 26, 27 and this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (90396)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Communication made in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90396&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No communication made in good faith is an offence by`
  line `reason of any harm to the person to whom it is made, if it is made for the benefit of that person.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, a surgeon, in good faith, communicates to a patient his opinion that he cannot live. The patient`
  line `dies in consequence of the shock. A has committed no offence, though he knew it to be likely that the`
  line `communication might cause the patient's death.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (90397)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Act to which a person is compelled by threats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90397&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Except murder, and offences against the State`
  line `punishable with death, nothing is an offence which is done by a person who is compelled to do it by`
  line `threats, which, at the time of doing it, reasonably cause the apprehension that instant death to that person`
  line `will otherwise be the consequence:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person doing the act did not of his own accord, or from a reasonable apprehension`
  line `of harm to himself short of instant death, place himself in the situation by which he became subject to`
  line `such constraint.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--A person who, of his own accord, or by reason of a threat of being beaten, joins a`
  line `gang of dacoits, knowing their character, is not entitled to the benefit of this exception, on the ground of`
  line `his having been compelled by his associates to do anything that is an offence by law.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--A person seized by a gang of dacoits, and forced, by threat of instant death, to do a`
  line `thing which is an offence by law; for example, a smith compelled to take his tools and to force the door`
  line `of a house for the dacoits to enter and plunder it, is entitled to the benefit of this exception.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (90398)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Act causing slight harm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90398&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence by reason that it causes, or that it is intended to`
  line `cause, or that it is known to be likely to cause, any harm, if that harm is so slight that no person of`
  line `ordinary sense and temper would complain of such harm.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (90399)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Things done in private defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90399&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is an offence which is done in the exercise of the`
  line `right of private defence.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (90400)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Right of private defence of body and of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90400&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Every person has a right, subject to the`
  line `restrictions contained in section 37, to defend—.`
  line
  line `(a) his own body, and the body of any other person, against any offence affecting the human`
  line body;.
  line
  line `(b) the property, whether movable or immovable, of himself or of any other person, against any`
  line `act which is an offence falling under the definition of theft, robbery, mischief or criminal trespass, or`
  line `which is an attempt to commit theft, robbery, mischief or criminal trespass.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (90401)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Right of private defence against act of a person of unsound mind, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90401&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `When an act, which`
  line `would otherwise be a certain offence, is not that offence, by reason of the youth, the want of maturity of`
  line `understanding, the unsoundness of mind or the intoxication of the person doing that act, or by reason of`
  line `any misconception on the part of that person, every person has the same right of private defence against`
  line `that act which he would have if the act were that offence.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) Z, a person of unsound mind, attempts to kill A; Z is guilty of no offence. But A has the same`
  line `right of private defence which he would have if Z were sane.`
  line
  line `(b) A enters by night a house which he is legally entitled to enter. Z, in good faith, taking A for a`
  line `house-breaker, attacks A. Here Z, by attacking A under this misconception, commits no offence. But A`
  line `has the same right of private defence against Z, which he would have if Z were not acting under that`
  line misconception.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (90402)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Acts against which there is no right of private defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90402&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) There is no right of private`
  line `defence, —`
  line
  line `(a) against an act which does not reasonably cause the apprehension of death or of grievous hurt,`
  line `if done, or attempted to be done, by a public servant acting in good faith under colour of his office,`
  line `though that act, may not be strictly justifiable by law;`
  line
  line `(b) against an act which does not reasonably cause the apprehension of death or of grievous hurt,`
  line `if done, or attempted to be done, by the direction of a public servant acting in good faith under colour`
  line `of his office, though that direction may not be strictly justifiable by law;`
  line
  line `(c) in cases in which there is time to have recourse to the protection of the public authorities.`
  line
  line `(2) The right of private defence in no case extends to the inflicting of more harm than it is necessary`
  line `to inflict for the purpose of defence.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A person is not deprived of the right of private defence against an act done, or`
  line `attempted to be done, by a public servant, as such, unless he knows or has reason to believe, that the`
  line `person doing the act is such public servant.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—A person is not deprived of the right of private defence against an act done, or`
  line `attempted to be done, by the direction of a public servant, unless he knows, or has reason to believe, that`
  line `the person doing the act is acting by such direction, or unless such person states the authority under which`
  line `he acts, or if he has authority in writing, unless he produces such authority, if demanded.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (90403)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `When right of private defence of body extends to causing death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90403&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The right of private`
  line `defence of the body extends, under the restrictions specified in section 37, to the voluntary causing of`
  line `death or of any other harm to the assailant, if the offence which occasions the exercise of the right be of`
  line `any of the descriptions hereinafter enumerated, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) such an assault as may reasonably cause the apprehension that death will otherwise be the`
  line `consequence of such assault;`
  line
  line `(b) such an assault as may reasonably cause the apprehension that grievous hurt will otherwise be`
  line `the consequence of such assault;`
  line
  line `(c) an assault with the intention of committing rape;`
  line
  line `(d) an assault with the intention of gratifying unnatural lust;`
  line
  line `(e) an assault with the intention of kidnapping or abducting;`
  line
  line `(f) an assault with the intention of wrongfully confining a person, under circumstances which`
  line `may reasonably cause him to apprehend that he will be unable to have recourse to the public`
  line `authorities for his release;`
  line
  line `(g) an act of throwing or administering acid or an attempt to throw or administer acid which may`
  line `reasonably cause the apprehension that grievous hurt will otherwise be the consequence of such act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (90404)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `When such right extends to causing any harm other than death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90404&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `If the offence be not of any`
  line `of the descriptions specified in section 38, the right of private defence of the body does not extend to the`
  line `voluntary causing of death to the assailant, but does extend, under the restrictions specified in section 37,`
  line `to the voluntary causing to the assailant of any harm other than death.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (90405)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Commencement and continuance of right of private defence of body.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90405&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The right of private`
  line `defence of the body commences as soon as a reasonable apprehension of danger to the body arises from`
  line `an attempt or threat to commit the offence though the offence may not have been committed; and it`
  line `continues as long as such apprehension of danger to the body continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (90406)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `When right of private defence of property extends to causing death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90406&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The right of private`
  line `defence of property extends, under the restrictions specified in section 37, to the voluntary causing of`
  line `death or of any other harm to the wrong-doer, if the offence, the committing of which, or the attempting`
  line `to commit which, occasions the exercise of the right, be an offence of any of the descriptions hereinafter`
  line `enumerated, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) robbery;`
  line
  line `(b) house-breaking after sunset and before sunrise;`
  line
  line `(c) mischief by fire or any explosive substance committed on any building, tent or vessel, which`
  line `building, tent or vessel is used as a human dwelling, or as a place for the custody of property;`
  line
  line `(d) theft, mischief, or house-trespass, under such circumstances as may reasonably cause`
  line `apprehension that death or grievous hurt will be the consequence, if such right of private defence is`
  line `not exercised.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (90407)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `When such right extends to causing any harm other than death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90407&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If the offence, the`
  line `committing of which, or the attempting to commit which occasions the exercise of the right of private`
  line `defence, be theft, mischief, or criminal trespass, not of any of the descriptions specified in section 41, that`
  line `right does not extend to the voluntary causing of death, but does extend, subject to the restrictions`
  line `specified in section 37, to the voluntary causing to the wrong-doer of any harm other than death.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (90408)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Commencement and continuance of right of private defence of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90408&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The right of`
  line `private defence of property,—`
  line
  line `(a) commences when a reasonable apprehension of danger to the property commences;`
  line
  line `(b) against theft continues till the offender has effected his retreat with the property or either the`
  line `assistance of the public authorities is obtained, or the property has been recovered;`
  line
  line `(c) against robbery continues as long as the offender causes or attempts to cause to any person`
  line `death or hurt or wrongful restraint or as long as the fear of instant death or of instant hurt or of instant`
  line `personal restraint continues;`
  line
  line `(d) against criminal trespass or mischief continues as long as the offender continues in the`
  line `commission of criminal trespass or mischief;`
  line
  line `(e) against house-breaking after sunset and before sunrise continues as long as the house-trespass`
  line `which has been begun by such house-breaking continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (90409)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Right of private defence against deadly assault when there is risk of harm to innocent person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90409&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If in the exercise of the right of private defence against an assault which reasonably causes the`
  line `apprehension of death, the defender be so situated that he cannot effectually exercise that right without`
  line `risk of harm to an innocent person, his right of private defence extends to the running of that risk.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A is attacked by a mob who attempt to murder him. He cannot effectually exercise his right of private`
  line `defence without firing on the mob, and he cannot fire without risk of harming young children who are`
  line `mingled with the mob. A commits no offence if by so firing he harms any of the children.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (90410)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Abetment of a thing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90410&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `A person abets the doing of a thing, who—`
  line
  line `(a) instigates any person to do that thing; or`
  line
  line `(b) engages with one or more other person or persons in any conspiracy for the doing of that`
  line `thing, if an act or illegal omission takes place in pursuance of that conspiracy, and in order to the`
  line `doing of that thing; or`
  line
  line `(c) intentionally aids, by any act or illegal omission, the doing of that thing.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A person who, by wilful misrepresentation, or by wilful concealment of a material`
  line `fact which he is bound to disclose, voluntarily causes or procures, or attempts to cause or procure, a thing`
  line `to be done, is said to instigate the doing of that thing.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, a public officer, is authorised by a warrant from a Court to apprehend Z. B, knowing that fact and`
  line `also that C is not Z, wilfully represents to A that C is Z and thereby intentionally causes A to apprehend`
  line `C. Here B abets by instigation the apprehension of C.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—Whoever, either prior to or at the time of the commission of an act, does anything in`
  line `order to facilitate the commission of that act, and thereby facilitates the commission thereof, is said to aid`
  line `the doing of that act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (90411)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title Abettor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90411&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `A person abets an offence, who abets either the commission of an offence, or the`
  line `commission of an act which would be an offence, if committed by a person capable by law of committing`
  line `an offence with the same intention or knowledge as that of the abettor.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---The abetment of the illegal omission of an act may amount to an offence although`
  line `the abettor may not himself be bound to do that act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---To constitute the offence of abetment it is not necessary that the act abetted should`
  line `be committed, or that the effect requisite to constitute the offence should be caused.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A instigates B to murder C. B refuses to do so. A is guilty of abetting B to commit murder.`
  line
  line `(b) A instigates B to murder D. B in pursuance of the instigation stabs D. D recovers from the wound.`
  line `A is guilty of instigating B to commit murder.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.---It is not necessary that the person abetted should be capable by law of committing`
  line `an offence, or that he should have the same guilty intention or knowledge as that of the abettor, or any`
  line `guilty intention or knowledge.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, with a guilty intention, abets a child or a person of unsound mind to commit an act which`
  line `would be an offence, if committed by a person capable by law of committing an offence, and having the`
  line `same intention as A. Here A, whether the act be committed or not, is guilty of abetting an offence.`
  line
  line `(b) A, with the intention of murdering Z, instigates B, a child under seven years of age, to do an act`
  line `which causes Z's death. B, in consequence of the abetment, does the act in the absence of A and thereby`
  line `causes Z's death. Here, though B was not capable by law of committing an offence, A is liable to be`
  line `punished in the same manner as if B had been capable by law of committing an offence, and had`
  line `committed murder, and he is therefore subject to the punishment of death.`
  line
  line `(c) A instigates B to set fire to a dwelling-house. B, in consequence of his unsoundness of mind,`
  line `being incapable of knowing the nature of the act, or that he is doing what is wrong or contrary to law, sets`
  line `fire to the house in consequence of A's instigation. B has committed no offence, but A is guilty of`
  line `abetting the offence of setting fire to a dwelling-house, and is liable to the punishment provided for that`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(d) A, intending to cause a theft to be committed, instigates B to take property belonging to Z out of`
  line `Z's possession. A induces B to believe that the property belongs to A. B takes the property out of Z's`
  line `possession, in good faith, believing it to be A's property. B, acting under this misconception, does not`
  line `take dishonestly, and therefore does not commit theft. But A is guilty of abetting theft, and is liable to the`
  line `same punishment as if B had committed theft.`
  line
  line `Explanation 4.---The abetment of an offence being an offence, the abetment of such an abetment is`
  line `also an offence.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A instigates B to instigate C to murder Z. B accordingly instigates C to murder Z, and C commits that`
  line `offence in consequence of B's instigation. B is liable to be punished for his offence with the punishment`
  line `for murder; and, as A instigated B to commit the offence, A is also liable to the same punishment.`
  line
  line `Explanation 5.---It is not necessary to the commission of the offence of abetment by conspiracy that`
  line `the abettor should concert the offence with the person who commits it. It is sufficient if he engages in the`
  line `conspiracy in pursuance of which the offence is committed.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A concerts with B a plan for poisoning Z. It is agreed that A shall administer the poison. B then`
  line `explains the plan to C mentioning that a third person is to administer the poison, but without mentioning`
  line `A's name. C agrees to procure the poison, and procures and delivers it to B for the purpose of its being`
  line `used in the manner explained. A administers the poison; Z dies in consequence. Here, though A and C`
  line `have not conspired together, yet C has been engaged in the conspiracy in pursuance of which Z has been`
  line `murdered. C has therefore committed the offence defined in this section and is liable to the punishment`
  line `for murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (90412)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Abetment in India of offences outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90412&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `A person abets an offence within the meaning of`
  line `this Sanhita who, in India, abets the commission of any act without and beyond India which would`
  line `constitute an offence if committed in India.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, in India, instigates B, a foreigner in country X, to commit a murder in that country, A is guilty of`
  line `abetting murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (90413)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Abetment outside India for offence in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90413&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `A person abets an offence within the meaning of`
  line `this Sanhita who, without and beyond India, abets the commission of any act in India which would`
  line `constitute an offence if committed in India.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, in country X, instigates B, to commit a murder in India, A is guilty of abetting murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (90726)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Punishment of abetment if act abetted is committed in consequence and where no express provision is made for its punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90726&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets any offence shall, if the act abetted is`
  line `committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made by this Sanhita for the`
  line `punishment of such abetment, be punished with the punishment provided for the offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—An act or offence is said to be committed in consequence of abetment, when it is`
  line `committed in consequence of the instigation, or in pursuance of the conspiracy, or with the aid which`
  line `constitutes the abetment.`
  line
  line llustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A instigates B to give false evidence. B, in consequence of the instigation, commits that offence.`
  line `A is guilty of abetting that offence, and is liable to the same punishment as B.`
  line
  line `(b) A and B conspire to poison Z. A, in pursuance of the conspiracy, procures the poison and delivers`
  line `it to B in order that he may administer it to Z. B, in pursuance of the conspiracy, administers the poison to`
  line `Z in A’s absence and thereby causes Z’s death. Here B is guilty of murder. A is guilty of abetting that`
  line `offence by conspiracy, and is liable to the punishment for murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (90727)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Punishment of abetment if person abetted does act with different intention from that of abettor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90727&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the commission of an offence shall, if the person abetted does the act with a`
  line `different intention or knowledge from that of the abettor, be punished with the punishment provided for`
  line `the offence which would have been committed if the act had been done with the intention or knowledge`
  line `of the abettor and with no other.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (90416)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Liability of abettor when one act abetted and different act done.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90416&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `When an act is abetted and`
  line `a different act is done, the abettor is liable for the act done, in the same manner and to the same extent as`
  line `if he had directly abetted it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the act done was a probable consequence of the abetment, and was committed under`
  line `the influence of the instigation, or with the aid or in pursuance of the conspiracy which constituted the`
  line abetment.
  line
  line llustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A instigates a child to put poison into the food of Z, and gives him poison for that purpose. The`
  line `child, in consequence of the instigation, by mistake puts the poison into the food of Y, which is by the`
  line `side of that of Z. Here, if the child was acting under the influence of A’s instigation, and the act done was`
  line `under the circumstances a probable consequence of the abetment, A is liable in the same manner and to`
  line `the same extent as if he had instigated the child to put the poison into the food of Y.`
  line
  line `(b) A instigates B to burn Z’s house, B sets fire to the house and at the same time commits theft of`
  line `property there. A, though guilty of abetting the burning of the house, is not guilty of abetting the theft; for`
  line `the theft was a distinct act, and not a probable consequence of the burning.`
  line
  line `(c) A instigates B and C to break into an inhabited house at midnight for the purpose of robbery, and`
  line `provides them with arms for that purpose. B and C break into the house, and being resisted by Z, one of`
  line `the inmates, murder Z. Here, if that murder was the probable consequence of the abetment, A is liable to`
  line `the punishment provided for murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (90417)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Abettor when liable to cumulative punishment for act abetted and for act done.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90417&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If the act`
  line `for which the abettor is liable under section 51 is committed in addition to the act abetted, and constitute`
  line `a distinct offence, the abettor is liable to punishment for each of the offences.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A instigates B to resist by force a distress made by a public servant. B, in consequence, resists that`
  line `distress. In offering the resistance, B voluntarily causes grievous hurt to the officer executing the distress.`
  line `As B has committed both the offence of resisting the distress, and the offence of voluntarily causing`
  line `grievous hurt, B is liable to punishment for both these offences; and, if A knew that B was likely`
  line `voluntarily to cause grievous hurt in resisting the distress, A will also be liable to punishment for each of`
  line `the offences.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (90418)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Liability of abettor for an effect caused by act abetted different from that intended by abettor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90418&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `When an act is abetted with the intention on the part of the abettor of causing a particular`
  line `effect, and an act for which the abettor is liable in consequence of the abetment, causes a different effect`
  line `from that intended by the abettor, the abettor is liable for the effect caused, in the same manner and to the`
  line `same extent as if he had abetted the act with the intention of causing that effect, provided he knew that`
  line `the act abetted was likely to cause that effect.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A instigates B to cause grievous hurt to Z. B, in consequence of the instigation, causes grievous hurt`
  line `to Z. Z dies in consequence. Here, if A knew that the grievous hurt abetted was likely to cause death, A is`
  line `liable to be punished with the punishment provided for murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (90419)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Abettor present when offence is committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90419&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person, who is absent would be`
  line `liable to be punished as an abettor, is present when the act or offence for which he would be punishable in`
  line `consequence of the abetment is committed, he shall be deemed to have committed such act or offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (90420)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Abetment of offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90420&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the`
  line `commission of an offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life, shall, if that offence be not`
  line `committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made under this Sanhita for the`
  line `punishment of such abetment, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine; and if any act for which the abettor is liable in`
  line `consequence of the abetment, and which causes hurt to any person, is done, the abettor shall be liable to`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to fourteen years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A instigates B to murder Z. The offence is not committed. If B had murdered Z, he would have been`
  line `subject to the punishment of death or imprisonment for life. Therefore, A is liable to imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to seven years and also to a fine; and if any hurt be done to Z in consequence of the abetment, he will be liable to imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years, and to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (90421)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Abetment of offence punishable with imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90421&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets an offence punishable`
  line `with imprisonment shall, if that offence be not committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express`
  line `provision is made under this Sanhita for the punishment of such abetment, be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of any description provided for that offence for a term which may extend to one-fourth part`
  line `of the longest term provided for that offence; or with such fine as is provided for that offence, or with`
  line `both; and if the abettor or the person abetted is a public servant, whose duty it is to prevent the`
  line `commission of such offence, the abettor shall be punished with imprisonment of any description provided`
  line `for that offence, for a term which may extend to one-half of the longest term provided for that offence, or`
  line `with such fine as is provided for the offence, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A instigates B to give false evidence. Here, if B does not give false evidence, A has nevertheless`
  line `committed the offence defined in this section, and is punishable accordingly.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a police officer, whose duty it is to prevent robbery, abets the commission of robbery. Here,`
  line `though the robbery be not committed, A is liable to one-half of the longest term of imprisonment`
  line `provided for that offence, and also to fine.`
  line
  line `(c) B abets the commission of a robbery by A, a police officer, whose duty it is to prevent that`
  line `offence. Here, though the robbery be not committed, B is liable to one-half of the longest term of`
  line `imprisonment provided for the offence of robbery, and also to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (90422)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Abetting commission of offence by public or by more than ten persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90422&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the`
  line `commission of an offence by the public generally or by any number or class of persons exceeding ten,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years`
  line `and with fine.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A affixes in a public place a placard instigating a sect consisting of more than ten members to meet at`
  line `a certain time and place, for the purpose of attacking the members of an adverse sect, while engaged in a`
  line `procession. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (90423)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Concealing design to commit offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90423&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Whoever intending to facilitate or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby facilitate the commission of`
  line `an offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life, voluntarily conceals by any act or omission, or`
  line `by the use of encryption or any other information hiding tool, the existence of a design to commit such`
  line `offence or makes any representation which he knows to be false respecting such design shall,.`
  line
  line `(a) if that offence be committed, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years; or.`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence be not committed, with imprisonment of either description, for a term which`
  line `may extend to three years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, knowing that dacoity is about to be committed at B, falsely informs the Magistrate that a dacoity is`
  line `about to be committed at C, a place in an opposite direction, and thereby misleads the Magistrate with`
  line `intent to facilitate the commission of the offence. The dacoity is committed at B in pursuance of the`
  line `design. A is punishable under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (90424)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Public servant concealing design to commit offence which it is his duty to prevent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90424&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, intending to facilitate or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby`
  line 33
  line `facilitate the commission of an offence which it is his duty as such public servant to prevent, voluntarily`
  line `conceals, by any act or omission or by the use of encryption or any other information hiding tool, the`
  line `existence of a design to commit such offence, or makes any representation which he knows to be false`
  line `respecting such design shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence be coommitted, be punished with imprisonment of any description provided for`
  line `the offence, for a term which may extend to one-half of the longest term of such imprisonment, or`
  line `with such fine as is provided for that offence, or with both; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence be punishable with death or imprisonment for life, with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to ten years; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the offence be not committed, shall be punished with imprisonment of any description`
  line `provided for the offence for a term which may extend to one-fourth part of the longest term of such`
  line `imprisonment or with such fine as is provided for the offence, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, an officer of police, being legally bound to give information of all designs to commit robbery`
  line `which may come to his knowledge, and knowing that B designs to commit robbery, omits to give such`
  line `information, with intent to so facilitate the commission of that offence.`
  line `Here A has by an illegal omission concealed the existence of B’s design, and is liable to punishment`
  line `according to the provision of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (90425)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Concealing design to commit offence punishable with imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90425&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, intending to`
  line `facilitate or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby facilitate the commission of an offence punishable`
  line `with imprisonment, voluntarily conceals, by any act or illegal omission, the existence of a design to`
  line `commit such offence, or makes any representation which he knows to be false respecting such design`
  line shall,—
  line
  line `(a) if the offence be committed, be punished with imprisonment of the description provided for`
  line `the offence, for a term which may extend to one-fourth; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence be not committed, to one-eighth,`
  line `of the longest term of such imprisonment, or with such fine as is provided for the offence, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (90426)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Criminal conspiracy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90426&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) When two or more persons agree with the common object to do, or`
  line `cause to be done—`
  line
  line `(a) an illegal act; or`
  line
  line `(b) an act which is not illegal by illegal means, such an agreement is designated a criminal`
  line `conspiracy:`
  line
  line `Provided that no agreement except an agreement to commit an offence shall amount to a criminal`
  line `conspiracy unless some act besides the agreement is done by one or more parties to such agreement in`
  line `pursuance thereof.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—It is immaterial whether the illegal act is the ultimate object of such agreement, or is`
  line `merely incidental to that object.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever is a party to a criminal conspiracy,—`
  line
  line `(a) to commit an offence punishable with death, imprisonment for life or rigorous imprisonment`
  line `for a term of two years or upwards, shall, where no express provision is made in this Sanhita for the`
  line `punishment of such a conspiracy, be punished in the same manner as if he had abetted such offence;`
  line
  line `(b) other than a criminal conspiracy to commit an offence punishable as aforesaid shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term not exceeding six months, or with fine or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (90728)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Punishment for attempting to commit offences punishable with imprisonment for life or other imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90728&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Whoever attempts to commit an offence punishable by this Sanhita with`
  line `imprisonment for life or imprisonment, or to cause such an offence to be committed, and in such attempt`
  line `does any act towards the commission of the offence, shall, where no express provision is made by this`
  line `Sanhita for the punishment of such attempt, be punished with imprisonment of any description provided`
  line `for the offence, for a term which may extend to one-half of the imprisonment for life or, as the case may`
  line `be, one-half of the longest term of imprisonment provided for that offence, or with such fine as is`
  line `provided for the offence, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A makes an attempt to steal some jewels by breaking open a box, and finds after so opening the`
  line `box, that there is no jewel in it. He has done an act towards the commission of theft, and therefore is`
  line `guilty under this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A makes an attempt to pick the pocket of Z by thrusting his hand into Z's pocket. A fails in the`
  line `attempt in consequence of Z's having nothing in his pocket. A is guilty under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (90428)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title Rape.
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90428&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `A man is said to commit "rape" if he---`
  line
  line `(a) penetrates his penis, to any extent, into the vagina, mouth, urethra or anus of a woman or`
  line `makes her to do so with him or any other person; or`
  line
  line `(b) inserts, to any extent, any object or a part of the body, not being the penis, into the vagina, the`
  line `urethra or anus of a woman or makes her to do so with him or any other person; or`
  line
  line `(c) manipulates any part of the body of a woman so as to cause penetration into the vagina,`
  line `urethra, anus or any part of body of such woman or makes her to do so with him or any other person;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) applies his mouth to the vagina, anus, urethra of a woman or makes her to do so with him or`
  line `any other person,`
  line
  line `under the circumstances falling under any of the following seven descriptions:`
  line
  line `(i) against her will;`
  line
  line `(ii) without her consent;`
  line
  line `(iii) with her consent, when her consent has been obtained by putting her or any person in whom`
  line `she is interested, in fear of death or of hurt;`
  line
  line `(iv) with her consent, when the man knows that he is not her husband and that her consent is`
  line `given because she believes that he is another man to whom she is or believes herself to be lawfully`
  line married;
  line
  line `(v) with her consent when, at the time of giving such consent, by reason of unsoundness of mind`
  line `or intoxication or the administration by him personally or through another of any stupefying or`
  line `unwholesome substance, she is unable to understand the nature and consequences of that to which`
  line `she gives consent;`
  line
  line `(vi) with or without her consent, when she is under eighteen years of age;`
  line
  line `(vii) when she is unable to communicate consent.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---For the purposes of this section, "vagina" shall also include labia majora.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---Consent means an unequivocal voluntary agreement when the woman by words,`
  line `gestures or any form of verbal or non-verbal communication, communicates willingness to`
  line `participate in the specific sexual act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a woman who does not physically resist to the act of penetration shall not by the`
  line `reason only of that fact, be regarded as consenting to the sexual activity.`
  line
  line `Exception 1.---A medical procedure or intervention shall not constitute rape.`
  line
  line `Exception 2.---Sexual intercourse or sexual acts by a man with his own wife, the wife not being under`
  line `eighteen years of age, is not rape.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (90429)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Punishment for rape.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90429&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, except in the cases provided for in sub-section (2),`
  line `commits rape, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment of either description for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than ten years, but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever,---`
  line
  line `(a) being a police officer, commits rape,---`
  line
  line `(i) within the limits of the police station to which such police officer is appointed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the premises of any station house; or`
  line
  line `(iii) on a woman in such police officer's custody or in the custody of a police officer`
  line `subordinate to such police officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) being a public servant, commits rape on a woman in such public servant's custody or in the`
  line `custody of a public servant subordinate to such public servant; or`
  line
  line `(c) being a member of the armed forces deployed in an area by the Central Government or a`
  line `State Government commits rape in such area; or`
  line
  line `(d) being on the management or on the staff of a jail, remand home or other place of custody`
  line `established by or under any law for the time being in force or of a women's or children's institution,`
  line `commits rape on any inmate of such jail, remand home, place or institution; or`
  line
  line `(e) being on the management or on the staff of a hospital, commits rape on a woman in that`
  line `hospital; or`
  line
  line `(f) being a relative, guardian or teacher of, or a person in a position of trust or authority towards`
  line `the woman, commits rape on such woman; or`
  line
  line `(g) commits rape during communal or sectarian violence; or`
  line
  line `(h) commits rape on a woman knowing her to be pregnant; or`
  line
  line `(i) commits rape, on a woman incapable of giving consent; or`
  line
  line `(j) being in a position of control or dominance over a woman, commits rape on such woman; or`
  line
  line `(k) commits rape on a woman suffering from mental or physical disability; or`
  line
  line `(l) while committing rape causes grievous bodily harm or maims or disfigures or endangers the`
  line `life of a woman; or`
  line
  line `(m) commits rape repeatedly on the same woman,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ten years, but which`
  line `may extend to imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of that person's`
  line `natural life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section,`
  line
  line `(a) "armed forces" means the naval, army and air forces and includes any member of the Armed`
  line `Forces constituted under any law for the time being in force, including the paramilitary forces and`
  line `any auxiliary forces that are under the control of the Central Government or the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "hospital" means the precincts of the hospital and includes the precincts of any institution for`
  line `the reception and treatment of persons during convalescence or of persons requiring medical attention`
  line `or rehabilitation;`
  line
  line `(c) "police officer" shall have the same meaning as assigned to the expression "police" under the`
  line `Police Act, 1861 (5 of 1861);`
  line
  line `(d) "women's or children's institution" means an institution, whether called an orphanage or a`
  line `home for neglected women or children or a widow's home or an institution called by any other name,`
  line `which is established and maintained for the reception and care of women or children.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (90430)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Punishment for rape in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90430&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, commits rape on a woman under sixteen`
  line `years of age shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than twenty`
  line `years, but which may extend to imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder`
  line `of that person's natural life, and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fine shall be just and reasonable to meet the medical expenses and rehabilitation`
  line `of the victim:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any fine imposed under this sub-section shall be paid to the victim.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, commits rape on a woman under twelve years of age shall be punished with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than twenty years, but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of that persons natural life, and`
  line `with fine or with death:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fine shall be just and reasonable to meet the medical expenses and rehabilitation`
  line `of the victim:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any fine imposed under this sub-section shall be paid to the victim.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (90431)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Punishment for causing death or resulting in persistent vegetative state of victim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90431&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, commits an offence punishable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 64 and in the`
  line `course of such commission inflicts an injury which causes the death of the woman or causes the woman`
  line `to be in a persistent vegetative state, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than twenty years, but which may extend to imprisonment for life, which shall mean`
  line `imprisonment for the remainder of that person’s natural life, or with death.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (90432)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Sexual intercourse by husband upon his wife during separation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90432&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Whoever has sexual`
  line `intercourse with his own wife, who is living separately, whether under a decree of separation or`
  line `otherwise, without her consent, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than two years but which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, “sexual intercourse” shall mean any of the acts mentioned in`
  line `clauses (a) to (d) of section 63.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (90433)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Sexual intercourse by a person in authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90433&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being---`
  line
  line `(a) in a position of authority or in a fiduciary relationship; or`
  line
  line `(b) a public servant; or`
  line
  line `(c) superintendent or manager of a jail, remand home or other place of custody established by or`
  line `under any law for the time being in force, or a women's or children's institution; or`
  line
  line `(d) on the management of a hospital or being on the staff of a hospital,`
  line
  line `abuses such position or fiduciary relationship to induce or seduce any woman either in his custody or`
  line `under his charge or present in the premises to have sexual intercourse with him, such sexual intercourse`
  line `not amounting to the offence of rape, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which shall not be less than five years, but which may extend to ten years, and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- In this section, "sexual intercourse" shall mean any of the acts mentioned in`
  line `clauses (a) to (d) of section 63.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- For the purposes of this section, Explanation 1 to section 63 shall also be`
  line applicable.
  line
  line `Explanation 3.--- "Superintendent", in relation to a jail, remand home or other place of custody or a`
  line `women's or children's institution, includes a person holding any other office in such jail, remand home,`
  line `place or institution by virtue of which such person can exercise any authority or control over its inmates.`
  line
  line `Explanation 4.---The expressions "hospital" and "women's or children's institution" shall`
  line `respectively have the same meanings as in clauses (b) and (d) of the Explanation to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (90434)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Sexual intercourse by employing deceitful means, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90434&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by deceitful means or by`
  line `making promise to marry to a woman without any intention of fulfilling the same, has sexual intercourse`
  line `with her, such sexual intercourse not amounting to the offence of rape, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `Explanation.— “deceitful means” shall include inducement for, or false promise of employment or`
  line `promotion, or marrying by suppressing identity.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (90435)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Gang rape.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90435&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a woman is raped by one or more persons constituting a group or acting`
  line `in furtherance of a common intention, each of those persons shall be deemed to have committed the`
  line `offence of rape and shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `twenty years, but which may extend to imprisonment for life which shall mean imprisonment for the`
  line `remainder of that person's natural life, and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fine shall be just and reasonable to meet the medical expenses and rehabilitation`
  line `of the victim:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any fine imposed under this sub-section shall be paid to the victim.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a woman under eighteen years of age is raped by one or more persons constituting a group`
  line `or acting in furtherance of a common intention, each of those persons shall be deemed to have committed`
  line `the offence of rape and shall be punished with imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for`
  line `the remainder of that person's natural life, and with fine, or with death:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fine shall be just and reasonable to meet the medical expenses and rehabilitation`
  line `of the victim:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any fine imposed under this sub-section shall be paid to the victim.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (90436)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Punishment for repeat offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90436&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Whoever has been previously convicted of an offence`
  line `punishable under section 64 or section 65 or section 66 or section 70 and is subsequently convicted of an`
  line `offence punishable under any of the said sections shall be punished with imprisonment for life which`
  line `shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of that person’s natural life, or with death.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (90437)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Disclosure of identity of victim of certain offences, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90437&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever prints or publishes the`
  line `name or any matter which may make known the identity of any person against whom an offence under`
  line `section 64 or section 65 or section 66 or section 67 or section 68 or section 69 or section 70 or section 71`
  line `is alleged or found to have been committed (hereafter in this section referred to as the victim) shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) extends to any printing or publication of the name or any matter which`
  line `may make known the identity of the victim if such printing or publication is—`
  line
  line `(a) by or under the order in writing of the officer-in-charge of the police station or the police`
  line `officer making the investigation into such offence acting in good faith for the purposes of such`
  line `investigation; or`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (90438)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Printing or publishing any matter relating to Court proceedings without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90438&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Whoever prints or publishes any matter in relation to any proceeding before a Court with respect to an`
  line `offence referred to in section 72 without the previous permission of such Court shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `Explanation.---The printing or publication of the judgment of any High Court or the Supreme Court`
  line `does not amount to an offence within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (90439)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Assault or use of criminal force to woman with intent to outrage her modesty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90439&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `assaults or uses criminal force to any woman, intending to outrage or knowing it to be likely that he will`
  line `thereby outrage her modesty, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `shall not be less than one year but which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (90440)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Sexual harassment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90440&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) A man committing any of the following acts:---`
  line
  line `(i) physical contact and advances involving unwelcome and explicit sexual overtures; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a demand or request for sexual favours; or`
  line
  line `(iii) showing pornography against the will of a woman; or`
  line
  line `(iv) making sexually coloured remarks,`
  line
  line `shall be guilty of the offence of sexual harassment.`
  line
  line `(2) Any man who commits the offence specified in clause (i) or clause (ii) or clause (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years,`
  line `or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Any man who commits the offence specified in clause (iv) of sub-section (1) shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (90441)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Assault or use of criminal force to woman with intent to disrobe.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90441&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Whoever assaults or uses`
  line `criminal force to any woman or abets such act with the intention of disrobing or compelling her to be`
  line `naked, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `three years but which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (90442)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title Voyeurism.
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90442&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Whoever watches, or captures the image of a woman engaging in a private act in`
  line `circumstances where she would usually have the expectation of not being observed either by the`
  line `perpetrator or by any other person at the behest of the perpetrator or disseminates such image shall be`
  line `punished on first conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than one year, but which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine, and be punished on a`
  line `second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than three years, but which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—For the purposes of this section, “private act” includes an act of watching carried out`
  line `in a place which, in the circumstances, would reasonably be expected to provide privacy and where the victim’s genitals, posterior or breasts are exposed or covered only in underwear; or the victim is using a`
  line `lavatory; or the victim is doing a sexual act that is not of a kind ordinarily done in public.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—Where the victim consents to the capture of the images or any act, but not to their`
  line `dissemination to third persons and where such image or act is disseminated, such dissemination shall be`
  line `considered an offence under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (90443)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title Stalking.
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90443&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any man who---`
  line
  line `(i) follows a woman and contacts, or attempts to contact such woman to foster personal`
  line `interaction repeatedly despite a clear indication of disinterest by such woman; or`
  line
  line `(ii) monitors the use by a woman of the internet, e-mail or any other form of electronic`
  line communication,
  line
  line `commits the offence of stalking:`
  line
  line `Provided that such conduct shall not amount to stalking if the man who pursued it proves that---`
  line
  line `(i) it was pursued for the purpose of preventing or detecting crime and the man accused of`
  line `stalking had been entrusted with the responsibility of prevention and detection of crime by the State;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) it was pursued under any law or to comply with any condition or requirement imposed by any`
  line `person under any law; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the particular circumstances such conduct was reasonable and justified.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits the offence of stalking shall be punished on first conviction with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine; and be`
  line `punished on a second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (90444)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Word, gesture or act intended to insult modesty of a woman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90444&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, intending to insult`
  line `the modesty of any woman, utters any words, makes any sound or gesture, or exhibits any object in any`
  line `form, intending that such word or sound shall be heard, or that such gesture or object shall be seen, by`
  line `such woman, or intrudes upon the privacy of such woman, shall be punished with simple imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years, and also with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (90445)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Dowry death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90445&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the death of a woman is caused by any burns or bodily injury or`
  line `occurs otherwise than under normal circumstances within seven years of her marriage and it is shown that`
  line `soon before her death she was subjected to cruelty or harassment by her husband or any relative of her`
  line `husband for, or in connection with, any demand for dowry, such death shall be called “dowry death”, and`
  line `such husband or relative shall be deemed to have caused her death.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, “dowry” shall have the same meaning as in`
  line `section 2 of the Dowry Prohibition Act, 1961 (28 of 1961).`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits dowry death shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than seven years but which may extend to imprisonment for life.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (90446)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Cohabitation caused by man deceitfully inducing belief of lawful marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90446&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Every man who`
  line `by deceit causes any woman who is not lawfully married to him to believe that she is lawfully married to`
  line `him and to cohabit or have sexual intercourse with him in that belief, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (90447)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Marrying again during lifetime of husband or wife.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90447&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, having a husband or wife`
  line `living, marries in any case in which such marriage is void by reason of its taking place during the life of`
  line `such husband or wife, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Exception.---This sub-section does not extend to any person whose marriage with such husband or`
  line `wife has been declared void by a Court of competent jurisdiction, nor to any person who contracts a`
  line `marriage during the life of a former husband or wife, if such husband or wife, at the time of the`
  line `subsequent marriage, shall have been continually absent from such person for the space of seven years,`
  line `and shall not have been heard of by such person as being alive within that time provided the person`
  line `contracting such subsequent marriage shall, before such marriage takes place, inform the person with`
  line `whom such marriage is contracted of the real state of facts so far as the same are within his or her`
  line knowledge.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits the offence under sub-section (1) having concealed from the person with`
  line `whom the subsequent marriage is contracted, the fact of the former marriage, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (90448)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Marriage ceremony fraudulently gone through without lawful marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90448&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line Whoever,
  line `dishonestly or with a fraudulent intention, goes through the ceremony of being married, knowing that he`
  line `is not thereby lawfully married, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (90449)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Enticing or taking away or detaining with criminal intent a married woman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90449&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `takes or entices away any woman who is and whom he knows or has reason to believe to be the wife of`
  line `any other man, with intent that she may have illicit intercourse with any person, or conceals or detains`
  line `with that intent any such woman, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (90450)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Husband or relative of husband of a woman subjecting her to cruelty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90450&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being the`
  line `husband or the relative of the husband of a woman, subjects such woman to cruelty shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (90451)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Cruelty defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90451&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 85, “cruelty” means—.`
  line
  line `(a) any wilful conduct which is of such a nature as is likely to drive the woman to commit suicide`
  line `or to cause grave injury or danger to life, limb or health (whether mental or physical) of the woman;`
  line or.
  line
  line `(b) harassment of the woman where such harassment is with a view to coercing her or any person`
  line `related to her to meet any unlawful demand for any property or valuable security or is on account of`
  line `failure by her or any person related to her to meet such demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (90452)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Kidnapping, abducting or inducing woman to compel her marriage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90452&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Whoever kidnaps`
  line `or abducts any woman with intent that she may be compelled, or knowing it to be likely that she will be`
  line `compelled, to marry any person against her will, or in order that she may be forced or seduced to illicit`
  line `intercourse, or knowing it to be likely that she will be forced or seduced to illicit intercourse, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine; and whoever, by means of criminal intimidation as defined in this Sanhita or of abuse of`
  line `authority or any other method of compulsion, induces any woman to go from any place with intent that`
  line `she may be, or knowing that it is likely that she will be, forced or seduced to illicit intercourse with`
  line `another person shall also be punishable as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (90453)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Causing miscarriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90453&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Whoever voluntarily causes a woman with child to miscarry, shall, if`
  line `such miscarriage be not caused in good faith for the purpose of saving the life of the woman, be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with`
  line `both; and, if the woman be quick with child, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A woman who causes herself to miscarry, is within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (90454)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Causing miscarriage without woman's consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90454&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits the offence under`
  line `section 88 without the consent of the woman, whether the woman is quick with child or not, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (90455)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Death caused by act done with intent to cause miscarriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90455&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, with intent to`
  line `cause the miscarriage of a woman with child, does any act which causes the death of such woman, shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the act referred to in sub-section (1) is done without the consent of the woman, shall be`
  line `punishable either with imprisonment for life, or with the punishment specified in said sub-section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—It is not essential to this offence that the offender should know that the act is likely to`
  line `cause death.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (90456)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Act done with intent to prevent child being born alive or to cause to die after birth.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90456&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Whoever before the birth of any child does any act with the intention of thereby preventing that child`
  line `from being born alive or causing it to die after its birth, and does by such act prevent that child from`
  line `being born alive, or causes it to die after its birth, shall, if such act be not caused in good faith for the`
  line `purpose of saving the life of the mother, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (90457)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Causing death of quick unborn child by act amounting to culpable homicide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90457&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `does any act under such circumstances, that if he thereby caused death he would be guilty of culpable`
  line `homicide, and does by such act cause the death of a quick unborn child, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, knowing that he is likely to cause the death of a pregnant woman, does an act which, if it caused`
  line `the death of the woman, would amount to culpable homicide. The woman is injured, but does not die; but`
  line `the death of an unborn quick child with which she is pregnant is thereby caused. A is guilty of the offence`
  line `defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (90729)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Exposure and abandonment of child under twelve years of age, by parent or person having care of it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90729&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Whoever being the father or mother of a child under the age of twelve years, or having the`
  line `care of such child, shall expose or leave such child in any place with the intention of wholly abandoning`
  line `such child, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—This section is not intended to prevent the trial of the offender for murder or culpable`
  line `homicide, as the case may be, if the child die in consequence of the exposure.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (90459)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Concealment of birth by secret disposal of dead body.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90459&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by secretly burying or`
  line `otherwise disposing of the dead body of a child whether such child die before or after or during its birth,`
  line `intentionally conceals or endeavours to conceal the birth of such child, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (90460)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Hiring, employing or engaging a child to commit an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90460&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `Whoever hires, employs or`
  line `engages any child to commit an offence shall be punished with imprisonment of either description which`
  line `shall not be less than three years but which may extend to ten years, and with fine; and if the offence be`
  line `committed shall also be punished with the punishment provided for that offence as if the offence has been`
  line `committed by such person himself.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Hiring, employing, engaging or using a child for sexual exploitation or pornography is`
  line `covered within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (90461)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Procuration of child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90461&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by any means whatsoever, induces any child to go from any`
  line `place or to do any act with intent that such child may be, or knowing that it is likely that such child will be, forced or seduced to illicit intercourse with another person shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (90462)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Kidnapping or abducting child under ten years of age with intent to steal from its person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90462&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Whoever kidnaps or abducts any child under the age of ten years with the intention of taking dishonestly`
  line `any movable property from the person of such child, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (90463)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Selling child for purposes of prostitution, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90463&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `Whoever sells, lets to hire, or otherwise`
  line `disposes of any child with intent that such child shall at any age be employed or used for the purpose of`
  line `prostitution or illicit intercourse with any person or for any unlawful and immoral purpose, or knowing it`
  line `to be likely that such child will at any age be employed or used for any such purpose, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---When a female under the age of eighteen years is sold, let for hire, or otherwise`
  line `disposed of to a prostitute or to any person who keeps or manages a brothel, the person so disposing of`
  line `such female shall, until the contrary is proved, be presumed to have disposed of her with the intent that`
  line `she shall be used for the purpose of prostitution.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---For the purposes of this section "illicit intercourse" means sexual intercourse`
  line `between persons not united by marriage or by any union or tie which, though not amounting to a`
  line `marriage, is recognised by the personal law or custom of the community to which they belong or, where`
  line `they belong to different communities, of both such communities, as constituting between them a`
  line `quasi-marital relation.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (90464)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Buying child for purposes of prostitution, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90464&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Whoever buys, hires or otherwise obtains`
  line `possession of any child with intent that such child shall at any age be employed or used for the purpose of`
  line `prostitution or illicit intercourse with any person or for any unlawful and immoral purpose, or knowing it`
  line `to be likely that such child will at any age be employed or used for any such purpose, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than seven years but which`
  line `may extend to fourteen years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—Any prostitute or any person keeping or managing a brothel, who buys, hires or`
  line `otherwise obtains possession of a female under the age of eighteen years shall, until the contrary is`
  line `proved, be presumed to have obtained possession of such female with the intent that she shall be used for`
  line `the purpose of prostitution.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.— “Illicit intercourse” has the same meaning as in section 98.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (90465)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Culpable homicide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90465&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `Whoever causes death by doing an act with the intention of causing`
  line `death, or with the intention of causing such bodily injury as is likely to cause death, or with the`
  line `knowledge that he is likely by such act to cause death, commits the offence of culpable homicide.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A lays sticks and turf over a pit, with the intention of thereby causing death, or with the`
  line `knowledge that death is likely to be thereby caused. Z, believing the ground to be firm, treads on it, falls`
  line `in and is killed. A has committed the offence of culpable homicide.`
  line
  line `(b) A knows Z to be behind a bush. B does not know it. A, intending to cause, or knowing it to be`
  line `likely to cause Z’s death, induces B to fire at the bush. B fires and kills Z. Here B may be guilty of no`
  line `offence; but A has committed the offence of culpable homicide.`
  line
  line `(c) A, by shooting at a fowl with intent to kill and steal it, kills B, who is behind a bush; A not`
  line `knowing that he was there. Here, although A was doing an unlawful act, he was not guilty of culpable homicide, as he did not intend to kill B, or to cause death by doing an act that he knew was likely to cause`
  line death.
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A person who causes bodily injury to another who is labouring under a disorder,`
  line `disease or bodily infirmity, and thereby accelerates the death of that other, shall be deemed to have`
  line `caused his death.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—Where death is caused by bodily injury, the person who causes such bodily injury`
  line `shall be deemed to have caused the death, although by resorting to proper remedies and skilful treatment`
  line `the death might have been prevented.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.—The causing of the death of a child in the mother’s womb is not homicide. But it`
  line `may amount to culpable homicide to cause the death of a living child, if any part of that child has been`
  line `brought forth, though the child may not have breathed or been completely born.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (90466)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title Murder.
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90466&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Except in the cases hereinafter excepted, culpable homicide is murder,---`
  line
  line `(a) if the act by which the death is caused is done with the intention of causing death; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the act by which the death is caused is done with the intention of causing such bodily injury`
  line `as the offender knows to be likely to cause the death of the person to whom the harm is caused; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the act by which the death is caused is done with the intention of causing bodily injury to`
  line `any person and the bodily injury intended to be inflicted is sufficient in the ordinary course of nature`
  line `to cause death; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the person committing the act by which the death is caused, knows that it is so imminently`
  line `dangerous that it must, in all probability, cause death, or such bodily injury as is likely to cause death,`
  line `and commits such act without any excuse for incurring the risk of causing death or such injury as`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A shoots Z with the intention of killing him. Z dies in consequence. A commits murder.`
  line
  line `(b) A, knowing that Z is labouring under such a disease that a blow is likely to cause his death, strikes`
  line `him with the intention of causing bodily injury. Z dies in consequence of the blow. A is guilty of murder,`
  line `although the blow might not have been sufficient in the ordinary course of nature to cause the death of a`
  line `person in a sound state of health. But if A, not knowing that Z is labouring under any disease, gives him`
  line `such a blow as would not in the ordinary course of nature kill a person in a sound state of health, here A,`
  line `although he may intend to cause bodily injury, is not guilty of murder, if he did not intend to cause death,`
  line `or such bodily injury as in the ordinary course of nature would cause death.`
  line
  line `(c) A intentionally gives Z a sword-cut or club-wound sufficient to cause the death of a man in the`
  line `ordinary course of nature. Z dies in consequence. Here A is guilty of murder, although he may not have`
  line `intended to cause Z's death.`
  line
  line `(d) A without any excuse fires a loaded cannon into a crowd of persons and kills one of them. A is`
  line `guilty of murder, although he may not have had a premeditated design to kill any particular individual.`
  line
  line `Exception 1.---Culpable homicide is not murder if the offender, whilst deprived of the power of`
  line `self-control by grave and sudden provocation, causes the death of the person who gave the provocation or`
  line `causes the death of any other person by mistake or accident:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provocation is not,---`
  line
  line `(a) sought or voluntarily provoked by the offender as an excuse for killing or doing harm to any`
  line person;
  line
  line `(b) given by anything done in obedience to the law, or by a public servant in the lawful exercise`
  line `of the powers of such public servant;`
  line
  line `(c) given by anything done in the lawful exercise of the right of private defence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---Whether the provocation was grave and sudden enough to prevent the offence`
  line `from amounting to murder is a question of fact.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, under the influence of passion excited by a provocation given by Z, intentionally kills Y,`
  line `Z's child. This is murder, in as much as the provocation was not given by the child, and the death of`
  line `the child was not caused by accident or misfortune in doing an act caused by the provocation.`
  line
  line `(b) Y gives grave and sudden provocation to A. A, on this provocation, fires a pistol at Y, neither`
  line `intending nor knowing himself to be likely to kill Z, who is near him, but out of sight. A kills Z. Here`
  line `A has not committed murder, but merely culpable homicide.`
  line
  line `(c) A is lawfully arrested by Z, a bailiff. A is excited to sudden and violent passion by the arrest,`
  line `and kills Z. This is murder, in as much as the provocation was given by a thing done by a public`
  line `servant in the exercise of his powers.`
  line
  line `(d) A appears as a witness before Z, a Magistrate. Z says that he does not believe a word of A's`
  line `deposition, and that A has perjured himself. A is moved to sudden passion by these words, and kills Z.`
  line `This is murder.`
  line
  line `(e) A attempts to pull Zs nose. Z, in the exercise of the right of private defence, lays hold of A to`
  line `prevent him from doing so. A is moved to sudden and violent passion in consequence, and kills Z.`
  line `This is murder, in as much as the provocation was giving by a thing done in the exercise of the right of`
  line `private defence.`
  line
  line `(f) Z strikes B. B is by this provocation excited to violent rage. A, a bystander, intending to take`
  line `advantage of B's rage, and to cause him to kill Z, puts a knife into B's hand for that purpose. B kills Z`
  line `with the knife. Here B may have committed only culpable homicide, but A is guilty of murder.`
  line
  line `Exception 2.---Culpable homicide is not murder if the offender in the exercise in good faith of the`
  line `right of private defence of person or property, exceeds the power given to him by law and causes the`
  line `death of the person against whom he is exercising such right of defence without premeditation, and`
  line `without any intention of doing more harm than is necessary for the purpose of such defence.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `Z attempts to horsewhip A, not in such a manner as to cause grievous hurt to A. A draws out a pistol.`
  line `Z persists in the assault. A believing in good faith that he can by no other means prevent himself from`
  line `being horsewhipped, shoots Z dead. A has not committed murder, but only culpable homicide.`
  line
  line `Exception 3.---Culpable homicide is not murder if the offender, being a public servant or aiding a`
  line `public servant acting for the advancement of public justice, exceeds the powers given to him by law, and`
  line `causes death by doing an act which he, in good faith, believes to be lawful and necessary for the due`
  line `discharge of his duty as such public servant and without ill-will towards the person whose death is`
  line caused.
  line
  line `Exception 4.---Culpable homicide is not murder if it is committed without premeditation in a sudden`
  line `fight in the heat of passion upon a sudden quarrel and without the offenders having taken undue`
  line `advantage or acted in a cruel or unusual manner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---It is immaterial in such cases which party offers the provocation or commits the first`
  line assault.
  line
  line `Exception 5.---Culpable homicide is not murder when the person whose death is caused, being above`
  line `the age of eighteen years, suffers death or takes the risk of death with his own consent.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, by instigation, voluntarily causes Z, a child to commit suicide. Here, on account of Z's youth, he`
  line `was incapable of giving consent to his own death; A has therefore abetted murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (90467)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Culpable homicide by causing death of person other than person whose death was intended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90467&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `If a person, by doing anything which he intends or knows to be likely to cause death, commits culpable homicide by causing the death of any person, whose death he neither intends nor`
  line `knows himself to be likely to cause, the culpable homicide committed by the offender is of the`
  line `description of which it would have been if he had caused the death of the person whose death he intended`
  line `or knew himself to be likely to cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (90468)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Punishment for murder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90468&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever commits murder shall be punished with death or`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine..`
  line
  line `(2) When a group of five or more persons acting in concert commits murder on the ground of race,`
  line `caste or community, sex, place of birth, language, personal belief or any other similar ground each`
  line `member of such group shall be punished with death or with imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (90469)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Punishment for murder by life-convict.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90469&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being under sentence of imprisonment for`
  line `life, commits murder, shall be punished with death or with imprisonment for life, which shall mean the`
  line `remainder of that person’s natural life.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (90470)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Punishment for culpable homicide not amounting to murder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90470&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits culpable`
  line `homicide not amounting to murder, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to ten years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine, if the act by which the death is caused is done with the intention of`
  line `causing death, or of causing such bodily injury as is likely to cause death; or with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to ten years and with fine, if the act is done with the knowledge`
  line `that it is likely to cause death, but without any intention to cause death, or to cause such bodily injury as`
  line `is likely to cause death.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (90471)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Causing death by negligence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90471&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever causes death of any person by doing any rash or`
  line `negligent act not amounting to culpable homicide, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to fine; and if such act is`
  line `done by a registered medical practitioner while performing medical procedure, he shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, “registered medical practitioner” means a`
  line `medical practitioner who possesses any medical qualification recognised under the National Medical`
  line `Commission Act, 2019 (30 of 2019) and whose name has been entered in the National Medical Register`
  line `or a State Medical Register under that Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever causes death of any person by rash and negligent driving of vehicle not amounting to`
  line `culpable homicide, and escapes without reporting it to a police officer or a Magistrate soon after the`
  line `incident, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description of a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (90472)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Abetment of suicide of child or person of unsound mind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90472&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `If any child, any person of`
  line `unsound mind, any delirious person or any person in a state of intoxication, commits suicide, whoever`
  line `abets the commission of such suicide, shall be punished with death or imprisonment for life, or`
  line `imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (90473)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Abetment of suicide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90473&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `If any person commits suicide, whoever abets the commission of such`
  line `suicide, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (90474)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Attempt to murder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90474&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever does any act with such intention or knowledge, and under`
  line `such circumstances that, if he by that act caused death, he would be guilty of murder, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine; and if hurt is caused to any person by such act, the offender shall be liable either to imprisonment`
  line `for life, or to such punishment as is hereinbefore mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) When any person offending under sub-section (1) is under sentence of imprisonment for life, he`
  line `may, if hurt is caused, be punished with death or with imprisonment for life, which shall mean the`
  line `remainder of that person's natural life.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A shoots at Z with intention to kill him, under such circumstances that, if death ensued, A would`
  line `be guilty of murder. A is liable to punishment under this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A, with the intention of causing the death of a child of tender years, exposes it in a desert place. A`
  line `has committed the offence defined by this section, though the death of the child does not ensue.`
  line
  line `(c) A, intending to murder Z, buys a gun and loads it. A has not yet committed the offence. A fires`
  line `the gun at Z. He has committed the offence defined in this section, and, if by such firing he wounds Z, he`
  line `is liable to the punishment provided by the latter part of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(d) A, intending to murder Z by poison, purchases poison and mixes the same with food which`
  line `remains in A's keeping; A has not yet committed the offence defined in this section. A places the food on`
  line `Z's table or delivers it to Z's servants to place it on Z's table. A has committed the offence defined in this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (90475)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Attempt to commit culpable homicide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90475&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does any act with such intention or`
  line `knowledge and under such circumstances that, if he by that act caused death, he would be guilty of`
  line `culpable homicide not amounting to murder, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both; and, if hurt is caused to any person`
  line `by such act, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A, on grave and sudden provocation, fires a pistol at Z, under such circumstances that if he thereby`
  line `caused death, he would be guilty of culpable homicide not amounting to murder. A has committed the`
  line `offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (90476)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Organised crime.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90476&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any continuing unlawful activity including kidnapping, robbery,`
  line `vehicle theft, extortion, land grabbing, contract killing, economic offence, cyber-crimes, trafficking of`
  line `persons, drugs, weapons or illicit goods or services, human trafficking for prostitution or ransom, by any`
  line `person or a group of persons acting in concert, singly or jointly, either as a member of an organised crime`
  line `syndicate or on behalf of such syndicate, by use of violence, threat of violence, intimidation, coercion, or`
  line `by any other unlawful means to obtain direct or indirect material benefit including a financial benefit,`
  line `shall constitute organised crime.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section,---`
  line
  line `(i)"organised crime syndicate" means a group of two or more persons who, acting either singly`
  line `or jointly, as a syndicate or gang indulge in any continuing unlawful activity;`
  line
  line `(ii) "continuing unlawful activity" means an activity prohibited by law which is a cognizable`
  line `offence punishable with imprisonment of three years or more, undertaken by any person, either singly`
  line `or jointly, as a member of an organised crime syndicate or on behalf of such syndicate in respect of`
  line `which more than one charge-sheets have been filed before a competent Court within the preceding`
  line `period of ten years and that Court has taken cognizance of such offence, and includes economic`
  line offence;
  line
  line `(iii) "economic offence" includes criminal breach of trust, forgery, counterfeiting of currency-notes, bank-notes and Government stamps, hawala transaction, mass-marketing fraud or running any`
  line `scheme to defraud several persons or doing any act in any manner with a view to defraud any bank or`
  line `financial institution or any other institution or organisation for obtaining monetary benefits in any`
  line form.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits organised crime shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) if such offence has resulted in the death of any person, be punished with death or`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five`
  line `years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine which shall not`
  line `be less than five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever abets, attempts, conspires or knowingly facilitates the commission of an organised`
  line `crime, or otherwise engages in any act preparatory to an organised crime, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to imprisonment`
  line `for life, and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who is a member of an organised crime syndicate shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to imprisonment`
  line `for life, and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever, intentionally, harbours or conceals any person who has committed the offence of an`
  line `organised crime shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years`
  line `but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than`
  line `five lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to any case in which the harbour or concealment is by`
  line `the spouse of the offender.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever possesses any property derived or obtained from the commission of an organised crime`
  line `or proceeds of any organised crime or which has been acquired through the organised crime, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(7) If any person on behalf of a member of an organised crime syndicate is, or at any time has been in`
  line `possession of movable or immovable property which he cannot satisfactorily account for, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for ten years and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (90477)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Petty organised crime.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90477&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, being a member of a group or gang, either singly or`
  line `jointly, commits any act of theft, snatching, cheating, unauthorised selling of tickets, unauthorised betting`
  line `or gambling, selling of public examination question papers or any other similar criminal act, is said to`
  line `commit petty organised crime.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section “theft” includes trick theft, theft from vehicle,`
  line `dwelling house or business premises, cargo theft, pick pocketing, theft through card skimming,`
  line `shoplifting and theft of Automated Teller Machine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits any petty organised crime shall be punished with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (90478)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Terrorist act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90478&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever does any act with the intent to threaten or likely to threaten the`
  line `unity, integrity, sovereignty, security, or economic security of India or with the intent to strike terror or`
  line `likely to strike terror in the people or any section of the people in India or in any foreign country,---`
  line
  line `(a) by using bombs, dynamite or other explosive substance or inflammable substance or firearms`
  line `or other lethal weapons or poisonous or noxious gases or other chemicals or by any other substance`
  line `(whether biological, radioactive, nuclear or otherwise) of a hazardous nature or by any other means`
  line `of whatever nature to cause or likely to cause,---`
  line
  line `(i) death of, or injury to, any person or persons; or`
  line
  line `(ii) loss of, or damage to, or destruction of, property; or`
  line
  line `(iii) disruption of any supplies or services essential to the life of the community in India or in`
  line `any foreign country; or`
  line
  line `(iv) damage to, the monetary stability of India by way of production or smuggling or`
  line `circulation of counterfeit Indian paper currency, coin or of any other material; or`
  line
  line `(v) damage or destruction of any property in India or in a foreign country used or intended to`
  line `be used for the defence of India or in connection with any other purposes of the Government of`
  line `India, any State Government or any of their agencies; or`
  line
  line `(b) overawes by means of criminal force or the show of criminal force or attempts to do so or`
  line `causes death of any public functionary or attempts to cause death of any public functionary; or`
  line
  line `(c) detains, kidnaps or abducts any person and threatening to kill or injure such person or does`
  line `any other act in order to compel the Government of India, any State Government or the Government`
  line `of a foreign country or an international or inter-governmental organisation or any other person to do`
  line `or abstain from doing any act,`
  line
  line `commit a terrorist act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purpose of this sub-section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "public functionary" means the constitutional authorities or any other functionary notified in`
  line `the Official Gazette by the Central Government as public functionary;`
  line
  line `(b) "counterfeit Indian currency" means the counterfeit currency as may be declared after`
  line `examination by an authorised or notified forensic authority that such currency imitates or`
  line `compromises with the key security features of Indian currency.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits a terrorist act shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) if such offence has resulted in the death of any person, be punished with death or`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five`
  line `years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever conspires or attempts to commit, or advocates, abets, advises or incites, directly or`
  line `knowingly facilitates the commission of a terrorist act or any act preparatory to the commission of a`
  line `terrorist act, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but`
  line `which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever organises or causes to be organised any camp or camps for imparting training in terrorist`
  line `act, or recruits or causes to be recruited any person or persons for commission of a terrorist act, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person who is a member of an organisation which is involved in terrorist act, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever voluntarily harbours or conceals, or attempts to harbour or conceal any person knowing`
  line `that such person has committed a terrorist act shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than three years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to any case in which the harbour or concealment is by`
  line `the spouse of the offender.`
  line
  line `(7) Whoever knowingly possesses any property derived or obtained from commission of any terrorist`
  line `act or acquired through the commission of any terrorist act shall be punished with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the officer not below the rank of`
  line `Superintendent of Police shall decide whether to register the case under this section or under the`
  line `Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, 1967 (37 of 1967).`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (90479)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title Hurt.
  content `Whoever causes bodily pain, disease or infirmity to any person is said to cause hurt.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90479&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (90480)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Voluntarily causing hurt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90480&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever does any act with the intention of thereby causing`
  line `hurt to any person, or with the knowledge that he is likely thereby to cause hurt to any person, and does`
  line `thereby cause hurt to any person, is said “voluntarily to cause hurt”.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, except in the case provided for by sub-section (1) of section 122 voluntarily causes`
  line `hurt, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (90481)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Grievous hurt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90481&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `The following kinds of hurt only are designated as “grievous”, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Emasculation;`
  line
  line `(b) Permanent privation of the sight of either eye;`
  line
  line `(c) Permanent privation of the hearing of either ear;`
  line
  line `(d) Privation of any member or joint;`
  line
  line `(e) Destruction or permanent impairing of the powers of any member or joint;`
  line
  line `(f) Permanent disfiguration of the head or face;`
  line
  line `(g) Fracture or dislocation of a bone or tooth;`
  line
  line `(h) Any hurt which endangers life or which causes the sufferer to be during the space of fifteen`
  line `days in severe bodily pain, or unable to follow his ordinary pursuits.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (90482)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Voluntarily causing grievous hurt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90482&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever voluntarily causes hurt, if the hurt which he`
  line `intends to cause or knows himself to be likely to cause is grievous hurt, and if the hurt which he causes is`
  line `grievous hurt, is said “voluntarily to cause grievous hurt”.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A person is not said voluntarily to cause grievous hurt except when he both causes`
  line `grievous hurt and intends or knows himself to be likely to cause grievous hurt. But he is said voluntarily`
  line `to cause grievous hurt, if intending or knowing himself to be likely to cause grievous hurt of one kind, he`
  line `actually causes grievous hurt of another kind.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, intending of knowing himself to be likely permanently to disfigure Z’s face, gives Z a blow which`
  line `does not permanently disfigure Z’s face, but which causes Z to suffer severe bodily pain for the space of`
  line `fifteen days. A has voluntarily caused grievous hurt.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, except in the case provided for by sub-section (2) of section 122, voluntarily causes`
  line `grievous hurt, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits an offence under sub-section (1) and in the course of such commission causes`
  line `any hurt to a person which causes that person to be in permanent disability or in persistent vegetative`
  line `state, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ten years but`
  line `which may extend to imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of that`
  line `person’s natural life.`
  line
  line `(4) When a group of five or more persons acting in concert, causes grievous hurt to a person on the`
  line `ground of his race, caste or community, sex, place of birth, language, personal belief or any other similar`
  line `ground, each member of such group shall be guilty of the offence of causing grievous hurt, and shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (90483)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Voluntarily causing hurt or grievous hurt by dangerous weapons or means.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90483&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever,`
  line `except in the case provided for by sub-section (1) of section 122, voluntarily causes hurt by means of any`
  line `instrument for shooting, stabbing or cutting, or any instrument which, used as a weapon of offence, is likely to cause death, or by means of fire or any heated substance, or by means of any poison or any`
  line `corrosive substance, or by means of any explosive substance, or by means of any substance which it is`
  line `deleterious to the human body to inhale, to swallow, or to receive into the blood, or by means of any`
  line `animal, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to twenty thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, except in the case provided for by sub-section (2) of section 122, voluntarily causes`
  line `grievous hurt by any means referred to in sub-section (1), shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may`
  line `extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (90484)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Voluntarily causing hurt or grievous hurt to extort property, or to constrain to an illegal act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90484&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever voluntarily causes hurt for the purpose of extorting from the sufferer, or from any`
  line `person interested in the sufferer, any property or valuable security, or of constraining the sufferer or any`
  line `person interested in such sufferer to do anything which is illegal or which may facilitate the commission`
  line `of an offence, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever voluntarily causes grievous hurt for any purpose referred to in sub-section (1), shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for life, or imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (90730)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Voluntarily causing hurt or grievous hurt to extort confession, or to compel restoration of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90730&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever voluntarily causes hurt for the purpose of extorting from the sufferer or from`
  line `any person interested in the sufferer, any confession or any information which may lead to the detection`
  line `of an offence or misconduct, or for the purpose of constraining the sufferer or any person interested in the`
  line `sufferer to restore or to cause the restoration of any property or valuable security or to satisfy any claim`
  line `or demand, or to give information which may lead to the restoration of any property or valuable security,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, a police officer, tortures Z in order to induce Z to confess that he committed a crime. A is`
  line `guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a police officer, tortures B to induce him to point out where certain stolen property is`
  line `deposited. A is guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(c) A, a revenue officer, tortures Z in order to compel him to pay certain arrears of revenue due from`
  line `Z. A is guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever voluntarily causes grievous hurt for any purpose referred to in sub-section (1), shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (90486)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Voluntarily causing hurt or grievous hurt to deter public servant from his duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90486&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Whoever voluntarily causes hurt to any person being a public servant in the discharge of his duty as such`
  line `public servant, or with intent to prevent or deter that person or any other public servant from discharging`
  line `his duty as such public servant or in consequence of anything done or attempted to be done by that person`
  line `in the lawful discharge of his duty as such public servant, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever voluntarily causes grievous hurt to any person being a public servant in the discharge of`
  line `his duty as such public servant, or with intent to prevent or deter that person or any other public servant`
  line `from discharging his duty as such public servant or in consequence of anything done or attempted to be`
  line `done by that person in the lawful discharge of his duty as such public servant, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend`
  line `to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (90487)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Voluntarily causing hurt or grievous hurt on provocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90487&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever voluntarily causes`
  line `hurt on grave and sudden provocation, if he neither intends nor knows himself to be likely to cause hurt`
  line `to any person other than the person who gave the provocation, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever voluntarily causes grievous hurt on grave and sudden provocation, if he neither intends`
  line `nor knows himself to be likely to cause grievous hurt to any person other than the person who gave the`
  line `provocation, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---This section is subject to the same proviso as Exception 1 of section 101.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (90488)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Causing hurt by means of poison, etc., with intent to commit an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90488&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `administers to or causes to be taken by any person any poison or any stupefying, intoxicating or`
  line `unwholesome drug, or other thing with intent to cause hurt to such person, or with intent to commit or to`
  line `facilitate the commission of an offence or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby cause hurt, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (90489)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Voluntarily causing grievous hurt by use of acid, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90489&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever causes permanent or`
  line `partial damage or deformity to, or burns or maims or disfigures or disables, any part or parts of the body`
  line `of a person or causes grievous hurt by throwing acid on or by administering acid to that person, or by`
  line `using any other means with the intention of causing or with the knowledge that he is likely to cause such`
  line `injury or hurt or causes a person to be in a permanent vegetative state shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend`
  line `to imprisonment for life, and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fine shall be just and reasonable to meet the medical expenses of the treatment of`
  line `the victim:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any fine imposed under this sub-section shall be paid to the victim.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever throws or attempts to throw acid on any person or attempts to administer acid to any`
  line `person, or attempts to use any other means, with the intention of causing permanent or partial damage or`
  line `deformity or burns or maiming or disfigurement or disability or grievous hurt to that person, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than five years but`
  line `which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this section, "acid" includes any substance which has acidic or`
  line `corrosive character or burning nature, that is capable of causing bodily injury leading to scars or`
  line `disfigurement or temporary or permanent disability.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---For the purposes of this section, permanent or partial damage or deformity or`
  line `permanent vegetative state shall not be required to be irreversible.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (90490)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Act endangering life or personal safety of others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90490&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does any act so rashly or`
  line `negligently as to endanger human life or the personal safety of others, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three months or with fine which may`
  line `extend to two thousand five hundred rupees, or with both, but—`
  line
  line `(a) where hurt is caused, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line both;
  line
  line `(b) where grievous hurt is caused, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (90491)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Wrongful restraint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90491&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever voluntarily obstructs any person so as to prevent that person`
  line `from proceeding in any direction in which that person has a right to proceed, is said wrongfully to restrain`
  line `that person.`
  line
  line `Exception.—The obstruction of a private way over land or water which a person in good faith`
  line `believes himself to have a lawful right to obstruct, is not an offence within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A obstructs a path along which Z has a right to pass, A not believing in good faith that he has a right`
  line `to stop the path. Z is thereby prevented from passing. A wrongfully restrains Z.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever wrongfully restrains any person shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (90492)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Wrongful confinement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90492&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever wrongfully restrains any person in such a manner as to`
  line `prevent that person from proceedings beyond certain circumscribing limits, is said “wrongfully to`
  line `confine” that person..`
  line
  line Illustrations..
  line
  line `(a) A causes Z to go within a walled space, and locks Z in. Z is thus prevented from proceeding in`
  line `any direction beyond the circumscribing line of wall. A wrongfully confines Z.`
  line
  line `(b) A places men with firearms at the outlets of a building, and tells Z that they will fire at Z if Z`
  line `attempts to leave the building. A wrongfully confines Z..`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever wrongfully confines any person shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both..`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever wrongfully confines any person for three days, or more, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both..`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever wrongfully confines any person for ten days or more, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees..`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever keeps any person in wrongful confinement, knowing that a writ for the liberation of that`
  line `person has been duly issued, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years in addition to any term of imprisonment to which he may be liable under any`
  line `other section of this Chapter and shall also be liable to fine..`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever wrongfully confines any person in such manner as to indicate an intention that the`
  line `confinement of such person may not be known to any person interested in the person so confined, or to`
  line `any public servant, or that the place of such confinement may not be known to or discovered by any such`
  line `person or public servant as hereinbefore mentioned, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to three years in addition to any other punishment to which he`
  line `may be liable for such wrongful confinement and shall also be liable to fine..`
  line
  line `(7) Whoever wrongfully confines any person for the purpose of extorting from the person confined,`
  line `or from any person interested in the person confined, any property or valuable security or of constraining`
  line `the person confined or any person interested in such person to do anything illegal or to give any`
  line `information which may facilitate the commission of an offence, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine..`
  line
  line `(8) Whoever wrongfully confines any person for the purpose of extorting from the person confined or`
  line `any person interested in the person confined any confession or any information which may lead to the`
  line `detection of an offence or misconduct, or for the purpose of constraining the person confined or any`
  line `person interested in the person confined to restore or to cause the restoration of any property or valuablesecurity or to satisfy any claim or demand, or to give information which may lead to the restoration of`
  line `any property or valuable security, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (90493)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title Force.
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90493&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `A person is said to use force to another if he causes motion, change of motion, or`
  line `cessation of motion to that other, or if he causes to any substance such motion, or change of motion, or`
  line `cessation of motion as brings that substance into contact with any part of that other’s body, or with`
  line `anything which that other is wearing or carrying, or with anything so situated that such contact affects`
  line `that other’s sense of feeling:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person causing the motion, or change of motion, or cessation of motion, causes that`
  line `motion, change of motion, or cessation of motion in one of the following three ways, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) by his own bodily power;`
  line
  line `(b) by disposing any substance in such a manner that the motion or change or cessation of motion`
  line `takes place without any further act on his part, or on the part of any other person;`
  line
  line `(c) by inducing any animal to move, to change its motion, or to cease to move.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (90494)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Criminal force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90494&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `Whoever intentionally uses force to any person, without that person’s`
  line `consent, in order to the committing of any offence, or intending by the use of such force to cause, or`
  line `knowing it to be likely that by the use of such force he will cause injury, fear or annoyance to the person`
  line `to whom the force is used, is said to use criminal force to that other.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) Z is sitting in a moored boat on a river. A unfastens the moorings, and thus intentionally causes`
  line `the boat to drift down the stream. Here A intentionally causes motion to Z, and he does this by disposing`
  line `substances in such a manner that the motion is produced without any other action on any person’s part. A`
  line `has therefore intentionally used force to Z; and if he has done so without Z’s consent, in order to the`
  line `committing of any offence, or intending or knowing it to be likely that this use of force will cause injury,`
  line `fear or annoyance to Z, A has used criminal force to Z.`
  line
  line `(b) Z is riding in a chariot. A lashes Z’s horses, and thereby causes them to quicken their pace. Here`
  line `A has caused change of motion to Z by inducing the animals to change their motion. A has therefore used`
  line `force to Z; and if A has done this without Z’s consent, intending or knowing it to be likely that he may`
  line `thereby injure, frighten or annoy Z, A has used criminal force to Z.`
  line
  line `(c) Z is riding in a palanquin. A, intending to rob Z, seizes the pole and stops the palanquin. Here A`
  line `has caused cessation of motion to Z, and he has done this by his own bodily power. A has therefore used`
  line `force to Z; and as A has acted thus intentionally, without Z’s consent, in order to the commission of an`
  line `offence. A has used criminal force to Z.`
  line
  line `(d) A intentionally pushes against Z in the street. Here A has by his own bodily power moved his`
  line `own person so as to bring it into contact with Z. He has therefore intentionally used force to Z; and if he`
  line `has done so without Z’s consent, intending or knowing it to be likely that he may thereby injure, frighten`
  line `or annoy Z, he has used criminal force to Z.`
  line
  line `(e) A throws a stone, intending or knowing it to be likely that the stone will be thus brought into`
  line `contact with Z, or with Z’s clothes, or with something carried by Z, or that it will strike water and dash up`
  line `the water against Z’s clothes or something carried by Z. Here, if the throwing of the stone produce the`
  line `effect of causing any substance to come into contact with Z, or Z’s clothes, A has used force to Z, and if`
  line `he did so without Z’s consent, intending thereby to injure, frighten or annoy Z, he has used criminal force`
  line `to Z.`
  line
  line `(f) A intentionally pulls up a woman’s veil. Here A intentionally uses force to her, and if he does so`
  line `without her consent intending or knowing it to be likely that he may thereby injure, frighten or annoy her,`
  line `he has used criminal force to her.`
  line `(g) Z is bathing. A pours into the bath water which he knows to be boiling. Here A intentionally by`
  line `his own bodily power causes such motion in the boiling water as brings that water into contact with Z, or`
  line `with other water so situated that such contact must affect Z’s sense of feeling; A has therefore`
  line `intentionally used force to Z; and if he has done this without Z’s consent intending or knowing it to be`
  line `likely that he may thereby cause injury, fear or annoyance to Z, A has used criminal force.`
  line
  line `(h) A incites a dog to spring upon Z, without Z’s consent. Here, if A intends to cause injury, fear or`
  line `annoyance to Z, he uses criminal force to Z.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (90495)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title Assault.
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90495&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes any gesture, or any preparation intending or knowing it to be likely`
  line `that such gesture or preparation will cause any person present to apprehend that he who makes that`
  line `gesture or preparation is about to use criminal force to that person, is said to commit an assault.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Mere words do not amount to an assault. But the words which a person uses may give`
  line `to his gestures or preparation such a meaning as may make those gestures or preparations amount to an`
  line assault.
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A shakes his fist at Z, intending or knowing it to be likely that he may thereby cause Z to believe`
  line `that A is about to strike Z. A has committed an assault.`
  line
  line `(b) A begins to unloose the muzzle of a ferocious dog, intending or knowing it to be likely that he may`
  line `thereby cause Z to believe that he is about to cause the dog to attack Z. A has committed an assault upon`
  line Z.
  line
  line `(c) A takes up a stick, saying to Z, “I will give you a beating”. Here, though the words used by A`
  line `could in no case amount to an assault, and though the mere gesture, unaccompanied by any other`
  line `circumstances, might not amount to an assault, the gesture explained by the words may amount to an`
  line assault.
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (90496)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Punishment for assault or criminal force otherwise than on grave provocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90496&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `assaults or uses criminal force to any person otherwise than on grave and sudden provocation given by`
  line `that person, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `three months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—Grave and sudden provocation will not mitigate the punishment for an offence under`
  line `this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the provocation is sought or voluntarily provoked by the offender as an excuse for the`
  line `offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the provocation is given by anything done in obedience to the law, or by a public servant, in`
  line `the lawful exercise of the powers of such public servant; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the provocation is given by anything done in the lawful exercise of the right of private`
  line defence.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—Whether the provocation was grave and sudden enough to mitigate the offence, is a`
  line `question of fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (90497)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Assault or criminal force to deter public servant from discharge of his duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90497&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `assaults or uses criminal force to any person being a public servant in the execution of his duty as such`
  line `public servant, or with intent to prevent or deter that person from discharging his duty as such public`
  line `servant, or in consequence of anything done or attempted to be done by such person in the lawful`
  line `discharge of his duty as such public servant, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (90731)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Assault or criminal force with intent to dishonour person, otherwise than on grave provocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90731&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `Whoever assaults or uses criminal force to any person, intending thereby to dishonour`
  line `that person, otherwise than on grave and sudden provocation given by that person, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (90499)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Assault or criminal force in attempt to commit theft of property carried by a person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90499&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Whoever assaults or uses criminal force to any person, in attempting to commit theft on any property`
  line `which that person is then wearing or carrying, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (90500)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Assault or criminal force in attempt to wrongfully confine a person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90500&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `Whoever assaults or`
  line `uses criminal force to any person, in attempting wrongfully to confine that person, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (90501)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Assault or criminal force on grave provocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90501&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `Whoever assaults or uses criminal force to`
  line `any person on grave and sudden provocation given by that person, shall be punished with simple`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—This section is subject to the same Explanation as section 131.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (90502)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title Kidnapping.
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90502&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) Kidnapping is of two kinds: kidnapping from India, and kidnapping from`
  line `lawful guardianship—`
  line
  line `(a) whoever conveys any person beyond the limits of India without the consent of that person, or`
  line `of some person legally authorised to consent on behalf of that person, is said to kidnap that person`
  line `from India;`
  line
  line `(b) whoever takes or entices any child or any person of unsound mind, out of the keeping of the`
  line `lawful guardian of such child or person of unsound mind, without the consent of such guardian, is`
  line `said to kidnap such child or person from lawful guardianship.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The words “lawful guardian” in this clause include any person lawfully entrusted`
  line `with the care or custody of such child or other person.`
  line
  line `Exception.—This clause does not extend to the act of any person who in good faith believes`
  line `himself to be the father of an illegitimate child, or who in good faith believes himself to be entitled to`
  line `the lawful custody of such child, unless such act is committed for an immoral or unlawful purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever kidnaps any person from India or from lawful guardianship shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (90503)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title Abduction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90503&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `Whoever by force compels, or by any deceitful means induces, any person to go`
  line `from any place, is said to abduct that person.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (90504)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Kidnapping or maiming a child for purposes of begging.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90504&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever kidnaps any child or,`
  line `not being the lawful guardian of such child, obtains the custody of the child, in order that such child may`
  line `be employed or used for the purposes of begging shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever maims any child in order that such child may be employed or used for the purposes of`
  line `begging shall be punishable with imprisonment which shall not be less than twenty years, but which may`
  line `extend to life which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of that person`
  line `s natural life, and with`
  line fine.
  line
  line `(3) Where any person, not being the lawful guardian of a child employs or uses such child for the`
  line `purposes of begging, it shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that he kidnapped or otherwise`
  line `obtained the custody of such child in order that such child might be employed or used for the purposes of`
  line begging.
  line
  line `(4) In this section "begging" means---`
  line
  line `(i) soliciting or receiving alms in a public place, whether under the pretence of singing, dancing,`
  line `fortune telling, performing tricks or selling articles or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) entering on any private premises for the purpose of soliciting or receiving alms;`
  line
  line `(iii) exposing or exhibiting, with the object of obtaining or extorting alms, any sore, wound,`
  line `injury, deformity or disease, whether of himself or of any other person or of an animal;`
  line
  line `(iv) using such child as an exhibit for the purpose of soliciting or receiving alms.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (90505)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Kidnapping or abducting in order to murder or for ransom, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90505&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever kidnaps or`
  line `abducts any person in order that such person may be murdered or may be so disposed of as to be put in`
  line `danger of being murdered, shall be punished with imprisonment for life or rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A kidnaps Z from India, intending or knowing it to be likely that Z may be sacrificed to an idol. A`
  line `has committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A forcibly carries or entices B away from his home in order that B may be murdered. A has`
  line `committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever kidnaps or abducts any person or keeps a person in detention after such kidnapping or`
  line `abduction, and threatens to cause death or hurt to such person, or by his conduct gives rise to a reasonable`
  line `apprehension that such person may be put to death or hurt, or causes hurt or death to such person in order`
  line `to compel the Government or any foreign State or international inter-governmental organisation or any`
  line `other person to do or abstain from doing any act or to pay a ransom, shall be punishable with death, or`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine..`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever kidnaps or abducts any person with intent to cause that person to be secretly and`
  line `wrongfully confined, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine..`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever kidnaps or abducts any person in order that such person may be subjected, or may be so`
  line `disposed of as to be put in danger of being subjected to grievous hurt, or slavery, or to the unnatural lust`
  line `of any person, or knowing it to be likely that such person will be so subjected or disposed of, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (90506)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Importation of girl or boy from foreign country.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90506&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `Whoever imports into India from any`
  line `country outside India any girl under the age of twenty-one years or any boy under the age of eighteen`
  line `years with intent that girl or boy may be, or knowing it to be likely that girl or boy will be, forced or`
  line `seduced to illicit intercourse with another person, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (90507)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Wrongfully concealing or keeping in confinement, kidnapped or abducted person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90507&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing that any person has been kidnapped or has been abducted, wrongfully conceals or`
  line `confines such person, shall be punished in the same manner as if he had kidnapped or abducted such`
  line `person with the same intention or knowledge, or for the same purpose as that with or for which he`
  line `conceals or detains such person in confinement.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (90508)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Trafficking of person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90508&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, for the purpose of exploitation recruits, transports,`
  line `harbours, transfers, or receives a person or persons, by---`
  line
  line `(a) using threats; or`
  line
  line `(b) using force, or any other form of coercion; or`
  line
  line `(c) by abduction; or`
  line
  line `(d) by practising fraud, or deception; or`
  line
  line `(e) by abuse of power; or`
  line
  line `(f) by inducement, including the giving or receiving of payments or benefits, in order to achieve`
  line `the consent of any person having control over the person recruited, transported, harboured,`
  line `transferred or received,`
  line
  line `commits the offence of trafficking.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---The expression "exploitation" shall include any act of physical exploitation or`
  line `any form of sexual exploitation, slavery or practices similar to slavery, servitude, beggary or forced`
  line `removal of organs.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---The consent of the victim is immaterial in determination of the offence of`
  line trafficking.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits the offence of trafficking shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than seven years, but which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the offence involves the trafficking of more than one person, it shall be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the offence involves the trafficking of a child, it shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ten years, but which may extend to imprisonment`
  line `for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the offence involves the trafficking of more than one child, it shall be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than fourteen years, but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(6) If a person is convicted of the offence of trafficking of a child on more than one occasion, then`
  line `such person shall be punished with imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the`
  line `remainder of that person's natural life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(7) When a public servant or a police officer is involved in the trafficking of any person then, such`
  line `public servant or police officer shall be punished with imprisonment for life, which shall mean`
  line `imprisonment for the remainder of that person's natural life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (90509)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Exploitation of a trafficked person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90509&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, knowingly or having reason to believe that`
  line `a child has been trafficked, engages such child for sexual exploitation in any manner, shall be punished`
  line `with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years, but which may extend to`
  line `ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `(2) Whoever, knowingly or having reason to believe that a person has been trafficked, engages such`
  line `person for sexual exploitation in any manner, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than three years, but which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (90510)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Habitual dealing in slaves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90510&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Whoever habitually imports, exports, removes, buys, sells, traffics`
  line `or deals in slaves, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term not exceeding ten years, and shall also be liable to fine`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (90511)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Unlawful compulsory labour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90511&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `Whoever unlawfully compels any person to labour against the`
  line `will of that person, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (90732)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Waging, or attempting to wage war, or abetting waging of war, against Government of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90732&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `Whoever wages war against the Government of India, or attempts to wage such war, or abets the`
  line `waging of such war, shall be punished with death, or imprisonment for life and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A joins an insurrection against the Government of India. A has committed the offence defined in this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (90513)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Conspiracy to commit offences punishable by section 147.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90513&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `Whoever within or without and`
  line `beyond India conspires to commit any of the offences punishable by section 147, or conspires to`
  line `overawe, by means of criminal force or the show of criminal force, the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description`
  line `which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—To constitute a conspiracy under this section, it is not necessary that any act or illegal`
  line `omission shall take place in pursuance thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (90514)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Collecting arms, etc., with intention of waging war against Government of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90514&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Whoever collects men, arms or ammunition or otherwise prepares to wage war with the intention of`
  line `either waging or being prepared to wage war against the Government of India, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life or imprisonment of either description for a term not exceeding ten years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (90515)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Concealing with intent to facilitate design to wage war.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90515&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `Whoever by any act, or by any`
  line `illegal omission, conceals the existence of a design to wage war against the Government of India,`
  line `intending by such concealment to facilitate, or knowing it to be likely that such concealment will`
  line `facilitate, the waging of such war, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (90733)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Assaulting President, Governor, etc., with intent to compel or restrain exercise of any lawful power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90733&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with the intention of inducing or compelling the President of India, or`
  line `Governor of any State, to exercise or refrain from exercising in any manner any of the lawful powers of`
  line `such President or Governor, assaults or wrongfully restrains, or attempts wrongfully to restrain, or`
  line `overawes, by means of criminal force or the show of criminal force, or attempts so to overawe, such`
  line `President or Governor, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (90517)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Act endangering sovereignty, unity and integrity of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90517&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, purposely or`
  line `knowingly, by words, either spoken or written, or by signs, or by visible representation, or by electronic`
  line `communication or by use of financial mean, or otherwise, excites or attempts to excite, secession or`
  line `armed rebellion or subversive activities, or encourages feelings of separatist activities or endangers`
  line `sovereignty or unity and integrity of India; or indulges in or commits any such act shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life or with imprisonment which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `Explanation.—Comments expressing disapprobation of the measures, or administrative or other`
  line `action of the Government with a view to obtain their alteration by lawful means without exciting or`
  line `attempting to excite the activities referred to in this section do not constitute an offence under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (90518)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Waging war against Government of any foreign State at peace with Government of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90518&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `Whoever wages war against the Government of any foreign State at peace with the Government`
  line `of India or attempts to wage such war, or abets the waging of such war, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, to which fine may be added, or with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years, to which fine may be added, or with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (90519)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Committing depredation on territories of foreign State at peace with Government of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90519&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits depredation, or makes preparations to commit depredation, on the territories`
  line `of any foreign State at peace with the Government of India, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine and to`
  line `forfeiture of any property used or intended to be used in committing such depredation, or acquired by`
  line `such depredation.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (90520)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Receiving property taken by war or depredation mentioned in sections 153 and 154.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90520&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `Whoever receives any property knowing the same to have been taken in the commission of any of the`
  line `offences mentioned in sections 153 and 154, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine and to forfeiture of the`
  line `property so received.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (90521)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Public servant voluntarily allowing prisoner of State or war to escape.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90521&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a`
  line `public servant and having the custody of any State prisoner or prisoner of war, voluntarily allows such`
  line `prisoner to escape from any place in which such prisoner is confined, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (90522)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Public servant negligently suffering such prisoner to escape.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90522&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public`
  line `servant and having the custody of any State prisoner or prisoner of war, negligently suffers such prisoner`
  line `to escape from any place of confinement in which such prisoner is confined, shall be punished with`
  line `simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (90523)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Aiding escape of, rescuing or harbouring such prisoner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90523&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly aids or assists`
  line `any State prisoner or prisoner of war in escaping from lawful custody, or rescues or attempts to rescue`
  line `any such prisoner, or harbours or conceals any such prisoner who has escaped from lawful custody, or`
  line `offers or attempts to offer any resistance to the recapture of such prisoner, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A State prisoner or prisoner of war, who is permitted to be at large on his parole`
  line `within certain limits in India, is said to escape from lawful custody if he goes beyond the limits`
  line `within which he is allowed to be at large.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (90524)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Abetting mutiny, or attempting to seduce a soldier, sailor or airman from his duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90524&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the committing of mutiny by an officer, soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or`
  line `Air Force of the Government of India or attempts to seduce any such officer, soldier, sailor or airman`
  line `from his allegiance or his duty, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (90525)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Abetment of mutiny, if mutiny is committed in consequence thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90525&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the`
  line `committing of mutiny by an officer, soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or Air Force of the`
  line `Government of India, shall, if mutiny be committed in consequence of that abetment, be punished with`
  line `death or with imprisonment for life, or imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (90734)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Abetment of assault by soldier, sailor or airman on his superior officer, when in execution of his office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90734&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets an assault by an officer, soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or Air`
  line `Force of the Government of India, on any superior officer being in the execution of his office, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (90527)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Abetment of such assault, if assault committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90527&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets an assault by an officer,`
  line `soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or Air Force of the Government of India, on any superior`
  line `officer being in the execution of his office, shall, if such assault be committed in consequence of that`
  line `abetment be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (90528)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Abetment of desertion of soldier, sailor or airman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90528&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the desertion of any`
  line `officer, soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or Air Force of the Government of India, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (90529)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Harbouring deserter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90529&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, except as hereinafter excepted, knowing or having reason to`
  line `believe that an officer, soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or Air Force of the Government of`
  line `India, has deserted, harbours such officer, soldier, sailor or airman, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `Exception.—This provision does not extend to the case in which the harbour is given by the spouse of`
  line `the deserter.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (90530)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Deserter concealed on board merchant vessel through negligence of master.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90530&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `The master or`
  line `person in charge of a merchant vessel, on board of which any deserter from the Army, Navy or Air Force`
  line `of the Government of India is concealed, shall, though ignorant of such concealment, be liable to a`
  line `penalty not exceeding three thousand rupees, if he might have known of such concealment but for some`
  line `neglect of his duty as such master or person in charge, or but for some want of discipline on board of the`
  line vessel.
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (90531)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Abetment of act of insubordination by soldier, sailor or airman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90531&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets what he`
  line `knows to be an act of insubordination by an officer, soldier, sailor or airman, in the Army, Navy or Air`
  line `Force, of the Government of India, shall, if such act of insubordination be committed in consequence of`
  line `that abetment, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (90532)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Persons subject to certain Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90532&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `No person subject to the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950),`
  line `the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950) and the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957), or shall be subject to punishment`
  line `under this Sanhita for any of the offences defined in this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (90533)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Wearing garb or carrying token used by soldier, sailor or airman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90533&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, not being a`
  line `soldier, sailor or airman in the Army, Naval or Air service of the Government of India, wears any garb or`
  line `carries any token resembling any garb or token used by such a soldier, sailor or airman with the intention`
  line `that it may be believed that he is such a soldier, sailor or airman, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (90534)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Candidate, electoral right defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90534&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter—`
  line
  line `(a) “candidate” means a person who has been nominated as a candidate at any election;`
  line
  line `(b) “electoral right” means the right of a person to stand, or not to stand as, or to withdraw from`
  line `being, a candidate or to vote or refrain from voting at an election.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (90535)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title Bribery.
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90535&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever—`
  line
  line `(i) gives a gratification to any person with the object of inducing him or any other person to`
  line `exercise any electoral right or of rewarding any person for having exercised any such right;`
  line or
  line `(ii) accepts either for himself or for any other person any gratification as a reward for exercising`
  line `any such right or for inducing or attempting to induce any other person to exercise any such right,`
  line `commits the offence of bribery:`
  line
  line `Provided that a declaration of public policy or a promise of public action shall not be an offence`
  line `under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) A person who offers, or agrees to give, or offers or attempts to procure, a gratification shall be`
  line `deemed to give a gratification.`
  line
  line `(3) A person who obtains or agrees to accept or attempts to obtain a gratification shall be deemed to`
  line `accept a gratification, and a person who accepts a gratification as a motive for doing what he does not`
  line `intend to do, or as a reward for doing what he has not done, shall be deemed to have accepted the`
  line `gratification as a reward.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (90536)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Undue influence at elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90536&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever voluntarily interferes or attempts to interfere with`
  line `the free exercise of any electoral right commits the offence of undue influence at an election.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), whoever—`
  line
  line `(a) threatens any candidate or voter, or any person in whom a candidate or voter is interested,`
  line `with injury of any kind; or`
  line
  line `(b) induces or attempts to induce a candidate or voter to believe that he or any person in whom he`
  line `is interested will become or will be rendered an object of Divine displeasure or of spiritual censure,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to interfere with the free exercise of the electoral right of such candidate or voter, within`
  line `the meaning of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) A declaration of public policy or a promise of public action or the mere exercise or a legal right`
  line `without intent to interfere with an electoral right, shall not be deemed to be interference within the`
  line `meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (90537)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Personation at elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90537&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `Whoever at an election applies for a voting paper on votes in the`
  line `name of any other person, whether living or dead, or in a fictitious name, or who having voted once at`
  line `such election applies at the same election for a voting paper in his own name, and whoever abets,`
  line `procures or attempts to procure the voting by any person in any such way, commits the offence of`
  line `personation at an election:.`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a person who has been authorised to vote as proxy`
  line `for an elector under any law for the time being in force in so far as he votes as a proxy for such elector.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (90538)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Punishment for bribery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90538&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits the offence of bribery shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that bribery by treating shall be punished with fine only.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—“Treating” means that form of bribery where the gratification consists in food, drink,`
  line `entertainment, or provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (90539)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Punishment for undue influence or personation at an election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90539&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits the`
  line `offence of undue influence or personation at an election shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to one year or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (90540)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `False statement in connection with an election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90540&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `Whoever with intent to affect the result of`
  line `an election makes or publishes any statement purporting to be a statement of fact which is false and`
  line `which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, in relation to the personal`
  line `character or conduct of any candidate shall be punished with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (90541)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Illegal payments in connection with an election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90541&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `Whoever without the general or special`
  line `authority in writing of a candidate incurs or authorises expenses on account of the holding of any public`
  line `meeting, or upon any advertisement, circular or publication, or in any other way whatsoever for the`
  line `purpose of promoting or procuring the election of such candidate, shall be punished with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any person having incurred any such expenses not exceeding the amount of ten`
  line `rupees without authority obtains within ten days from the date on which such expenses were incurred the`
  line `approval in writing of the candidate, he shall be deemed to have incurred such expenses with the`
  line `authority of the candidate.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (90542)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Failure to keep election accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90542&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `Whoever being required by any law for the time being in`
  line `force or any rule having the force of law to keep accounts of expenses incurred at or in connection with`
  line `an election fails to keep such accounts shall be punished with fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (90543)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Counterfeiting coin, Government stamps, currency-notes or bank-notes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90543&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `counterfeits, or knowingly performs any part of the process of counterfeiting, any coin, stamp issued by`
  line `Government for the purpose of revenue, currency-note or bank-note, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this Chapter,—`
  line
  line `(1) the expression “bank-note” means a promissory note or engagement for the payment of`
  line `money to bearer on demand issued by any person carrying on the business of banking in any part of`
  line `the world, or issued by or under the authority of any State or Sovereign Power, and intended to be`
  line `used as equivalent to, or as a substitute for money;`
  line
  line `(2) “coin” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 2 of the Coinage Act, 2011`
  line `(11 of 2011) and includes metal used for the time being as money and is stamped and issued by or`
  line `under the authority of any State or Sovereign Power intended to be so used;`
  line
  line `(3) a person commits the offence of “counterfeiting Government stamp” who counterfeits by`
  line `causing a genuine stamp of one denomination to appear like a genuine stamp of a different`
  line denomination;
  line `(4) a person commits the offence of counterfeiting coin who intending to practise deception, or`
  line `knowing it to be likely that deception will thereby be practised, causes a genuine coin to appear like a`
  line `different coin; and`
  line
  line `(5) the offence of “counterfeiting coin” includes diminishing the weight or alteration of the`
  line `composition, or alteration of the appearance of the coin.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (90735)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Using as genuine, forged or counterfeit coin, Government stamp, currency-notes or bank-notes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90735&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `Whoever imports or exports, or sells or delivers to, or buys or receives from, any other person, or`
  line `otherwise traffics or uses as genuine, any forged or counterfeit coin, stamp, currency-note or bank-note,`
  line `knowing or having reason to believe the same to be forged or counterfeit, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (90545)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Possession of forged or counterfeit coin, Government stamp, currency-notes or bank-notes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90545&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `Whoever has in his possession any forged or counterfeit coin, stamp, currency-note or bank-note,`
  line `knowing or having reason to believe the same to be forged or counterfeit and intending to use the same as`
  line `genuine or that it may be used as genuine, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If a person establishes the possession of the forged or counterfeit coin, stamp,`
  line `currency-note or bank-note to be from a lawful source, it shall not constitute an offence under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (90736)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Making or possessing instruments or materials for forging or counterfeiting coin, Government stamp, currency-notes or bank-notes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90736&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes or mends, or performs any part`
  line `of the process of making or mending, or buys or sells or disposes of, or has in his possession, any`
  line `machinery, die, or instrument or material for the purpose of being used, or knowing or having reason to`
  line `believe that it is intended to be used, for forging or counterfeiting any coin, stamp issued by Government`
  line `for the purpose of revenue, currency-note or bank-note, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (90547)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Making or using documents resembling currency-notes or bank-notes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90547&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever`
  line `makes, or causes to be made, or uses for any purpose whatsoever, or delivers to any person, any`
  line `document purporting to be, or in any way resembling, or so nearly resembling as to be calculated to deceive, any currency-note or bank-note shall be punished with fine which may extend to three hundred`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(2) If any person, whose name appears on a document the making of which is an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1), refuses, without lawful excuse, to disclose to a police officer on being so required the`
  line `name and address of the person by whom it was printed or otherwise made, he shall be punished with fine`
  line `which may extend to six hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the name of any person appears on any document in respect of which any person is`
  line `charged with an offence under sub-section (1) or on any other document used or distributed in connection`
  line `with that document it may, until the contrary is proved, be presumed that the person caused the document`
  line `to be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (90737)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Effacing writing from substance bearing Government stamp, or removing from document a stamp used for it, with intent to cause loss to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90737&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fraudulently or with intent to`
  line `cause loss to the Government, removes or effaces from any substance, bearing any stamp issued by`
  line `Government for the purpose of revenue, any writing or document for which such stamp has been used, or`
  line `removes from any writing or document a stamp which has been used for such writing or document, in`
  line `order that such stamp may be used for a different writing or document, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (90549)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Using Government stamp known to have been before used.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90549&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fraudulently or with`
  line `intent to cause loss to the Government, uses for any purpose a stamp issued by Government for the`
  line `purpose of revenue, which he knows to have been before used, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (90550)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Erasure of mark denoting that stamp has been used.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90550&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fraudulently or with intent`
  line `to cause loss to Government, erases or removes from a stamp issued by Government for the purpose of`
  line `revenue, any mark, put or impressed upon such stamp for the purpose of denoting that the same has been`
  line `used, or knowingly has in his possession or sells or disposes of any such stamp from which such mark`
  line `has been erased or removed, or sells or disposes of any such stamp which he knows to have been used,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (90551)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Prohibition of fictitious stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90551&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever—.`
  line
  line `(a) makes, knowingly utters, deals in or sells any fictitious stamp, or knowingly uses for any`
  line `postal purpose any fictitious stamp; or.`
  line
  line `(b) has in his possession, without lawful excuse, any fictitious stamp; or.`
  line
  line `(c) makes or, without lawful excuse, has in his possession any die, plate, instrument or materials`
  line `for making any fictitious stamp,`
  line `shall be punished with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees..`
  line
  line `(2) Any such stamp, die, plate, instrument or materials in the possession of any person for making`
  line `any fictitious stamp may be seized and, if seized shall be forfeited..`
  line
  line `(3) In this section “fictitious stamp” means any stamp falsely purporting to be issued by Government`
  line `for the purpose of denoting a rate of postage, or any facsimile or imitation or representation, whether on`
  line `paper or otherwise, of any stamp issued by Government for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section and also in sections 178 to 181 (both inclusive), and sections 183 to 185 (both`
  line `inclusive) the word “Government”, when used in connection with, or in reference to any stamp issued for`
  line `the purpose of denoting a rate of postage, shall, notwithstanding anything in clause (12) of section 2, be`
  line `deemed to include the person or persons authorised by law to administer executive Government in any`
  line `part of India or in any foreign country.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (90738)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Person employed in mint causing coin to be of different weight or composition from that fixed by law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90738&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being employed in any mint lawfully established in India, does any act, or`
  line `omits what he is legally bound to do, with the intention of causing any coin issued from that mint to be of a different weight or composition from the weight or composition fixed by law, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (90553)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Unlawfully taking coining instrument from mint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90553&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, without lawful authority, takes`
  line `out of any mint, lawfully established in India, any coining tool or instrument, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (90554)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Unlawful assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90554&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `(1) An assembly of five or more persons is designated an unlawful`
  line `assembly, if the common object of the persons composing that assembly is---`
  line
  line `(a) to overawe by criminal force, or show of criminal force, the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government or Parliament or the Legislature of any State, or any public servant in the exercise of the`
  line `lawful power of such public servant; or`
  line
  line `(b) to resist the execution of any law, or of any legal process; or`
  line
  line `(c) to commit any mischief or criminal trespass, or other offence; or`
  line
  line `(d) by means of criminal force, or show of criminal force, to any person, to take or obtain`
  line `possession of any property, or to deprive any person of the enjoyment of a right of way, or of the use`
  line `of water or other incorporeal right of which he is in possession or enjoyment, or to enforce any right`
  line `or supposed right; or`
  line
  line `(e) by means of criminal force, or show of criminal force, to compel any person to do what he is`
  line `not legally bound to do, or to omit to do what he is legally entitled to do.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---An assembly which was not unlawful when it assembled, may subsequently become`
  line `an unlawful assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being aware of facts which render any assembly an unlawful assembly, intentionally`
  line `joins that assembly, or continues in it, is said to be a member of an unlawful assembly and such member`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever joins or continues in an unlawful assembly, knowing that such unlawful assembly has`
  line `been commanded in the manner prescribed by law to disperse, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever, being armed with any deadly weapon, or with anything which, used as a weapon of`
  line `offence, is likely to cause death, is a member of an unlawful assembly, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever knowingly joins or continues in any assembly of five or more persons likely to cause a`
  line `disturbance of the public peace, after such assembly has been lawfully commanded to disperse, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---If the assembly is an unlawful assembly within the meaning of sub-section (1), the`
  line `offender shall be punishable under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever hires or engages, or employs, or promotes, or connives at the hiring, engagement or`
  line `employment of any person to join or become a member of any unlawful assembly, shall be punishable as`
  line `a member of such unlawful assembly, and for any offence which may be committed by any such person`
  line `as a member of such unlawful assembly in pursuance of such hiring, engagement or employment, in the`
  line `same manner as if he had been a member of such unlawful assembly, or himself had committed such`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(7) Whoever harbours, receives or assembles, in any house or premises in his occupation or charge,`
  line `or under his control any persons knowing that such persons have been hired, engaged or employed, or are`
  line `about to be hired, engaged or employed, to join or become members of an unlawful assembly, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(8) Whoever is engaged, or hired, or offers or attempts to be hired or engaged, to do or assist in doing`
  line `any of the acts specified in sub-section (1), shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(9) Whoever, being so engaged or hired as referred to in sub-section (8), goes armed, or engages or`
  line `offers to go armed, with any deadly weapon or with anything which used as a weapon of offence is likely`
  line `to cause death, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (90739)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Every member of unlawful assembly guilty of offence committed in prosecution of common object.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90739&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `If an offence is committed by any member of an unlawful assembly in prosecution of`
  line `the common object of that assembly, or such as the members of that assembly knew to be likely to be`
  line `committed in prosecution of that object, every person who, at the time of the committing of that offence,`
  line `is a member of the same assembly, is guilty of that offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (90556)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title Rioting.
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90556&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever force or violence is used by an unlawful assembly, or by any member`
  line `thereof, in prosecution of the common object of such assembly, every member of such assembly is guilty`
  line `of the offence of rioting.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever is guilty of rioting, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever is guilty of rioting, being armed with a deadly weapon or with anything which, used as a`
  line `weapon of offence, is likely to cause death, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (90740)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Wantonly giving provocation with intent to cause riot-if rioting be committed; if not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90740&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `Whoever malignantly, or wantonly by doing anything which is illegal, gives provocation to`
  line `any person intending or knowing it to be likely that such provocation will cause the offence of rioting to`
  line `be committed, shall, if the offence of rioting be committed in consequence of such provocation, be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine,`
  line `or with both; and if the offence of rioting be not committed, with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (90558)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title `Liability of owner, occupier, etc., of land on which an unlawful assembly or riot takes place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90558&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any unlawful assembly or riot takes place, the owner or occupier of the land upon`
  line `which such unlawful assembly is held, or such riot is committed, and any person having or claiming an`
  line `interest in such land, shall be punishable with fine not exceeding one thousand rupees, if he or his agent`
  line `or manager, knowing that such offence is being or has been committed, or having reason to believe it is`
  line `likely to be committed, do not give the earliest notice thereof in his or their power to the officer in charge`
  line `at the nearest police station, and do not, in the case of his or their having reason to believe that it was`
  line `about to be committed, use all lawful means in his or their power to prevent it and, in the event of its`
  line `taking place, do not use all lawful means in his or their power to disperse or suppress the riot or unlawful`
  line assembly.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever a riot is committed for the benefit or on behalf of any person who is the owner or`
  line `occupier of any land respecting which such riot takes place or who claims any interest in such land, or in`
  line `the subject of any dispute which gave rise to the riot, or who has accepted or derived any benefit`
  line `therefrom, such person shall be punishable with fine, if he or his agent or manager, having reason to`
  line `believe that such riot was likely to be committed or that the unlawful assembly by which such riot was`
  line `committed was likely to be held, shall not respectively use all lawful means in his or their power to`
  line `prevent such assembly or riot from taking place, and for suppressing and dispersing the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever a riot is committed for the benefit or on behalf of any person who is the owner or`
  line `occupier of any land respecting which such riot takes place, or who claims any interest in such land, or in`
  line `the subject of any dispute which gave rise to the riot, or who has accepted or derived any benefit`
  line `therefrom, the agent or manager of such person shall be punishable with fine, if such agent or manager,`
  line `having reason to believe that such riot was likely to be committed, or that the unlawful assembly by`
  line `which such riot was committed was likely to be held, shall not use all lawful means in his power to`
  line `prevent such riot or assembly from taking place and for suppressing and dispersing the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (90559)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title Affray.
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90559&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `(1) When two or more persons, by fighting in a public place, disturb the public peace,`
  line `they are said to commit an affray.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits an affray, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (90560)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Assaulting or obstructing public servant when suppressing riot, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90560&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever assaults`
  line `or obstructs any public servant or uses criminal force on any public servant in the discharge of his duty as`
  line `such public servant in endeavouring to disperse an unlawful assembly, or to suppress a riot or affray,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever threatens to assault or attempts to obstruct any public servant or threatens or attempts to`
  line `use criminal force to any public servant in the discharge of his duty as such public servant in`
  line `endeavouring to disperse an unlawful assembly, or to suppress a riot or affray, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (90741)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Promoting enmity between different groups on grounds of religion, race, place of birth, residence, language, etc., and doing acts prejudicial to maintenance of harmony.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90741&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever—`
  line
  line `(a) by words, either spoken or written, or by signs or by visible representations or through`
  line `electronic communication or otherwise, promotes or attempts to promote, on grounds of religion,`
  line `race, place of birth, residence, language, caste or community or any other ground whatsoever,`
  line `disharmony or feelings of enmity, hatred or ill-will between different religious, racial, language or`
  line `regional groups or castes or communities; or`
  line
  line `(b) commits any act which is prejudicial to the maintenance of harmony between different`
  line `religious, racial, language or regional groups or castes or communities, and which disturbs or is likely`
  line `to disturb the public tranquillity; or`
  line
  line `(c) organises any exercise, movement, drill or other similar activity intending that the participants`
  line `in such activity shall use or be trained to use criminal force or violence or knowing it to be likely that`
  line `the participants in such activity will use or be trained to use criminal force or violence, or participates`
  line `in such activity intending to use or be trained to use criminal force or violence or knowing it to be`
  line `likely that the participants in such activity will use or be trained to use criminal force or violence,`
  line `against any religious, racial, language or regional group or caste or community and such activity for`
  line `any reason whatsoever causes or is likely to cause fear or alarm or a feeling of insecurity amongst`
  line `members of such religious, racial, language or regional group or caste or community,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits an offence specified in sub-section (1) in any place of worship or in any`
  line `assembly engaged in the performance of religious worship or religious ceremonies, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment which may extend to five years and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (90562)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `Imputations, assertions prejudicial to national integration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90562&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, by words either`
  line `spoken or written or by signs or by visible representations or through electronic communication or`
  line otherwise,—
  line
  line `(a) makes or publishes any imputation that any class of persons cannot, by reason of their being`
  line `members of any religious, racial, language or regional group or caste or community, bear true faith`
  line `and allegiance to the Constitution of India as by law established or uphold the sovereignty and`
  line `integrity of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) asserts, counsels, advises, propagates or publishes that any class of persons shall, by reason of`
  line `their being members of any religious, racial, language or regional group or caste or community, be`
  line `denied, or deprived of their rights as citizens of India; or`
  line
  line `(c) makes or publishes any assertion, counsel, plea or appeal concerning the obligation of any`
  line `class of persons, by reason of their being members of any religious, racial, language or regional`
  line `group or caste or community, and such assertion, counsel, plea or appeal causes or is likely to cause`
  line `disharmony or feelings of enmity or hatred or ill-will between such members and other persons; or`
  line
  line `(d) makes or publishes false or misleading information, jeopardising the sovereignty, unity and`
  line `integrity or security of India,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits an offence specified in sub-section (1) in any place of worship or in any`
  line `assembly engaged in the performance of religious worship or religious ceremonies, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment which may extend to five years and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (90563)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Public servant disobeying law, with intent to cause injury to any person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90563&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a`
  line `public servant, knowingly disobeys any direction of the law as to the way in which he is to conduct`
  line `himself as such public servant, intending to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he will by such`
  line `disobedience, cause injury to any person, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, being an officer directed by law to take property in execution, in order to satisfy a decree`
  line `pronounced in Z’s favour by a Court, knowingly disobeys that direction of law, with the knowledge that`
  line `he is likely thereby to cause injury to Z. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (90564)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Public servant disobeying direction under law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90564&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant,—`
  line
  line `(a) knowingly disobeys any direction of the law which prohibits him from requiring the`
  line `attendance at any place of any person for the purpose of investigation into an offence or any other`
  line `matter; or`
  line
  line `(b) knowingly disobeys, to the prejudice of any person, any other direction of the law regulating`
  line `the manner in which he shall conduct such investigation; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails to record any information given to him under sub-section (1) of section 173 of the`
  line `Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 in relation to cognizable offence punishable under`
  line `section 64, section 65, section 66, section 67, section 68, section 70, section 71, section 74,`
  line `section 76, section 77, section 79, section 124, section 143 or section 144,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but`
  line `which may extend to two years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (90565)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 200
  title `Punishment for non-treatment of victim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90565&sectionno=200&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being in charge of a hospital, public or`
  line `private, whether run by the Central Government, the State Government, local bodies or any other person,`
  line `contravenes the provisions of section 397 of the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (90566)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 201
  title `Public servant framing an incorrect document with intent to cause injury.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90566&sectionno=201&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line Whoever,
  line `being a public servant, and being, as such public servant, charged with the preparation or translation of`
  line `any document or electronic record, frames, prepares or translates that document or electronic record in a`
  line `manner which he knows or believes to be incorrect, intending thereby to cause or knowing it to be likely`
  line `that he may thereby cause injury to any person, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (90567)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 202
  title `Public servant unlawfully engaging in trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90567&sectionno=202&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, and being`
  line `legally bound as such public servant not to engage in trade, engages in trade, shall be punished with`
  line `simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both or with`
  line `community service.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (90568)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 203
  title `Public servant unlawfully buying or bidding for property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90568&sectionno=203&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public`
  line `servant, and being legally bound as such public servant, not to purchase or bid for certain property,`
  line `purchases or bids for that property, either in his own name or in the name of another, or jointly, or in`
  line `shares with others, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years, or with fine, or with both; and the property, if purchased, shall be confiscated.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (90569)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 204
  title `Personating a public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90569&sectionno=204&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `Whoever pretends to hold any particular office as a public`
  line `servant, knowing that he does not hold such office or falsely personates any other person holding such`
  line `office, and in such assumed character does or attempts to do any act under colour of such office, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than six months but`
  line `which may extend to three years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (90570)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 205
  title `Wearing garb or carrying token used by public servant with fraudulent intent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90570&sectionno=205&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line Whoever,
  line `not belonging to a certain class of public servants, wears any garb or carries any token resembling any`
  line `garb or token used by that class of public servants, with the intention that it may be believed, or with the`
  line `knowledge that it is likely to be believed, that he belongs to that class of public servants, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three months, or with`
  line `fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (90571)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 206
  title `Absconding to avoid service of summons or other proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90571&sectionno=206&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `Whoever absconds in order`
  line `to avoid being served with a summons, notice or order proceeding from any public servant legally`
  line `competent, as such public servant, to issue such summons, notice or order,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where such summons or notice or order is to attend in person or by agent, or to produce a`
  line `document or an electronic record in a Court shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (90572)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 207
  title `Preventing service of summons or other proceeding, or preventing publication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90572&sectionno=207&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `Whoever in any manner intentionally prevents the serving on himself, or on any other person, of any`
  line `summons, notice or order proceeding from any public servant legally competent, as such public servant,`
  line `to issue such summons, notice or order, or intentionally prevents the lawful affixing to any place of any`
  line `such summons, notice or order or intentionally removes any such summons, notice or order from any`
  line `place to which it is lawfully affixed or intentionally prevents the lawful making of any proclamation,`
  line `under the authority of any public servant legally competent, as such public servant, to direct such`
  line `proclamation to be made,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the summons, notice, order or proclamation is to attend in person or by agent, or to`
  line `produce a document or electronic record in a Court, with simple imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (90573)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 208
  title `Non-attendance in obedience to an order from public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90573&sectionno=208&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally`
  line `bound to attend in person or by an agent at a certain place and time in obedience to a summons, notice,`
  line `order, or proclamation proceeding from any public servant legally competent, as such public servant, to`
  line `issue the same, intentionally omits to attend at that place or time or departs from the place where he is`
  line `bound to attend before the time at which it is lawful for him to depart,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the summons, notice, order or proclamation is to attend in person or by agent in a`
  line `Court with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, being legally bound to appear before a High Court, in obedience to a subpoena issuing from`
  line `that Court, intentionally omits to appear. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A, being legally bound to appear before a District Judge, as a witness, in obedience to a summons`
  line `issued by that District Judge intentionally omits to appear. A has committed the offence defined in this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (90742)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 209
  title `Non-appearance in response to a proclamation under section 84 of Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90742&sectionno=209&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to appear at the specified place and the specified time as`
  line `required by a proclamation published under sub-section (1) of section 84 of the Bharatiya Nagarik`
  line `Suraksha Sanhita, 2023, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years,`
  line `or with fine, or with both, or with community service, and where a declaration has been made under`
  line `sub-section (4) of that section pronouncing him as a proclaimed offender, he shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (90743)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 210
  title `Omission to produce document or electronic record to public servant by person legally bound to produce it`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90743&sectionno=210&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally bound to produce or deliver up any document or`
  line `electronic record to any public servant, as such, intentionally omits so to produce or deliver up the`
  line same,—
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) and where the document or electronic record is to be produced or delivered up to a Court with`
  line `simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, being legally bound to produce a document before a District Court, intentionally omits to produce`
  line `the same. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (90576)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 211
  title `Omission to give notice or information to public servant by person legally bound to give it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90576&sectionno=211&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally bound to give any notice or to furnish information on any subject to any`
  line `public servant, as such, intentionally omits to give such notice or to furnish such information in the`
  line `manner and at the time required by law,—.`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;.`
  line
  line `(b) where the notice or information required to be given respects the commission of an offence,`
  line `or is required for the purpose of preventing the commission of an offence, or in order to the`
  line `apprehension of an offender, with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;.`
  line
  line `(c) where the notice or information required to be given is required by an order passed`
  line `under section 394 of the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (90577)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 212
  title `Furnishing false information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90577&sectionno=212&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally bound to furnish information on any`
  line `subject to any public servant, as such, furnishes, as true, information on the subject which he knows or`
  line `has reason to believe to be false,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the information which he is legally bound to give respects the commission of an`
  line `offence, or is required for the purpose of preventing the commission of an offence, or in order to the`
  line `apprehension of an offender, with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, a landholder, knowing of the commission of a murder within the limits of his estate, wilfully`
  line `misinforms the Magistrate of the district that the death has occurred by accident in consequence of the`
  line `bite of a snake. A is guilty of the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a village watchman, knowing that a considerable body of strangers has passed through his`
  line `village in order to commit a dacoity in the house of Z, a wealthy merchant residing in a neighbouring`
  line `place, and being legally bound to give early and punctual information of the above fact to the officer of`
  line `the nearest police station, wilfully misinforms the police officer that a body of suspicious characters`
  line `passed through the village with a view to commit dacoity in a certain distant place in a different direction.`
  line `Here A is guilty of the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In section 211 and in this section the word “offence” include any act committed at any`
  line `place out of India, which, if committed in India, would be punishable under any of the following sections,`
  line `namely, 103, 105, 307, sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 309, sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (5) of`
  line `section 310, 311, 312, clauses (f) and (g) of section 326, sub-sections (4), (6), (7) and (8) of section 331,`
  line `clauses (a) and (b) of section 332 and the word “offender” includes any person who is alleged to have`
  line `been guilty of any such act.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (90578)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 213
  title `Refusing oath or affirmation when duly required by public servant to make it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90578&sectionno=213&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `refuses to bind himself by an oath or affirmation to state the truth, when required so to bind himself by a`
  line `public servant legally competent to require that he shall so bind himself, shall be punished with simple`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (90579)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 214
  title `Refusing to answer public servant authorised to question.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90579&sectionno=214&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally bound to`
  line `state the truth on any subject to any public servant, refuses to answer any question demanded of him`
  line `touching that subject by such public servant in the exercise of the legal powers of such public servant,`
  line `shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (90580)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 215
  title `Refusing to sign statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90580&sectionno=215&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `Whoever refuses to sign any statement made by him, when`
  line `required to sign that statement by a public servant legally competent to require that he shall sign that`
  line `statement, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to three thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (90744)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 216
  title `False statement on oath or affirmation to public servant or person authorised to administer an oath or affirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90744&sectionno=216&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally bound by an oath or affirmation to state`
  line `the truth on any subject to any public servant or other person authorised by law to administer such oath or`
  line `affirmation, makes, to such public servant or other person as aforesaid, touching that subject, any`
  line `statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (90745)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 217
  title `False information, with intent to cause public servant to use his lawful power to injury of another person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90745&sectionno=217&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `Whoever gives to any public servant any information which he knows or believes to be`
  line `false, intending thereby to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby cause, such public`
  line servant—
  line
  line `(a) to do or omit anything which such public servant ought not to do or omit if the true state of`
  line `facts respecting which such information is given were known by him; or`
  line
  line `(b) to use the lawful power of such public servant to the injury or annoyance of any person,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A informs a Magistrate that Z, a police officer, subordinate to such Magistrate, has been guilty of`
  line `neglect of duty or misconduct, knowing such information to be false, and knowing it to be likely that the`
  line `information will cause the Magistrate to dismiss Z. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A falsely informs a public servant that Z has contraband salt in a secret place, knowing such`
  line `information to be false, and knowing that it is likely that the consequence of the information will be a`
  line `search of Z’s premises, attended with annoyance to Z. A has committed the offence defined in this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(c) A falsely informs a policeman that he has been assaulted and robbed in the neighbourhood of a`
  line `particular village. He does not mention the name of any person as one of his assailants, but knows it to be`
  line `likely that in consequence of this information the police will make enquiries and institute searches in the`
  line `village to the annoyance of the villagers or some of them. A has committed an offence under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (90583)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 218
  title `Resistance to taking of property by lawful authority of a public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90583&sectionno=218&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `Whoever offers`
  line `any resistance to the taking of any property by the lawful authority of any public servant, knowing or`
  line `having reason to believe that he is such public servant, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (90584)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 219
  title `Obstructing sale of property offered for sale by authority of public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90584&sectionno=219&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `intentionally obstructs any sale of property offered for sale by the lawful authority of any public servant,`
  line `as such, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one`
  line `month, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (90585)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 220
  title `Illegal purchase or bid for property offered for sale by authority of public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90585&sectionno=220&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, at any sale of property held by the lawful authority of a public servant, as such, purchases or`
  line `bids for any property on account of any person, whether himself or any other, whom he knows to be`
  line `under a legal incapacity to purchase that property at that sale, or bids for such property not intending to`
  line `perform the obligations under which he lays himself by such bidding, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to two hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (90586)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 221
  title `Obstructing public servant in discharge of public functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90586&sectionno=221&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `Whoever voluntarily obstructs`
  line `any public servant in the discharge of his public functions, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to two thousand`
  line `and five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (90587)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 222
  title `Omission to assist public servant when bound by law to give assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90587&sectionno=222&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being`
  line `bound by law to render or furnish assistance to any public servant in the execution of his public duty,`
  line `intentionally omits to give such assistance,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to two thousand and five hundred rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) and where such assistance be demanded of him by a public servant legally competent to make`
  line `such demand for the purposes of executing any process lawfully issued by a Court or of preventing`
  line `the commission of an offence, or suppressing a riot, or affray, or of apprehending a person charged`
  line `with or guilty of an offence, or of having escaped from lawful custody, shall be punished with simple`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (90588)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 223
  title `Disobedience to order duly promulgated by public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90588&sectionno=223&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing that, by an`
  line `order promulgated by a public servant lawfully empowered to promulgate such order, he is directed to abstain from a certain act, or to take certain order with certain property in his possession or under his`
  line `management, disobeys such direction,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall, if such disobedience causes or tends to cause obstruction, annoyance or injury, or risk`
  line `of obstruction, annoyance or injury, to any person lawfully employed, be punished with simple`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand and five hundred rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) and where such disobedience causes or tends to cause danger to human life, health or safety,`
  line `or causes or tends to cause a riot or affray, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—It is not necessary that the offender should intend to produce harm, or contemplate his`
  line `disobedience as likely to produce harm. It is sufficient that he knows of the order which he disobeys, and`
  line `that his disobedience produces, or is likely to produce, harm.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `An order is promulgated by a public servant lawfully empowered to promulgate such order, directing`
  line `that a religious procession shall not pass down a certain street. A knowingly disobeys the order, and`
  line `thereby causes danger of riot. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (90589)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 224
  title `Threat of injury to public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90589&sectionno=224&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `Whoever holds out any threat of injury to any public`
  line `servant, or to any person in whom he believes that public servant to be interested, for the purpose of`
  line `inducing that public servant to do any act, or to forbear or delay to do any act, connected with the`
  line `exercise of the public functions of such public servant, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (90590)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 225
  title `Threat of injury to induce person to refrain from applying for protection to public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90590&sectionno=225&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `Whoever holds out any threat of injury to any person for the purpose of inducing that person`
  line `to refrain or desist from making a legal application for protection against any injury to any public servant`
  line `legally empowered as such to give such protection, or to cause such protection to be given, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (90591)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 226
  title `Attempt to commit suicide to compel or restrain exercise of lawful power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90591&sectionno=226&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `attempts to commit suicide with the intent to compel or restrain any public servant from discharging his`
  line `official duty shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine, or with both, or with community service.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (90592)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 227
  title `Giving false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90592&sectionno=227&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being legally bound by an oath or by an express provision of`
  line `law to state the truth, or being bound by law to make a declaration upon any subject, makes any statement`
  line `which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, is said to`
  line `give false evidence.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A statement is within the meaning of this section, whether it is made verbally or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—A false statement as to the belief of the person attesting is within the meaning of this`
  line `section, and a person may be guilty of giving false evidence by stating that he believes a thing which he`
  line `does not believe, as well as by stating that he knows a thing which he does not know.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, in support of a just claim which B has against Z for one thousand rupees, falsely swears on a`
  line `trial that he heard Z admit the justice of Bs claim. A has given false evidence.`
  line
  line `(b) A, being bound by an oath to state the truth, states that he believes a certain signature to be the`
  line `handwriting of Z, when he does not believe it to be the handwriting of Z. Here A states that which he`
  line `knows to be false, and therefore gives false evidence.`
  line
  line `(c) A, knowing the general character of Zs handwriting, states that he believes a certain signature to`
  line `be the handwriting of Z; A in good faith believing it to be so. Here As statement is merely as to his`
  line `belief, and is true as to his belief, and therefore, although the signature may not be the handwriting of Z,`
  line `A has not given false evidence.`
  line
  line `(d) A, being bound by an oath to state the truth, states that he knows that Z was at a particular place`
  line `on a particular day, not knowing anything upon the subject. A gives false evidence whether Z was at that`
  line `place on the day named or not.`
  line
  line `(e) A, an interpreter or translator, gives or certifies as a true interpretation or translation of a`
  line `statement or document which he is bound by oath to interpret or translate truly, that which is not and`
  line `which he does not believe to be a true interpretation or translation. A has given false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (90593)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 228
  title `Fabricating false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90593&sectionno=228&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `Whoever causes any circumstance to exist or makes any false`
  line `entry in any book or record, or electronic record or makes any document or electronic record containing a`
  line `false statement, intending that such circumstance, false entry or false statement may appear in evidence in`
  line `a judicial proceeding, or in a proceeding taken by law before a public servant as such, or before an`
  line `arbitrator, and that such circumstance, false entry or false statement, so appearing in evidence, may cause`
  line `any person who in such proceeding is to form an opinion upon the evidence, to entertain an erroneous`
  line `opinion touching any point material to the result of such proceeding is said "to fabricate false evidence".`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A puts jewels into a box belonging to Z, with the intention that they may be found in that box, and`
  line `that this circumstance may cause Z to be convicted of theft. A has fabricated false evidence.`
  line
  line `(b) A makes a false entry in his shop-book for the purpose of using it as corroborative evidence in a`
  line `Court. A has fabricated false evidence.`
  line
  line `(c) A, with the intention of causing Z to be convicted of a criminal conspiracy, writes a letter in`
  line `imitation of Z's handwriting, purporting to be addressed to an accomplice in such criminal conspiracy,`
  line `and puts the letter in a place which he knows that the officers of the police are likely to search. A has`
  line `fabricated false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (90594)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 229
  title `Punishment for false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90594&sectionno=229&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever intentionally gives false evidence in any stage`
  line `of a judicial proceeding, or fabricates false evidence for the purpose of being used in any stage of a`
  line `judicial proceeding, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever intentionally gives or fabricates false evidence in any case other than that referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years, and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A trial before a Court-martial is a judicial proceeding.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—An investigation directed by law preliminary to a proceeding before a Court, is a`
  line `stage of a judicial proceeding, though that investigation may not take place before a Court.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, in an enquiry before a Magistrate for the purpose of ascertaining whether Z ought to be committed`
  line `for trial, makes on oath a statement which he knows to be false. As this enquiry is a stage of a judicial`
  line `proceeding, A has given false evidence.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.—An investigation directed by a Court according to law, and conducted under the`
  line `authority of a Court, is a stage of a judicial proceeding, though that investigation may not take place`
  line `before a Court.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, in an enquiry before an officer deputed by a Court to ascertain on the spot the boundaries of land,`
  line `makes on oath a statement which he knows to be false. As this enquiry is a stage of a judicial proceeding,`
  line `A has given false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (90595)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 230
  title `Giving or fabricating false evidence with intent to procure conviction of capital offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90595&sectionno=230&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever gives or fabricates false evidence, intending thereby to cause, or knowing it to be likely that`
  line `he will thereby cause, any person to be convicted of an offence which is capital by the law for the time`
  line `being in force in India shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(2) If an innocent person be convicted and executed in consequence of false evidence referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), the person who gives such false evidence shall be punished either with death or the`
  line `punishment specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (90746)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 231
  title `Giving or fabricating false evidence with intent to procure conviction of offence punishable with imprisonment for life or imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90746&sectionno=231&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `Whoever gives or fabricates false evidence intending`
  line `thereby to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby cause, any person to be convicted of an`
  line `offence which by the law for the time being in force in India is not capital, but punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or imprisonment for a term of seven years or upwards, shall be punished as a`
  line `person convicted of that offence would be liable to be punished.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A gives false evidence before a Court, intending thereby to cause Z to be convicted of a dacoity. The`
  line `punishment of dacoity is imprisonment for life, or rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `ten years, with or without fine. A, therefore, is liable to imprisonment for life or imprisonment, with or`
  line `without fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (90597)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 232
  title `Threatening any person to give false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90597&sectionno=232&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever threatens another with any`
  line `injury to his person, reputation or property or to the person or reputation of any one in whom that person`
  line `is interested, with intent to cause that person to give false evidence shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If innocent person is convicted and sentenced in consequence of false evidence referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), with death or imprisonment for more than seven years, the person who threatens shall be`
  line `punished with the same punishment and sentence in the same manner and to the same extent such`
  line `innocent person is punished and sentenced.`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (90598)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 233
  title `Using evidence known to be false.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90598&sectionno=233&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `Whoever corruptly uses or attempts to use as true or`
  line `genuine evidence any evidence which he knows to be false or fabricated, shall be punished in the same`
  line `manner as if he gave or fabricated false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (90599)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 234
  title `Issuing or signing false certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90599&sectionno=234&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `Whoever issues or signs any certificate required by law to`
  line `be given or signed, or relating to any fact of which such certificate is by law admissible in evidence,`
  line `knowing or believing that such certificate is false in any material point, shall be punished in the same`
  line `manner as if he gave false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (90600)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 235
  title `Using as true a certificate known to be false.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90600&sectionno=235&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `Whoever corruptly uses or attempts to use any`
  line `such certificate as a true certificate, knowing the same to be false in any material point, shall be punished`
  line `in the same manner as if he gave false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (90601)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 236
  title `False statement made in declaration which is by law receivable as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90601&sectionno=236&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in`
  line `any declaration made or subscribed by him, which declaration any Court or any public servant or other`
  line `person, is bound or authorised by law to receive as evidence of any fact, makes any statement which is`
  line `false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, touching any point`
  line `material to the object for which the declaration is made or used, shall be punished in the same manner as`
  line `if he gave false evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (90602)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 237
  title `Using as true such declaration knowing it to be false.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90602&sectionno=237&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line `Whoever corruptly uses or attempts to`
  line `use as true any such declaration, knowing the same to be false in any material point, shall be punished in`
  line `the same manner as if he gave false evidence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A declaration which is inadmissible merely upon the ground of some informality, is a`
  line `declaration within the meaning of section 236 and this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (90747)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 238
  title `Causing disappearance of evidence of offence, or giving false information to screen offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90747&sectionno=238&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing or having reason to believe that an offence has been committed, causes`
  line `any evidence of the commission of that offence to disappear, with the intention of screening the offender`
  line `from legal punishment, or with that intention gives any information respecting the offence which he`
  line `knows or believes to be false shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence which he knows or believes to have been committed is punishable with death,`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to ten years, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to three years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(c) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for any term not extending to ten years, be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of the description provided for the offence, for a term which may extend`
  line `to one-fourth part of the longest term of the imprisonment provided for the offence, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, knowing that B has murdered Z, assists B to hide the body with the intention of screening B from`
  line `punishment. A is liable to imprisonment of either description for seven years, and also to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (90604)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 239
  title `Intentional omission to give information of offence by person bound to inform.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90604&sectionno=239&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line Whoever,
  line `knowing or having reason to believe that an offence has been committed, intentionally omits to give any`
  line `information respecting that offence which he is legally bound to give, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  sectionId (90605)
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 240
  title `Giving false information respecting an offence committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90605&sectionno=240&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing or having`
  line `reason to believe that an offence has been committed, gives any information respecting that offence`
  line `which he knows or believes to be false, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In sections 238 and 239 and in this section the word "offence" includes any act`
  line `committed at any place out of India, which, if committed in India, would be punishable under any of the`
  line `following sections, namely, 103, 105, 307, sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 309, sub-sections (2),`
  line `(3), (4) and (5) of section 310, 311, 312, clauses (f) and (g) of section 326, sub-sections (4), (6), (7) and`
  line `(8) of section 331, clauses (a) and (b) of section 332.`
obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (90606)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 241
  title `Destruction of document or electronic record to prevent its production as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90606&sectionno=241&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `Whoever secretes or destroys any document or electronic record which he may be lawfully compelled to`
  line `produce as evidence in a Court or in any proceeding lawfully held before a public servant, as such, or`
  line `obliterates or renders illegible the whole or any part of such document or electronic record with the`
  line `intention of preventing the same from being produced or used as evidence before such Court or public`
  line `servant as aforesaid, or after he shall have been lawfully summoned or required to produce the same for`
  line `that purpose, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (90607)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 242
  title `False personation for purpose of act or proceeding in suit or prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90607&sectionno=242&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `Whoever falsely`
  line `personates another, and in such assumed character makes any admission or statement, or confesses`
  line `judgment, or causes any process to be issued or becomes bail or security, or does any other act in any suit`
  line `or criminal prosecution, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_243:
  sectionId (90748)
  sectionNo (243)
  orderNo 243
  title `Fraudulent removal or concealment of property to prevent its seizure as forfeited or in execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_243_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90748&sectionno=243&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_243_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fraudulently removes, conceals, transfers or delivers to any person any property or`
  line `any interest therein, intending thereby to prevent that property or interest therein from being taken as a`
  line `forfeiture or in satisfaction of a fine, under a sentence which has been pronounced, or which he knows to`
  line `be likely to be pronounced, by a Court or other competent authority, or from being taken in execution of a`
  line `decree or order which has been made, or which he knows to be likely to be made by a Court in a civil`
  line `suit, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_244:
  sectionId (90609)
  sectionNo (244)
  orderNo 244
  title `Fraudulent claim to property to prevent its seizure as forfeited or in execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_244_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90609&sectionno=244&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `fraudulently accepts, receives or claims any property or any interest therein, knowing that he has no right`
  line `or rightful claim to such property or interest, or practises any deception touching any right to any`
  line `property or any interest therein, intending thereby to prevent that property or interest therein from being`
  line `taken as a forfeiture or in satisfaction of a fine, under a sentence which has been pronounced, or which he`
  line `knows to be likely to be pronounced by a Court or other competent authority, or from being taken in`
  line `execution of a decree or order which has been made, or which he knows to be likely to be made by a`
  line `Court in a civil suit, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_245:
  sectionId (90610)
  sectionNo (245)
  orderNo 245
  title `Fraudulently suffering decree for sum not due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_245_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90610&sectionno=245&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_245_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fraudulently causes or suffers a`
  line `decree or order to be passed against him at the suit of any person for a sum not due or for a larger sum`
  line `than is due to such person or for any property or interest in property to which such person is not entitled,`
  line `or fraudulently causes or suffers a decree or order to be executed against him after it has been satisfied, or`
  line `for anything in respect of which it has been satisfied, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A institutes a suit against Z. Z, knowing that A is likely to obtain a decree against him, fraudulently`
  line `suffers a judgment to pass against him for a larger amount at the suit of B, who has no just claim against`
  line `him, in order that B, either on his own account or for the benefit of Z, may share in the proceeds of any`
  line `sale of Zs property which may be made under As decree. Z has committed an offence under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_246:
  sectionId (90611)
  sectionNo (246)
  orderNo 246
  title `Dishonestly making false claim in Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_246_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90611&sectionno=246&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_246_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fraudulently or dishonestly, or with`
  line `intent to injure or annoy any person, makes in a Court any claim which he knows to be false, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_247:
  sectionId (90612)
  sectionNo (247)
  orderNo 247
  title `Fraudulently obtaining decree for sum not due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_247_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90612&sectionno=247&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_247_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fraudulently obtains a decree or`
  line `order against any person for a sum not due, or for a larger sum than is due or for any property or interest`
  line `in property to which he is not entitled, or fraudulently causes a decree or order to be executed against any`
  line `person after it has been satisfied or for anything in respect of which it has been satisfied, or fraudulently`
  line `suffers or permits any such act to be done in his name, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_248:
  sectionId (90613)
  sectionNo (248)
  orderNo 248
  title `False charge of offence made with intent to injure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_248_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90613&sectionno=248&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_248_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with intent to cause injury to`
  line `any person, institutes or causes to be instituted any criminal proceeding against that person, or falsely`
  line `charges any person with having committed an offence, knowing that there is no just or lawful ground for`
  line `such proceeding or charge against that person,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to five`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) if such criminal proceeding be instituted on a false charge of an offence punishable with`
  line `death, imprisonment for life, or imprisonment for ten years or upwards, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_249:
  sectionId (90614)
  sectionNo (249)
  orderNo 249
  title `Harbouring offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_249_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90614&sectionno=249&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_249_content:
  string
  line `Whenever an offence has been committed, whoever harbours or`
  line `conceals a person whom he knows or has reason to believe to be the offender, with the intention of`
  line `screening him from legal punishment shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence is punishable with death, be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to ten years, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to three years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(c) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment which may extend to one year, and not to ten`
  line `years, be punished with imprisonment of the description provided for the offence for a term which`
  line `may extend to one-fourth part of the longest term of imprisonment provided for the offence, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— "Offence" in this section includes any act committed at any place out of India, which,`
  line `if committed in India, would be punishable under any of the following sections, namely, 103, 105, 307,`
  line `sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 309, sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (5) of section 310, 311, 312,`
  line `clauses (f) and (g) of section 326, sub-sections (4), (6), (7) and (8) of section 331, clauses (a) and (b) of`
  line `section 332 and every such act shall, for the purposes of this section, be deemed to be punishable as if the`
  line `accused person had been guilty of it in India.`
  line
  line `Exception.—This section shall not extend to any case in which the harbour or concealment is by the`
  line `spouse of the offender.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, knowing that B has committed dacoity, knowingly conceals B in order to screen him from legal`
  line `punishment. Here, as B is liable to imprisonment for life, A is liable to imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term not exceeding three years, and is also liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_250:
  sectionId (90615)
  sectionNo (250)
  orderNo 250
  title `Taking gift, etc., to screen an offender from punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_250_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90615&sectionno=250&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_250_content:
  string
  line `Whoever accepts or attempts to`
  line `obtain, or agrees to accept, any gratification for himself or any other person, or any restitution of property`
  line `to himself or any other person, in consideration of his concealing an offence or of his screening any`
  line `person from legal punishment for any offence, or of his not proceeding against any person for the purpose`
  line `of bringing him to legal punishment shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence is punishable with death, be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to ten years, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to three years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(c) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment not extending to ten years, be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of the description provided for the offence for a term which may extend to one-fourth`
  line `part of the longest term of imprisonment provided for the offence, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_251:
  sectionId (90616)
  sectionNo (251)
  orderNo 251
  title `Offering gift or restoration of property in consideration of screening offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_251_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90616&sectionno=251&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_251_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `gives or causes, or offers or agrees to give or cause, any gratification to any person, or restores or causes`
  line `the restoration of any property to any person, in consideration of that person’s concealing an offence, or`
  line `of his screening any person from legal punishment for any offence, or of his not proceeding against any`
  line `person for the purpose of bringing him to legal punishment shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence is punishable with death, be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for life or with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to ten years, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to three years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(c) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment not extending to ten years, be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of the description provided for the offence for a term which may extend to one-fourth`
  line `part of the longest term of imprisonment provided for the offence, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Exception.—The provisions of this section and section 250 do not extend to any case in which the`
  line `offence may lawfully be compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_252:
  sectionId (90617)
  sectionNo (252)
  orderNo 252
  title `Taking gift to help to recover stolen property, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_252_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90617&sectionno=252&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_252_content:
  string
  line `Whoever takes or agrees or consents to`
  line `take any gratification under pretence or on account of helping any person to recover any movable`
  line `property of which he shall have been deprived by any offence punishable under this Sanhita, shall, unless`
  line `he uses all means in his power to cause the offender to be apprehended and convicted of the offence, be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_253:
  sectionId (90749)
  sectionNo (253)
  orderNo 253
  title `Harbouring offender who has escaped from custody or whose apprehension has been ordered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_253_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90749&sectionno=253&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_253_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person convicted of or charged with an offence, being in lawful custody for`
  line `that offence, escapes from such custody, or whenever a public servant, in the exercise of the lawful`
  line `powers of such public servant, orders a certain person to be apprehended for an offence, whoever,`
  line `knowing of such escape or order for apprehension, harbours or conceals that person with the intention of`
  line `preventing him from being apprehended, shall be punished in the manner following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence for which the person was in custody or is ordered to be apprehended is`
  line `punishable with death, he shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for life or imprisonment for ten years, he shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, with`
  line `or without fine;`
  line
  line `(c) if the offence is punishable with imprisonment which may extend to one year and not to ten`
  line `years, he shall be punished with imprisonment of the description provided for the offence for a term`
  line `which may extend to one-fourth part of the longest term of the imprisonment provided for such`
  line `offence, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—"Offence" in this section includes also any act or omission of which a person is`
  line `alleged to have been guilty out of India, which, if he had been guilty of it in India, would have been`
  line `punishable as an offence, and for which he is, under any law relating to extradition, or otherwise, liable to`
  line `be apprehended or detained in custody in India, and every such act or omission shall, for the purposes of`
  line `this section, be deemed to be punishable as if the accused person had been guilty of it in India.`
  line
  line `Exception.—The provisions of this section do not extend to the case in which the harbour or`
  line `concealment is by the spouse of the person to be apprehended.`
obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_254:
  sectionId (90619)
  sectionNo (254)
  orderNo 254
  title `Penalty for harbouring robbers or dacoits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_254_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90619&sectionno=254&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_254_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing or having reason to believe`
  line `that any persons are about to commit or have recently committed robbery or dacoity, harbours them or`
  line `any of them, with the intention of facilitating the commission of such robbery or dacoity, or of screening`
  line `them or any of them from punishment, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section it is immaterial whether the robbery or dacoity is`
  line `intended to be committed, or has been committed, within or without India.`
  line
  line `Exception.—The provisions of this section do not extend to the case in which the harbour is by the`
  line `spouse of the offender.`
obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_255:
  sectionId (90750)
  sectionNo (255)
  orderNo 255
  title `Public servant disobeying direction of law with intent to save person from punishment or property from forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_255_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90750&sectionno=255&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_255_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, knowingly disobeys any direction of the`
  line `law as to the way in which he is to conduct himself as such public servant, intending thereby to save, or`
  line `knowing it to be likely that he will thereby save, any person from legal punishment, or subject him to a`
  line `less punishment than that to which he is liable, or with intent to save, or knowing that he is likely thereby`
  line `to save, any property from forfeiture or any charge to which it is liable by law, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_256:
  sectionId (90751)
  sectionNo (256)
  orderNo 256
  title `Public servant framing incorrect record or writing with intent to save person from punishment or property from forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_256_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90751&sectionno=256&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_256_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, and being as such public`
  line `servant, charged with the preparation of any record or other writing, frames that record or writing in a`
  line `manner which he knows to be incorrect, with intent to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he will`
  line `thereby cause, loss or injury to the public or to any person, or with intent thereby to save, or knowing it to`
  line `be likely that he will thereby save, any person from legal punishment, or with intent to save, or knowing`
  line `that he is likely thereby to save, any property from forfeiture or other charge to which it is liable by law,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_257:
  sectionId (90622)
  sectionNo (257)
  orderNo 257
  title `Public servant in judicial proceeding corruptly making report, etc., contrary to law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_257_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90622&sectionno=257&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_257_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, corruptly or maliciously makes or pronounces in any stage of a judicial`
  line `proceeding, any report, order, verdict, or decision which he knows to be contrary to law, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_258:
  sectionId (90752)
  sectionNo (258)
  orderNo 258
  title `Commitment for trial or confinement by person having authority who knows that he is acting contrary to law`
  content obj_root_law_sections_258_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90752&sectionno=258&orderno=258&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_258_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being in any office which gives him legal authority to commit`
  line `persons for trial or to confinement, or to keep persons in confinement, corruptly or maliciously commits`
  line `any person for trial or to confinement, or keeps any person in confinement, in the exercise of that`
  line `authority knowing that in so doing he is acting contrary to law, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_259:
  sectionId (90624)
  sectionNo (259)
  orderNo 259
  title `Intentional omission to apprehend on part of public servant bound to apprehend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_259_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90624&sectionno=259&orderno=259&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_259_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, legally bound as such public servant to apprehend or to keep in`
  line `confinement any person charged with or liable to be apprehended for an offence, intentionally omits to`
  line `apprehend such person, or intentionally suffers such person to escape, or intentionally aids such person in`
  line `escaping or attempting to escape from such confinement, shall be punished,—`
  line
  line `(a) with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, with or`
  line `without fine, if the person in confinement, or who ought to have been apprehended, was charged`
  line `with, or liable to be apprehended for, an offence punishable with death; or`
  line
  line `(b) with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, with or`
  line `without fine, if the person in confinement, or who ought to have been apprehended, was charged`
  line `with, or liable to be apprehended for, an offence punishable with imprisonment for life or`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years; or`
  line
  line `(c) with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, with or`
  line `without fine, if the person in confinement, or who ought to have been apprehended, was charged`
  line `with, or liable to be apprehended for, an offence punishable with imprisonment for a term less than`
  line `ten years.`
obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_260:
  sectionId (90753)
  sectionNo (260)
  orderNo 260
  title `Intentional omission to apprehend on part of public servant bound to apprehend person under sentence or lawfully committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_260_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90753&sectionno=260&orderno=260&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_260_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant, legally bound as such public`
  line `servant to apprehend or to keep in confinement any person under sentence of a Court for any offence or`
  line `lawfully committed to custody, intentionally omits to apprehend such person, or intentionally suffers such`
  line `person to escape or intentionally aids such person in escaping or attempting to escape from such`
  line `confinement, shall be punished,—`
  line
  line `(a) with imprisonment for life or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to fourteen years, with or without fine, if the person in confinement, or who ought to have`
  line `been apprehended, is under sentence of death; or`
  line
  line `(b) with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, with or`
  line `without fine, if the person in confinement or who ought to have been apprehended, is subject, by a`
  line `sentence of a Court, or by virtue of a commutation of such sentence, to imprisonment for life or`
  line `imprisonment for a term of ten years, or upwards; or`
  line
  line `(c) with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or with`
  line `fine, or with both, if the person in confinement or who ought to have been apprehended, is subject by`
  line `a sentence of a Court to imprisonment for a term not extending to ten years or if the person was`
  line `lawfully committed to custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_261:
  sectionId (90626)
  sectionNo (261)
  orderNo 261
  title `Escape from confinement or custody negligently suffered by public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_261_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90626&sectionno=261&orderno=261&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_261_content:
  string
  line Whoever,
  line `being a public servant legally bound as such public servant to keep in confinement any person charged`
  line `with or convicted of any offence or lawfully committed to custody, negligently suffers such person to`
  line `escape from confinement, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_262:
  sectionId (90627)
  sectionNo (262)
  orderNo 262
  title `Resistance or obstruction by a person to his lawful apprehension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_262_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90627&sectionno=262&orderno=262&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_262_content:
  string
  line `Whoever intentionally`
  line `offers any resistance or illegal obstruction to the lawful apprehension of himself for any offence with`
  line `which he is charged or of which he has been convicted, or escapes or attempts to escape from any`
  line `custody in which he is lawfully detained for any such offence, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The punishment in this section is in addition to the punishment for which the person`
  line `to be apprehended or detained in custody was liable for the offence with which he was charged, or of`
  line `which he was convicted.`
obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_263:
  sectionId (90628)
  sectionNo (263)
  orderNo 263
  title `Resistance or obstruction to lawful apprehension of another person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_263_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90628&sectionno=263&orderno=263&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_263_content:
  string
  line Whoever,
  line `intentionally offers any resistance or illegal obstruction to the lawful apprehension of any other person for`
  line `an offence, or rescues or attempts to rescue any other person from any custody in which that person is`
  line `lawfully detained for an offence,—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years, or with fine, or with both; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the person to be apprehended, or the person rescued or attempted to be rescued, is charged`
  line `with or liable to be apprehended for an offence punishable with imprisonment for life or`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the person to be apprehended or rescued, or attempted to be rescued, is charged with or`
  line `liable to be apprehended for an offence punishable with death, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine; or`
  line
  line `(d) if the person to be apprehended or rescued, or attempted to be rescued, is liable under the`
  line `sentence of a Court or by virtue of a commutation of such a sentence, to imprisonment for life, or`
  line `imprisonment for a term of ten years or upwards, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine; or`
  line
  line `(e) if the person to be apprehended or rescued, or attempted to be rescued, is under sentence of`
  line `death, shall be punished with imprisonment for life or imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `not exceeding ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_264:
  sectionId (90754)
  sectionNo (264)
  orderNo 264
  title `Omission to apprehend, or sufferance of escape, on part of public servant, in cases not otherwise provided for`
  content obj_root_law_sections_264_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90754&sectionno=264&orderno=264&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_264_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a public servant legally bound as such public servant to`
  line `apprehend, or to keep in confinement, any person in any case not provided for in section 259, section 260`
  line `or section 261, or in any other law for the time being in force, omits to apprehend that person or suffers`
  line `him to escape from confinement, shall be punished—`
  line
  line `(a) if he does so intentionally, with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with fine, or with both; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he does so negligently, with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_265:
  sectionId (90755)
  sectionNo (265)
  orderNo 265
  title `Resistance or obstruction to lawful apprehension or escape or rescue in cases not otherwise provided for.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_265_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90755&sectionno=265&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_265_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in any case not provided for in section 262 or section 263 or in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, intentionally offers any resistance or illegal obstruction to the lawful`
  line `apprehension of himself or of any other person, or escapes or attempts to escape from any custody in`
  line `which he is lawfully detained, or rescues or attempts to rescue any other person from any custody in`
  line `which that person is lawfully detained, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_266:
  sectionId (90631)
  sectionNo (266)
  orderNo 266
  title `Violation of condition of remission of punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_266_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90631&sectionno=266&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_266_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having accepted any`
  line `conditional remission of punishment, knowingly violates any condition on which such remission was`
  line `granted, shall be punished with the punishment to which he was originally sentenced, if he has already`
  line `suffered no part of that punishment, and if he has suffered any part of that punishment, then with so much`
  line `of that punishment as he has not already suffered.`
obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_267:
  sectionId (90632)
  sectionNo (267)
  orderNo 267
  title `Intentional insult or interruption to public servant sitting in judicial proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_267_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90632&sectionno=267&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_267_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, intentionally offers any insult, or causes any interruption to any public servant, while such`
  line `public servant is sitting in any stage of a judicial proceeding, shall be punished with simple imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_268:
  sectionId (90633)
  sectionNo (268)
  orderNo 268
  title `Personation of assessor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_268_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90633&sectionno=268&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_268_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by personation or otherwise, shall intentionally cause, or`
  line `knowingly suffer himself to be returned, empanelled or sworn as an assessor in any case in which he`
  line `knows that he is not entitled by law to be so returned, empanelled or sworn, or knowing himself to have`
  line `been so returned, empanelled or sworn contrary to law, shall voluntarily serve as such assessor, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_269:
  sectionId (90634)
  sectionNo (269)
  orderNo 269
  title `Failure by person released on bail bond or bond to appear in Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_269_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90634&sectionno=269&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_269_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having`
  line `been charged with an offence and released on bail bond or on bond, fails without sufficient cause (the`
  line `burden of proving which shall lie upon him), to appear in Court in accordance with the terms of the bail`
  line `or bond, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The punishment under this section is—`
  line
  line `(a) in addition to the punishment to which the offender would be liable on a conviction for the`
  line `offence with which he has been charged; and`
  line
  line `(b) without prejudice to the power of the Court to order forfeiture of the bond.`
obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_270:
  sectionId (90635)
  sectionNo (270)
  orderNo 270
  title `Public nuisance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_270_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90635&sectionno=270&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line `A person is guilty of a public nuisance who does any act or is guilty of an`
  line `illegal omission which causes any common injury, danger or annoyance to the public or to the people in`
  line `general who dwell or occupy property in the vicinity, or which must necessarily cause injury, obstruction,`
  line `danger or annoyance to persons who may have occasion to use any public right but a common nuisance is`
  line `not excused on the ground that it causes some convenience or advantage.`
obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_271:
  sectionId (90636)
  sectionNo (271)
  orderNo 271
  title `Negligent act likely to spread infection of disease dangerous to life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_271_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90636&sectionno=271&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_271_content:
  string
  line `Whoever unlawfully or`
  line `negligently does any act which is, and which he knows or has reason to believe to be, likely to spread the`
  line `infection of any disease dangerous to life, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_272:
  sectionId (90637)
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 272
  title `Malignant act likely to spread infection of disease dangerous to life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90637&sectionno=272&orderno=272&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line `Whoever malignantly`
  line `does any act which is, and which he knows or has reason to believe to be, likely to spread the infection of`
  line `any disease dangerous to life, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_273:
  sectionId (90638)
  sectionNo (273)
  orderNo 273
  title `Disobedience to quarantine rule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90638&sectionno=273&orderno=273&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly disobeys any rule made by the`
  line `Government for putting any mode of transport into a state of quarantine, or for regulating the intercourse`
  line `of any such transport in a state of quarantine or for regulating the intercourse between places where an`
  line `infectious disease prevails and other places, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_274:
  sectionId (90639)
  sectionNo (274)
  orderNo 274
  title `Adulteration of food or drink intended for sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_274_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90639&sectionno=274&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line `Whoever adulterates any article of food or`
  line `drink, so as to make such article noxious as food or drink, intending to sell such article as food or drink,`
  line `or knowing it to be likely that the same will be sold as food or drink, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_275:
  sectionId (90640)
  sectionNo (275)
  orderNo 275
  title `Sale of noxious food or drink.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_275_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90640&sectionno=275&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_275_content:
  string
  line `Whoever sells, or offers or exposes for sale, as food or drink,`
  line `any article which has been rendered or has become noxious, or is in a state unfit for food or drink,`
  line `knowing or having reason to believe that the same is noxious as food or drink, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_276:
  sectionId (90641)
  sectionNo (276)
  orderNo 276
  title `Adulteration of drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_276_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90641&sectionno=276&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line `Whoever adulterates any drug or medical preparation in such a`
  line `manner as to lessen the efficacy or change the operation of such drug or medical preparation, or to make`
  line `it noxious, intending that it shall be sold or used for, or knowing it to be likely that it will be sold or used`
  line `for, any medicinal purpose, as if it had not undergone such adulteration, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_277:
  sectionId (90642)
  sectionNo (277)
  orderNo 277
  title `Sale of adulterated drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_277_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90642&sectionno=277&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, knowing any drug or medical preparation to have been`
  line `adulterated in such a manner as to lessen its efficacy, to change its operation, or to render it noxious, sells`
  line `the same, or offers or exposes it for sale, or issues it from any dispensary for medicinal purposes as`
  line `unadulterated, or causes it to be used for medicinal purposes by any person not knowing of the`
  line `adulteration, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  sectionId (90643)
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 278
  title `Sale of drug as a different drug or preparation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90643&sectionno=278&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly sells, or offers or`
  line `exposes for sale, or issues from a dispensary for medicinal purposes, any drug or medical preparation, as`
  line `a different drug or medical preparation, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_279:
  sectionId (90644)
  sectionNo (279)
  orderNo 279
  title `Fouling water of public spring or reservoir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_279_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90644&sectionno=279&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line `Whoever voluntarily corrupts or fouls the water`
  line `of any public spring or reservoir, so as to render it less fit for the purpose for which it is ordinarily used,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_280:
  sectionId (90645)
  sectionNo (280)
  orderNo 280
  title `Making atmosphere noxious to health.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_280_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90645&sectionno=280&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line `Whoever voluntarily vitiates the atmosphere in any`
  line `place so as to make it noxious to the health of persons in general dwelling or carrying on business in the`
  line `neighbourhood or passing along a public way, shall be punished with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_281:
  sectionId (90646)
  sectionNo (281)
  orderNo 281
  title `Rash driving or riding on a public way.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_281_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90646&sectionno=281&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line `Whoever drives any vehicle, or rides, on any public`
  line `way in a manner so rash or negligent as to endanger human life, or to be likely to cause hurt or injury to`
  line `any other person, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_282:
  sectionId (90647)
  sectionNo (282)
  orderNo 282
  title `Rash navigation of vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_282_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90647&sectionno=282&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line `Whoever navigates any vessel in a manner so rash or negligent as`
  line `to endanger human life, or to be likely to cause hurt or injury to any other person, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_283:
  sectionId (90648)
  sectionNo (283)
  orderNo 283
  title `Exhibition of false light, mark or buoy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_283_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90648&sectionno=283&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line `Whoever exhibits any false light, mark or buoy,`
  line `intending or knowing it to be likely that such exhibition will mislead any navigator, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  sectionId (90649)
  sectionNo (284)
  orderNo 284
  title `Conveying person by water for hire in unsafe or overloaded vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_284_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90649&sectionno=284&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_284_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly or`
  line `negligently conveys, or causes to be conveyed for hire, any person by water in any vessel, when that`
  line `vessel is in such a state or so loaded as to endanger the life of that person, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_285:
  sectionId (90650)
  sectionNo (285)
  orderNo 285
  title `Danger or obstruction in public way or line of navigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_285_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90650&sectionno=285&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_285_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by doing any act, or`
  line `by omitting to take order with any property in his possession or under his charge, causes danger,`
  line `obstruction or injury to any person in any public way or public line of navigation, shall be punished with`
  line `fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_286:
  sectionId (90651)
  sectionNo (286)
  orderNo 286
  title `Negligent conduct with respect to poisonous substance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_286_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90651&sectionno=286&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_286_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does, with any poisonous`
  line `substance, any act in a manner so rash or negligent as to endanger human life, or to be likely to cause hurt`
  line `or injury to any person or knowingly or negligently omits to take such order with any poisonous`
  line `substance in his possession as is sufficient to guard against any probable danger to human life from such`
  line `poisonous substance, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_287:
  sectionId (90652)
  sectionNo (287)
  orderNo 287
  title `Negligent conduct with respect to fire or combustible matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_287_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90652&sectionno=287&orderno=287&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does, with fire or`
  line `any combustible matter, any act so rashly or negligently as to endanger human life, or to be likely to`
  line `cause hurt or injury to any other person or knowingly or negligently omits to take such order with any fire`
  line `or any combustible matter in his possession as is sufficient to guard against any probable danger to`
  line `human life from such fire or combustible matter, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to two thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_288:
  sectionId (90653)
  sectionNo (288)
  orderNo 288
  title `Negligent conduct with respect to explosive substance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_288_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90653&sectionno=288&orderno=288&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does, with any explosive`
  line `substance, any act so rashly or negligently as to endanger human life, or to be likely to cause hurt or`
  line `injury to any other person, or knowingly or negligently omits to take such order with any explosive`
  line `substance in his possession as is sufficient to guard against any probable danger to human life from that`
  line `substance, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_289:
  sectionId (90654)
  sectionNo (289)
  orderNo 289
  title `Negligent conduct with respect to machinery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_289_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90654&sectionno=289&orderno=289&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line `Whoever does, with any machinery, any act`
  line `so rashly or negligently as to endanger human life or to be likely to cause hurt or injury to any other`
  line `person or knowingly or negligently omits to take such order with any machinery in his possession or`
  line `under his care as is sufficient to guard against any probable danger to human life from such machinery,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_290:
  sectionId (90655)
  sectionNo (290)
  orderNo 290
  title `Negligent conduct with respect to pulling down, repairing or constructing buildings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_290_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90655&sectionno=290&orderno=290&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_290_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in pulling down, repairing or constructing any building, knowingly or negligently omits to take`
  line `such measures with that building as is sufficient to guard against any probable danger to human life from`
  line `the fall of that building, or of any part thereof, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_291:
  sectionId (90656)
  sectionNo (291)
  orderNo 291
  title `Negligent conduct with respect to animal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_291_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90656&sectionno=291&orderno=291&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly or negligently omits to take`
  line `such measures with any animal in his possession as is sufficient to guard against any probable danger to`
  line `human life, or any probable danger of grievous hurt from such animal, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  sectionId (90657)
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 292
  title `Punishment for public nuisance in cases not otherwise provided for.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90657&sectionno=292&orderno=292&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits a`
  line `public nuisance in any case not otherwise punishable by this Sanhita shall be punished with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_293:
  sectionId (90658)
  sectionNo (293)
  orderNo 293
  title `Continuance of nuisance after injunction to discontinue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_293_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90658&sectionno=293&orderno=293&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_293_content:
  string
  line `Whoever repeats or continues a`
  line `public nuisance, having been enjoined by any public servant who has lawful authority to issue such`
  line `injunction not to repeat or continue such nuisance, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_294:
  sectionId (90659)
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 294
  title `Sale, etc., of obscene books, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90659&sectionno=294&orderno=294&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of sub-section (2), a book, pamphlet,`
  line `paper, writing, drawing, painting, representation, figure or any other object, including display of any`
  line `content in electronic form shall be deemed to be obscene if it is lascivious or appeals to the prurient`
  line `interest or if its effect, or (where it comprises two or more distinct items) the effect of any one of its`
  line `items, is, if taken as a whole, such as to tend to deprave and corrupt persons who are likely, having regard`
  line `to all relevant circumstances, to read, see or hear the matter contained or embodied in it.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever—`
  line
  line `(a) sells, lets to hire, distributes, publicly exhibits or in any manner puts into circulation, or for`
  line `purposes of sale, hire, distribution, public exhibition or circulation, makes, produces or has in his`
  line `possession any obscene book, pamphlet, paper, drawing, painting, representation or figure or any`
  line `other obscene object whatsoever in whatever manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) imports, exports or conveys any obscene object for any of the purposes aforesaid, or knowing`
  line `or having reason to believe that such object will be sold, let to hire, distributed or publicly exhibited`
  line `or in any manner put into circulation; or`
  line
  line `(c) takes part in or receives profits from any business in the course of which he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe that any such obscene objects are, for any of the purposes aforesaid, made`
  line `produced, purchased, kept, imported, exported, conveyed, publicly exhibited or in any manner put`
  line `into circulation; or`
  line
  line `(d) advertises or makes known by any means whatsoever that any person is engaged or is ready`
  line `to engage in any act which is an offence under this section, or that any such obscene object can be`
  line `procured from or through any person; or`
  line
  line `(e) offers or attempts to do any act which is an offence under this section,`
  line
  line `shall be punished on first conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, and with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, and, in the event of a`
  line `second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years, and also with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Exception.—This section does not extend to—`
  line
  line `(a) any book, pamphlet, paper, writing, drawing, painting, representation or figure—`
  line
  line `(i) the publication of which is proved to be justified as being for the public good on the ground`
  line `that such book, pamphlet, paper, writing, drawing, painting, representation or figure is in the interest`
  line `of science, literature, art or learning or other objects of general concern; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is kept or used bona fide for religious purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) any representation sculptured, engraved, painted or otherwise represented on or in—`
  line
  line `(i) any ancient monument within the meaning of the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological`
  line `Sites and Remains Act, 1958 (24 of 1958); or`
  line
  line `(ii) any temple, or on any car used for the conveyance of idols, or kept or used for any religious`
  line purpose.
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  sectionId (90660)
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 295
  title `Sale, etc., of obscene objects to child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90660&sectionno=295&orderno=295&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line `Whoever sells, lets to hire, distributes, exhibits or`
  line `circulates to any child any such obscene object as is referred to in section 294, or offers or attempts so to`
  line `do, shall be punished on first conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, and with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, and, in the event of a`
  line `second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years, and also with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_296:
  sectionId (90661)
  sectionNo (296)
  orderNo 296
  title `Obscene acts and songs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_296_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90661&sectionno=296&orderno=296&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, to the annoyance of others,—`
  line
  line `(a) does any obscene act in any public place; or`
  line
  line `(b) sings, recites or utters any obscene song, ballad or words, in or near any public place,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three months,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  sectionId (90662)
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 297
  title `Keeping lottery office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90662&sectionno=297&orderno=297&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever keeps any office or place for the purpose of drawing any`
  line `lottery not being a State lottery or a lottery authorised by the State Government, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever publishes any proposal to pay any sum, or to deliver any goods, or to do or forbear from`
  line `doing anything for the benefit of any person, on any event or contingency relative or applicable to the`
  line `drawing of any ticket, lot, number or figure in any such lottery, shall be punished with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (90663)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 298
  title `Injuring or defiling place of worship with intent to insult religion of any class.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90663&sectionno=298&orderno=298&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `destroys, damages or defiles any place of worship, or any object held sacred by any class of persons with`
  line `the intention of thereby insulting the religion of any class of persons or with the knowledge that any class`
  line `of persons is likely to consider such destruction, damage or defilement as an insult to their religion, shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (90756)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 299
  title `Deliberate and malicious acts, intended to outrage religious feelings of any class by insulting its religion or religious beliefs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90756&sectionno=299&orderno=299&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with deliberate and malicious intention of`
  line `outraging the religious feelings of any class of citizens of India, by words, either spoken or written, or by`
  line `signs or by visible representations or through electronic means or otherwise, insults or attempts to insult`
  line `the religion or the religious beliefs of that class, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (90665)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 300
  title `Disturbing religious assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90665&sectionno=300&orderno=300&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `Whoever voluntarily causes disturbance to any assembly`
  line `lawfully engaged in the performance of religious worship, or religious ceremonies, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (90666)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 301
  title `Trespassing on burial places, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90666&sectionno=301&orderno=301&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with the intention of wounding the feelings of`
  line `any person, or of insulting the religion of any person, or with the knowledge that the feelings of any`
  line `person are likely to be wounded, or that the religion of any person is likely to be insulted thereby,`
  line `commits any trespass in any place of worship or on any place of sepulchre, or any place set apart for the`
  line `performance of funeral rites or as a depository for the remains of the dead, or offers any indignity to any`
  line `human corpse, or causes disturbance to any persons assembled for the performance of funeral`
  line `ceremonies, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (90667)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 302
  title `Uttering words, etc., with deliberate intent to wound religious feelings of any person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90667&sectionno=302&orderno=302&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with the deliberate intention of wounding the religious feelings of any person, utters any word`
  line `or makes any sound in the hearing of that person or makes any gesture in the sight of that person or`
  line `places any object in the sight of that person, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (90668)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 303
  title Theft.
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90668&sectionno=303&orderno=303&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, intending to take dishonestly any movable property out of the possession`
  line `of any person without that person’s consent, moves that property in order to such taking, is said to`
  line `commit theft.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A thing so long as it is attached to the earth, not being movable property, is not the`
  line `subject of theft; but it becomes capable of being the subject of theft as soon as it is severed from the`
  line earth.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—A moving effected by the same act which affects the severance may be a theft.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.—A person is said to cause a thing to move by removing an obstacle which prevented`
  line `it from moving or by separating it from any other thing, as well as by actually moving it.`
  line
  line `Explanation 4.—A person, who by any means causes an animal to move, is said to move that animal,`
  line `and to move everything which, in consequence of the motion so caused, is moved by that animal.`
  line
  line `Explanation 5.—The consent mentioned in this section may be express or implied, and may be given`
  line `either by the person in possession, or by any person having for that purpose authority either express or`
  line implied.
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A cuts down a tree on Z’s ground, with the intention of dishonestly taking the tree out of Z’s`
  line `possession without Z’s consent. Here, as soon as A has severed the tree in order to such taking, he has`
  line `committed theft.`
  line
  line `(b) A puts a bait for dogs in his pocket, and thus induces Z’s dog to follow it. Here, if A’s intention`
  line `be dishonestly to take the dog out of Z’s possession without Z’s consent. A has committed theft as soon`
  line `as Z’s dog has begun to follow A.`
  line
  line `(c) A meets a bullock carrying a box of treasure. He drives the bullock in a certain direction, in order`
  line `that he may dishonestly take the treasure. As soon as the bullock begins to move, A has committed theft`
  line `of the treasure.`
  line
  line `(d) A being Z’s servant, and entrusted by Z with the care of Z’s plate, dishonestly runs away with the`
  line `plate, without Z’s consent. A has committed theft.`
  line
  line `(e) Z, going on a journey, entrusts his plate to A, the keeper of a warehouse, till Z shall return. A`
  line `carries the plate to a goldsmith and sells it. Here the plate was not in Z’s possession. It could not therefore`
  line `be taken out of Z’s possession, and A has not committed theft, though he may have committed criminal`
  line `breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(f) A finds a ring belonging to Z on a table in the house which Z occupies. Here the ring is in Z’s`
  line `possession, and if A dishonestly removes it, A commits theft.`
  line
  line `(g) A finds a ring lying on the highroad, not in the possession of any person. A, by taking it, commits`
  line `no theft, though he may commit criminal misappropriation of property.`
  line
  line `(h) A sees a ring belonging to Z lying on a table in Z’s house. Not venturing to misappropriate the`
  line `ring immediately for fear of search and detection, A hides the ring in a place where it is highly`
  line `improbable that it will ever be found by Z, with the intention of taking the ring from the hiding place and`
  line `selling it when the loss is forgotten. Here A, at the time of first moving the ring, commits theft.`
  line
  line `(i) A delivers his watch to Z, a jeweler, to be regulated. Z carries it to his shop. A, not owing to the`
  line `jeweler any debt for which the jeweler might lawfully detain the watch as a security, enters the shop`
  line `openly, takes his watch by force out of Z’s hand, and carries it away. Here A, though he may have`
  line `committed criminal trespass and assault, has not committed theft, in as much as what he did was not done`
  line dishonestly.
  line
  line `(j) If A owes money to Z for repairing the watch, and if Z retains the watch lawfully as a security for`
  line `the debt, and A takes the watch out of Z’s possession, with the intention of depriving Z of the property as`
  line `a security for his debt, he commits theft, in as much as he takes it dishonestly.`
  line
  line `(k) Again, if A, having pawned his watch to Z, takes it out of Z’s possession without Z’s consent, not`
  line `having paid what he borrowed on the watch, he commits theft, though the watch is his own property in as`
  line `much as he takes it dishonestly.`
  line
  line `(l) A takes an article belonging to Z out of Z’s possession without Z’s consent, with the intention of`
  line `keeping it until he obtains money from Z as a reward for its restoration. Here A takes dishonestly; A has`
  line `therefore committed theft.`
  line
  line `(m) A, being on friendly terms with Z, goes into Z’s library in Z’s absence, and takes away a book`
  line `without Z’s express consent for the purpose merely of reading it, and with the intention of returning it.`
  line `Here, it is probable that A may have conceived that he had Z’s implied consent to use Z’s book. If this`
  line `was A’s impression, A has not committed theft.`
  line
  line `(n) A asks charity from Z’s wife. She gives A money, food and clothes, which A knows to belong to`
  line `Z her husband. Here it is probable that A may conceive that Z’s wife is authorised to give away alms. If`
  line `this was A’s impression, A has not committed theft.`
  line
  line `(o) A is the paramour of Z’s wife. She gives a valuable property, which A knows to belong to her`
  line `husband Z, and to be such property as she has no authority from Z to give. If A takes the property`
  line `dishonestly, he commits theft.`
  line
  line `(p) A, in good faith, believing property belonging to Z to be A’s own property, takes that property out`
  line `of Z’s possession. Here, as A does not take dishonestly, he does not commit theft.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits theft shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both and in case of second or subsequent`
  line `conviction of any person under this section, he shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to five years and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases of theft where the value of the stolen property is less than five thousand rupees,`
  line `and a person is convicted for the first time, shall upon return of the value of property or restoration of the`
  line `stolen property, shall be punished with community service.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_304:
  sectionId (90669)
  sectionNo (304)
  orderNo 304
  title Snatching.
  content obj_root_law_sections_304_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90669&sectionno=304&orderno=304&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line `(1) Theft is snatching if, in order to commit theft, the offender suddenly or quickly`
  line `or forcibly seizes or secures or grabs or takes away from any person or from his possession any movable`
  line property.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits snatching, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_305:
  sectionId (90670)
  sectionNo (305)
  orderNo 305
  title `Theft in a dwelling house, or means of transportation or place of worship, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_305_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90670&sectionno=305&orderno=305&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `commits theft—`
  line
  line `(a) in any building, tent or vessel used as a human dwelling or used for the custody of property;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) of any means of transport used for the transport of goods or passengers; or`
  line
  line `(c) of any article or goods from any means of transport used for the transport of goods or`
  line `passengers; or`
  line
  line `(d) of idol or icon in any place of worship; or`
  line
  line `(e) of any property of the Government or of a local authority,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_306:
  sectionId (90671)
  sectionNo (306)
  orderNo 306
  title `Theft by clerk or servant of property in possession of master.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_306_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90671&sectionno=306&orderno=306&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a clerk or`
  line `servant, or being employed in the capacity of a clerk or servant, commits theft in respect of any property`
  line `in the possession of his master or employer, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_307:
  sectionId (90757)
  sectionNo (307)
  orderNo 307
  title `Theft after preparation made for causing death, hurt or restraint in order to committing of theft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_307_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90757&sectionno=307&orderno=307&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_307_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits theft, having made preparation for causing death, or hurt, or restraint, or`
  line `fear of death, or of hurt, or of restraint, to any person, in order to the committing of such theft, or in order`
  line `to the effecting of his escape after the committing of such theft, or in order to the retaining of property`
  line `taken by such theft, shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A commits theft on property in Z’s possession; and while committing this theft, he has a loaded`
  line `pistol under his garment, having provided this pistol for the purpose of hurting Z in case Z should resist.`
  line `A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A picks Z’s pocket, having posted several of his companions near him, in order that they may`
  line `restrain Z, if Z should perceive what is passing and should resist, or should attempt to apprehend A. A`
  line `has committed the offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_308:
  sectionId (90673)
  sectionNo (308)
  orderNo 308
  title Extortion.
  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90673&sectionno=308&orderno=308&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever intentionally puts any person in fear of any injury to that person, or to`
  line `any other, and thereby dishonestly induces the person so put in fear to deliver to any person any property,`
  line `or valuable security or anything signed or sealed which may be converted into a valuable security,`
  line `commits extortion.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A threatens to publish a defamatory libel concerning Z unless Z gives him money. He thus`
  line `induces Z to give him money. A has committed extortion.`
  line
  line `(b) A threatens Z that he will keep Z’s child in wrongful confinement, unless Z will sign and deliver`
  line `to A a promissory note binding Z to pay certain monies to A. Z signs and delivers the note. A has`
  line `committed extortion.`
  line
  line `(c) A threatens to send club-men to plough up Z’s field unless Z will sign and deliver to B a bond`
  line `binding Z under a penalty to deliver certain produce to B, and thereby induces Z to sign and deliver the`
  line `bond. A has committed extortion.`
  line
  line `(d) A, by putting Z in fear of grievous hurt, dishonestly induces Z to sign or affix his seal to a blank`
  line `paper and deliver it to A. Z signs and delivers the paper to A. Here, as the paper so signed may be`
  line `converted into a valuable security. A has committed extortion.`
  line
  line `(e) A threatens Z by sending a message through an electronic device that "Your child is in my`
  line `possession, and will be put to death unless you send me one lakh rupees." A thus induces Z to give him`
  line `money. A has committed extortion.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits extortion shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, in order to the committing of extortion, puts any person in fear, or attempts to put any`
  line `person in fear, of any injury, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever, in order to the committing of extortion, puts or attempts to put any person in fear of`
  line `death or of grievous hurt to that person or to any other, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever commits extortion by putting any person in fear of death or of grievous hurt to that`
  line `person or to any other, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever, in order to the committing of extortion, puts or attempts to put any person in fear of an`
  line `accusation, against that person or any other, of having committed, or attempted to commit, an offence`
  line `punishable with death or with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to ten years, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(7) Whoever commits extortion by putting any person in fear of an accusation against that person or`
  line `any other, of having committed or attempted to commit any offence punishable with death, or with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, or of having`
  line `attempted to induce any other person to commit such offence, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  sectionId (90674)
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 309
  title Robbery.
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90674&sectionno=309&orderno=309&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all robbery there is either theft or extortion.`
  line
  line `(2) Theft is robbery if, in order to the committing of the theft, or in committing the theft, or in`
  line `carrying away or attempting to carry away property obtained by the theft, the offender, for that end`
  line `voluntarily causes or attempts to cause to any person death or hurt or wrongful restraint, or fear of instant`
  line `death or of instant hurt, or of instant wrongful restraint.`
  line
  line `(3) Extortion is robbery if the offender, at the time of committing the extortion, is in the presence of`
  line `the person put in fear, and commits the extortion by putting that person in fear of instant death, of instant`
  line `hurt, or of instant wrongful restraint to that person or to some other person, and, by so putting in fear,`
  line `induces the person so put in fear then and there to deliver up the thing extorted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The offender is said to be present if he is sufficiently near to put the other person in`
  line `fear of instant death, of instant hurt, or of instant wrongful restraint.`
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A holds Z down, and fraudulently takes Z’s money and jewels from Z’s clothes, without Z’s`
  line `consent. Here A has committed theft, and, in order to the committing of that theft, has voluntarily caused`
  line `wrongful restraint to Z. A has therefore committed robbery.`
  line
  line `(b) A meets Z on the high road, shows a pistol, and demands Z’s purse. Z, in consequence, surrenders`
  line `his purse. Here A has extorted the purse from Z by putting him in fear of instant hurt, and being at the`
  line `time of committing the extortion in his presence. A has therefore committed robbery.`
  line
  line `(c) A meets Z and Z’s child on the high road. A takes the child, and threatens to fling it down a`
  line `precipice, unless Z delivers his purse. Z, in consequence, delivers his purse. Here A has extorted the`
  line `purse from Z, by causing Z to be in fear of instant hurt to the child who is there present. A has therefore`
  line `committed robbery on Z.`
  line
  line `(d) A obtains property from Z by saying—"Your child is in the hands of my gang, and will be put to`
  line `death unless you send us ten thousand rupees". This is extortion, and punishable as such; but it is not`
  line `robbery, unless Z is put in fear of the instant death of his child.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever commits robbery shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine; and, if the robbery be committed on the highway`
  line `between sunset and sunrise, the imprisonment may be extended to fourteen years.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever attempts to commit robbery shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person, in committing or in attempting to commit robbery, voluntarily causes hurt, such`
  line `person, and any other person jointly concerned in committing or attempting to commit such robbery, shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_310:
  sectionId (90675)
  sectionNo (310)
  orderNo 310
  title Dacoity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_310_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90675&sectionno=310&orderno=310&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_310_content:
  string
  line `(1) When five or more persons conjointly commit or attempt to commit a robbery, or`
  line `where the whole number of persons conjointly committing or attempting to commit a robbery, and`
  line `persons present and aiding such commission or attempt, amount to five or more, every person so`
  line `committing, attempting or aiding, is said to commit dacoity.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits dacoity shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) If any one of five or more persons, who are conjointly committing dacoity, commits murder in so`
  line `committing dacoity, every one of those persons shall be punished with death, or imprisonment for life, or`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever makes any preparation for committing dacoity, shall be punished with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever is one of five or more persons assembled for the purpose of committing dacoity, shall be`
  line `punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever belongs to a gang of persons associated for the purpose of habitually committing`
  line `dacoity, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_311:
  sectionId (90676)
  sectionNo (311)
  orderNo 311
  title `Robbery, or dacoity, with attempt to cause death or grievous hurt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90676&sectionno=311&orderno=311&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line `If, at the time of`
  line `committing robbery or dacoity, the offender uses any deadly weapon, or causes grievous hurt to any`
  line `person, or attempts to cause death or grievous hurt to any person, the imprisonment with which such`
  line `offender shall be punished shall not be less than seven years.`
obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_312:
  sectionId (90677)
  sectionNo (312)
  orderNo 312
  title `Attempt to commit robbery or dacoity when armed with deadly weapon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_312_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90677&sectionno=312&orderno=312&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line `If, at the time of`
  line `attempting to commit robbery or dacoity, the offender is armed with any deadly weapon, the`
  line `imprisonment with which such offender shall be punished shall not be less than seven years.`
obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_313:
  sectionId (90678)
  sectionNo (313)
  orderNo 313
  title `Punishment for belonging to gang of robbers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_313_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90678&sectionno=313&orderno=313&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_313_content:
  string
  line `Whoever belongs to any gang of persons`
  line `associated in habitually committing theft or robbery, and not being a gang of dacoits, shall be punished`
  line `with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_314:
  sectionId (90679)
  sectionNo (314)
  orderNo 314
  title `Dishonest misappropriation of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_314_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90679&sectionno=314&orderno=314&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line `Whoever dishonestly misappropriates or converts`
  line `to his own use any movable property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to two years and with fine.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A takes property belonging to Z out of Z’s possession, in good faith believing at the time when he`
  line `takes it, that the property belongs to himself. A is not guilty of theft; but if A, after discovering his`
  line `mistake, dishonestly appropriates the property to his own use, he is guilty of an offence under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(b) A, being on friendly terms with Z, goes into Z’s library in Z’s absence, and takes away a book`
  line `without Z’s express consent. Here, if A was under the impression that he had Z’s implied consent to take`
  line `the book for the purpose of reading it, A has not committed theft. But, if A afterwards sells the book for`
  line `his own benefit, he is guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(c) A and B, being, joint owners of a horse. A takes the horse out of B’s possession, intending to use`
  line `it. Here, as A has a right to use the horse, he does not dishonestly misappropriate it. But, if A sells the`
  line `horse and appropriates the whole proceeds to his own use, he is guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A dishonest misappropriation for a time only is a misappropriation within the`
  line `meaning of this section.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A finds a Government promissory note belonging to Z, bearing a blank endorsement. A, knowing that`
  line `the note belongs to Z, pledges it with a banker as a security for a loan, intending at a future time to restore`
  line `it to Z. A has committed an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—A person who finds property not in the possession of any other person, and takes`
  line `such property for the purpose of protecting it for, or of restoring it to, the owner, does not take or`
  line `misappropriate it dishonestly, and is not guilty of an offence; but he is guilty of the offence above`
  line `defined, if he appropriates it to his own use, when he knows or has the means of discovering the owner,`
  line `or before he has used reasonable means to discover and give notice to the owner and has kept the`
  line `property a reasonable time to enable the owner to claim it.`
  line
  line `What are reasonable means or what is a reasonable time in such a case, is a question of fact.`
  line
  line `It is not necessary that the finder should know who is the owner of the property, or that any particular`
  line `person is the owner of it; it is sufficient if, at the time of appropriating it, he does not believe it to be his`
  line `own property, or in good faith believe that the real owner cannot be found.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A finds a rupee on the high road, not knowing to whom the rupee belongs, A picks up the rupee.`
  line `Here A has not committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A finds a letter on the road, containing a bank-note. From the direction and contents of the letter`
  line `he learns to whom the note belongs. He appropriates the note. He is guilty of an offence under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(c) A finds a cheque payable to bearer. He can form no conjecture as to the person who has lost the`
  line `cheque. But the name of the person, who has drawn the cheque, appears. A knows that this person can`
  line `direct him to the person in whose favour the cheque was drawn. A appropriates the cheque without`
  line `attempting to discover the owner. He is guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(d) A sees Z drop his purse with money in it. A picks up the purse with the intention of restoring it`
  line `to Z, but afterwards appropriates it to his own use. A has committed an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(e) A finds a purse with money, not knowing to whom it belongs; he afterwards discovers that it`
  line `belongs to Z, and appropriates it to his own use. A is guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(f) A finds a valuable ring, not knowing to whom it belongs. A sells it immediately without`
  line `attempting to discover the owner. A is guilty of an offence under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_315:
  sectionId (90758)
  sectionNo (315)
  orderNo 315
  title `Dishonest misappropriation of property possessed by deceased person at the time of his death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_315_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90758&sectionno=315&orderno=315&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line `Whoever dishonestly misappropriates or converts to his own use any property, knowing that`
  line `such property was in the possession of a deceased person at the time of that person’s decease, and has not`
  line `since been in the possession of any person legally entitled to such possession, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine, and if the offender at the time of such person’s decease was employed by him as a clerk or servant,`
  line `the imprisonment may extend to seven years.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `Z dies in possession of furniture and money. His servant A, before the money comes into the`
  line `possession of any person entitled to such possession, dishonestly misappropriates it. A has committed the`
  line `offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  sectionId (90681)
  sectionNo (316)
  orderNo 316
  title `Criminal breach of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_316_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90681&sectionno=316&orderno=316&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, being in any manner entrusted with property, or with`
  line `any dominion over property, dishonestly misappropriates or converts to his own use that property, or`
  line `dishonestly uses or disposes of that property in violation of any direction of law prescribing the mode in`
  line `which such trust is to be discharged, or of any legal contract, express or implied, which he has made`
  line `touching the discharge of such trust, or wilfully suffers any other person so to do, commits criminal`
  line `breach of trust.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A person, being an employer of an establishment whether exempted under`
  line `section 17 of the Employees’ Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952) or`
  line `not who deducts the employee’s contribution from the wages payable to the employee for credit to a`
  line `Provident Fund or Family Pension Fund established by any law for the time being in force, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been entrusted with the amount of the contribution so deducted by him and if he makes`
  line `default in the payment of such contribution to the said Fund in violation of the said law, shall be deemed`
  line `to have dishonestly used the amount of the said contribution in violation of a direction of law as`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—A person, being an employer, who deducts the employees’ contribution from the`
  line `wages payable to the employee for credit to the Employees’ State Insurance Fund held and administered`
  line `by the Employees’ State Insurance Corporation established under the Employees’ State Insurance`
  line `Act, 1948 (34 of 1948) shall be deemed to have been entrusted with the amount of the contribution so`
  line `deducted by him and if he makes default in the payment of such contribution to the said Fund in violation`
  line `of the said Act, shall be deemed to have dishonestly used the amount of the said contribution in violation`
  line `of a direction of law as aforesaid.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, being executor to the will of a deceased person, dishonestly disobeys the law which directs`
  line `him to divide the effects according to the will, and appropriates them to his own use. A has committed`
  line `criminal breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(b) A is a warehouse-keeper Z going on a journey, entrusts his furniture to A, under a contract that it`
  line `shall be returned on payment of a stipulated sum for warehouse room. A dishonestly sells the goods. A`
  line `has committed criminal breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(c) A, residing in Kolkata, is agent for Z, residing at Delhi. There is an express or implied contract`
  line `between A and Z, that all sums remitted by Z to A shall be invested by A, according to Z’s direction. Z`
  line `remits one lakh of rupees to A, with directions to A to invest the same in Company’s paper. A dishonestly`
  line `disobeys the directions and employs the money in his own business. A has committed criminal breach of`
  line trust.
  line
  line `(d) But if A, in illustration (c), not dishonestly but in good faith, believing that it will be more for Z’s`
  line `advantage to hold shares in the Bank of Bengal, disobeys Z’s directions, and buys shares in the Bank of`
  line `Bengal, for Z, instead of buying Company’s paper, here, though Z should suffer loss, and should be`
  line `entitled to bring a civil action against A, on account of that loss, yet A, not having acted dishonestly, has`
  line `not committed criminal breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(e) A, a revenue-officer, is entrusted with public money and is either directed by law, or bound by a`
  line `contract, express or implied, with the Government, to pay into a certain treasury all the public money`
  line `which he holds. A dishonestly appropriates the money. A has committed criminal breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(f) A, a carrier, is entrusted by Z with property to be carried by land or by water. A dishonestly`
  line `misappropriates the property. A has committed criminal breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits criminal breach of trust shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, being entrusted with property as a carrier, wharfinger or warehouse-keeper, commits`
  line `criminal breach of trust in respect of such property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever, being a clerk or servant or employed as a clerk or servant, and being in any manner`
  line `entrusted in such capacity with property, or with any dominion over property, commits criminal breach of`
  line `trust in respect of that property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever, being in any manner entrusted with property, or with any dominion over property in his`
  line `capacity of a public servant or in the way of his business as a banker, merchant, factor, broker, attorney or`
  line `agent commits criminal breach of trust in respect of that property, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `for life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  sectionId (90682)
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 317
  title `Stolen property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90682&sectionno=317&orderno=317&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line `(1) Property, the possession whereof has been transferred by theft or`
  line `extortion or robbery or cheating, and property which has been criminally misappropriated or in respect of`
  line `which criminal breach of trust has been committed, is designated as stolen property, whether the transfer`
  line `has been made, or the misappropriation or breach of trust has been committed, within or without India,`
  line `but, if such property subsequently comes into the possession of a person legally entitled to the possession`
  line `thereof, it then ceases to be stolen property.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever dishonestly receives or retains any stolen property, knowing or having reason to believe`
  line `the same to be stolen property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever dishonestly receives or retains any stolen property, the possession whereof he knows or`
  line `has reason to believe to have been transferred by the commission of dacoity, or dishonestly receives from`
  line `a person, whom he knows or has reason to believe to belong or to have belonged to a gang of dacoits,`
  line `property which he knows or has reason to believe to have been stolen, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever habitually receives or deals in property which he knows or has reason to believe to be`
  line `stolen property, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever voluntarily assists in concealing or disposing of or making away with property which he`
  line `knows or has reason to believe to be stolen property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  sectionId (90683)
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 318
  title Cheating.
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90683&sectionno=318&orderno=318&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, by deceiving any person, fraudulently or dishonestly induces the`
  line `person so deceived to deliver any property to any person, or to consent that any person shall retain any`
  line `property, or intentionally induces the person so deceived to do or omit to do anything which he would not`
  line `do or omit if he were not so deceived, and which act or omission causes or is likely to cause damage or`
  line `harm to that person in body, mind, reputation or property, is said to cheat.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A dishonest concealment of facts is a deception within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A, by falsely pretending to be in the Civil Service, intentionally deceives Z, and thus dishonestly`
  line `induces Z to let him have on credit goods for which he does not mean to pay. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(b) A, by putting a counterfeit mark on an article, intentionally deceives Z into a belief that this`
  line `article was made by a certain celebrated manufacturer, and thus dishonestly induces Z to buy and pay for`
  line `the article. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(c) A, by exhibiting to Z a false sample of an article intentionally deceives Z into believing that the`
  line `article corresponds with the sample, and thereby dishonestly induces Z to buy and pay for the article. A`
  line cheats.
  line
  line `(d) A, by tendering in payment for an article a bill on a house with which A keeps no money, and by`
  line `which A expects that the bill will be dishonoured, intentionally deceives Z, and thereby dishonestly`
  line `induces Z to deliver the article, intending not to pay for it. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(e) A, by pledging as diamonds articles which he knows are not diamonds, intentionally deceives Z,`
  line `and thereby dishonestly induces Z to lend money. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(f) A intentionally deceives Z into a belief that A means to repay any money that Z may lend to him`
  line `and thereby dishonestly induces Z to lend him money, A not intending to repay it. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(g) A intentionally deceives Z into a belief that A means to deliver to Z a certain quantity of indigo`
  line `plant which he does not intend to deliver, and thereby dishonestly induces Z to advance money upon the`
  line `faith of such delivery. A cheats; but if A, at the time of obtaining the money, intends to deliver the indigo`
  line `plant, and afterwards breaks his contract and does not deliver it, he does not cheat, but is liable only to a`
  line `civil action for breach of contract.`
  line
  line `(h) A intentionally deceives Z into a belief that A has performed A’s part of a contract made with Z,`
  line `which he has not performed, and thereby dishonestly induces Z to pay money. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(i) A sells and conveys an estate to B. A, knowing that in consequence of such sale he has no right to`
  line `the property, sells or mortgages the same to Z, without disclosing the fact of the previous sale and`
  line `conveyance to B, and receives the purchase or mortgage money from Z. A cheats.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever cheats shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever cheats with the knowledge that he is likely thereby to cause wrongful loss to a person`
  line `whose interest in the transaction to which the cheating relates, he was bound, either by law, or by a legal`
  line `contract, to protect, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to five years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever cheats and thereby dishonestly induces the person deceived to deliver any property to`
  line `any person, or to make, alter or destroy the whole or any part of a valuable security, or anything which is`
  line `signed or sealed, and which is capable of being converted into a valuable security, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_319:
  sectionId (90684)
  sectionNo (319)
  orderNo 319
  title `Cheating by personation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_319_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90684&sectionno=319&orderno=319&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person is said to cheat by personation if he cheats by`
  line `pretending to be some other person, or by knowingly substituting one person for or another, or`
  line `representing that he or any other person is a person other than he or such other person really is.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The offence is committed whether the individual personated is a real or imaginary`
  line person.
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A cheats by pretending to be a certain rich banker of the same name. A cheats by personation.`
  line
  line `(b) A cheats by pretending to be B, a person who is deceased. A cheats by personation.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever cheats by personation shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_320:
  sectionId (90759)
  sectionNo (320)
  orderNo 320
  title `Dishonest or fraudulent removal or concealment of property to prevent distribution among creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90759&sectionno=320&orderno=320&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line `Whoever dishonestly or fraudulently removes, conceals or delivers to any person, or`
  line `transfers or causes to be transferred to any person, without adequate consideration, any property,`
  line `intending thereby to prevent, or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby prevent, the distribution of`
  line `that property according to law among his creditors or the creditors of any other person, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_321:
  sectionId (90686)
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 321
  title `Dishonestly or fraudulently preventing debt being available for creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90686&sectionno=321&orderno=321&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `dishonestly or fraudulently prevents any debt or demand due to himself or to any other person from being`
  line `made available according to law for payment of his debts or the debts of such other person, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  sectionId (90760)
  sectionNo (322)
  orderNo 322
  title `Dishonest or fraudulent execution of deed of transfer containing false statement of consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90760&sectionno=322&orderno=322&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line `Whoever dishonestly or fraudulently signs, executes or becomes a party to any deed or`
  line `instrument which purports to transfer or subject to any charge any property, or any interest therein, and`
  line `which contains any false statement relating to the consideration for such transfer or charge, or relating to`
  line `the person or persons for whose use or benefit it is really intended to operate, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_323:
  sectionId (90688)
  sectionNo (323)
  orderNo 323
  title `Dishonest or fraudulent removal or concealment of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90688&sectionno=323&orderno=323&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line `Whoever dishonestly or`
  line `fraudulently conceals or removes any property of himself or any other person, or dishonestly or`
  line `fraudulently assists in the concealment or removal thereof, or dishonestly releases any demand or claim`
  line `to which he is entitled, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  sectionId (90689)
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 324
  title Mischief.
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90689&sectionno=324&orderno=324&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever with intent to cause, or knowing that he is likely to cause, wrongful`
  line `loss or damage to the public or to any person, causes the destruction of any property, or any such change`
  line `in any property or in the situation thereof as destroys or diminishes its value or utility, or affects it`
  line `injuriously, commits mischief.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—It is not essential to the offence of mischief that the offender should intend to cause`
  line `loss or damage to the owner of the property injured or destroyed. It is sufficient if he intends to cause, or`
  line `knows that he is likely to cause, wrongful loss or damage to any person by injuring any property, whether`
  line `it belongs to that person or not.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—Mischief may be committed by an act affecting property belonging to the person`
  line `who commits the act, or to that person and others jointly.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A voluntarily burns a valuable security belonging to Z intending to cause wrongful loss to Z. A`
  line `has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(b) A introduces water into an ice-house belonging to Z and thus causes the ice to melt, intending`
  line `wrongful loss to Z. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(c) A voluntarily throws into a river a ring belonging to Z, with the intention of thereby causing`
  line `wrongful loss to Z. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(d) A, knowing that his effects are about to be taken in execution in order to satisfy a debt due from`
  line `him to Z, destroys those effects, with the intention of thereby preventing Z from obtaining satisfaction of`
  line `the debt, and of thus causing damage to Z. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(e) A having insured a ship, voluntarily causes the same to be cast away, with the intention of causing`
  line `damage to the underwriters. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(f) A causes a ship to be cast away, intending thereby to cause damage to Z who has lent money on`
  line `bottomry on the ship. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(g) A, having joint property with Z in a horse, shoots the horse, intending thereby to cause wrongful`
  line `loss to Z. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(h) A causes cattle to enter upon a field belonging to Z, intending to cause and knowing that he is`
  line `likely to cause damage to Z’s crop. A has committed mischief.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits mischief shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits mischief and thereby causes loss or damage to any property including the`
  line `property of Government or Local Authority shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever commits mischief and thereby causes loss or damage to the amount of twenty thousand`
  line `rupees and more but less than one lakh rupees shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever commits mischief and thereby causes loss or damage to the amount of one lakh rupees`
  line `or upwards, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever commits mischief, having made preparation for causing to any person death, or hurt, or`
  line `wrongful restraint, or fear of death, or of hurt, or of wrongful restraint, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_325:
  sectionId (90690)
  sectionNo (325)
  orderNo 325
  title `Mischief by killing or maiming animal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_325_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90690&sectionno=325&orderno=325&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits mischief by killing, poisoning,`
  line `maiming or rendering useless any animal shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (90691)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 326
  title `Mischief by injury, inundation, fire or explosive substance, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90691&sectionno=326&orderno=326&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits`
  line `mischief by,---`
  line
  line `(a) doing any act which causes, or which he knows to be likely to cause, a diminution of the supply`
  line `of water for agricultural purposes, or for food or drink for human beings or for animals which are`
  line `property, or for cleanliness or for carrying on any manufacture, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) doing any act which renders or which he knows to be likely to render any public road, bridge,`
  line `navigable river or navigable channel, natural or artificial, impassable or less safe for travelling or`
  line `conveying property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to five years, or with fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(c) doing any act which causes or which he knows to be likely to cause an inundation or an`
  line `obstruction to any public drainage attended with injury or damage, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(d) destroying or moving any sign or signal used for navigation of rail, aircraft or ship or other thing`
  line `placed as a guide for navigators, or by any act which renders any such sign or signal less useful as a guide`
  line `for navigators, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years, or with fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(e) destroying or moving any land-mark fixed by the authority of a public servant, or by any act`
  line `which renders such land-mark less useful as such, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(f) fire or any explosive substance intending to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby`
  line `cause, damage to any property including agricultural produce, shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(g) fire or any explosive substance, intending to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he will thereby`
  line `cause, the destruction of any building which is ordinarily used as a place of worship or as a human`
  line `dwelling or as a place for the custody of property, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (90761)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 327
  title `Mischief with intent to destroy or make unsafe a rail, aircraft, decked vessel or one of twenty tons burden.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90761&sectionno=327&orderno=327&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever commits mischief to any rail, aircraft, or a decked vessel or any`
  line `vessel of a burden of twenty tons or upwards, intending to destroy or render unsafe, or knowing it to be`
  line `likely that he will thereby destroy or render unsafe, that rail, aircraft or vessel, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits, or attempts to commit, by fire or any explosive substance, such mischief as is`
  line `described in sub-section (1), shall be punished with imprisonment for life or with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (90762)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 328
  title `Punishment for intentionally running vessel aground or ashore with intent to commit theft, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90762&sectionno=328&orderno=328&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line `Whoever intentionally runs any vessel aground or ashore, intending to commit theft of any`
  line `property contained therein or to dishonestly misappropriate any such property, or with intent that such`
  line `theft or misappropriation of property may be committed, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (90694)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 329
  title `Criminal trespass and house-trespass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90694&sectionno=329&orderno=329&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever enters into or upon property in the`
  line `possession of another with intent to commit an offence or to intimidate, insult or annoy any person in`
  line `possession of such property or having lawfully entered into or upon such property, unlawfully remains`
  line `there with intent thereby to intimidate, insult or annoy any such person or with intent to commit an`
  line `offence is said to commit criminal trespass.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits criminal trespass by entering into or remaining in any building, tent or vessel`
  line `used as a human dwelling or any building used as a place for worship, or as a place for the custody of`
  line `property, is said to commit house-trespass.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The introduction of any part of the criminal trespasser's body is entering sufficient to`
  line `constitute house-trespass.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits criminal trespass shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(4) Whoever commits house-trespass shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (90695)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 330
  title `House-trespass and hous-ebreaking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90695&sectionno=330&orderno=330&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever commits house-trespass having taken`
  line `precautions to conceal such house-trespass from some person who has a right to exclude or eject the`
  line `trespasser from the building, tent or vessel which is the subject of the trespass, is said to commit lurking`
  line house-trespass.
  line
  line `(2) A person is said to commit house-breaking who commits house-trespass if he effects his entrance`
  line `into the house or any part of it in any of the six ways hereinafter described; or if, being in the house or`
  line `any part of it for the purpose of committing an offence, or having committed an offence therein, he quits`
  line `the house or any part of it in any of the following ways, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) if he enters or quits through a passage made by himself, or by any abettor of the house-trespass, in`
  line `order to the committing of the house-trespass;`
  line
  line `(b) if he enters or quits through any passage not intended by any person, other than himself or an`
  line `abettor of the offence, for human entrance; or through any passage to which he has obtained access by`
  line `scaling or climbing over any wall or building;`
  line
  line `(c) if he enters or quits through any passage which he or any abettor of the house-trespass has`
  line `opened, in order to the committing of the house-trespass by any means by which that passage was not`
  line `intended by the occupier of the house to be opened;`
  line
  line `(d) if he enters or quits by opening any lock in order to the committing of the house-trespass, or in`
  line `order to the quitting of the house after a house-trespass;`
  line
  line `(e) if he effects his entrance or departure by using criminal force or committing an assault, or by`
  line `threatening any person with assault;`
  line
  line `(f) if he enters or quits by any passage which he knows to have been fastened against such entrance or`
  line `departure, and to have been unfastened by himself or by an abettor of the house-trespass.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- Any out-house or building occupied with a house, and between which and such house`
  line `there is an immediate internal communication, is part of the house within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A commits house-trespass by making a hole through the wall of Z’s house, and putting his hand`
  line `through the aperture. This is house-breaking.`
  line
  line `(b) A commits house-trespass by creeping into a ship at a port-hole between decks. This is`
  line house-breaking.
  line
  line `(c) A commits house-trespass by entering Z’s house through a window. This is house-breaking.`
  line
  line `(d) A commits house-trespass by entering Z’s house through the door, having opened a door which`
  line `was fastened. This is house-breaking.`
  line
  line `(e) A commits house-trespass by entering Z’s house through the door, having lifted a latch by putting`
  line `a wire through a hole in the door. This is house-breaking.`
  line
  line `(f) A finds the key of Z’s house door, which Z had lost, and commits house-trespass by entering Z’s`
  line `house, having opened the door with that key. This is house-breaking.`
  line
  line `(g) Z is standing in his doorway. A forces a passage by knocking Z down, and commits housetrespass by entering the house. This is house-breaking.`
  line
  line `(h) Z, the door-keeper of Y, is standing in Y’s doorway. A commits house-trespass by entering the`
  line `house, having deterred Z from opposing him by threatening to beat him. This is house-breaking.`
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (90696)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 331
  title `Punishment for house-trespass or house-breaking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90696&sectionno=331&orderno=331&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever commits lurking housetrespass or house-breaking, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits lurking house-trespass or house-breaking after sunset and before sunrise, shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits lurking house-trespass or house-breaking, in order to the committing of any`
  line `offence punishable with imprisonment, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine; and if the offence intended to be`
  line `committed is theft, the term of the imprisonment may be extended to ten years.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever commits lurking house-trespass or house-breaking after sunset and before sunrise, in`
  line `order to the committing of any offence punishable with imprisonment, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine; and, if the offence intended to be committed is theft, the term of the imprisonment may be extended`
  line `to fourteen years.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever commits lurking house-trespass, or house-breaking, having made preparation for`
  line `causing hurt to any person, or for assaulting any person, or for wrongfully restraining any person, or for`
  line `putting any person in fear of hurt or of assault or of wrongful restraint, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description or a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line
  line `(6) Whoever commits lurking house-trespass or house-breaking after sunset and before sunrise,`
  line `having made preparation for causing hurt to any person or for assaulting any person, or for wrongfully`
  line `restraining any person, or for putting any person in fear of hurt, or of assault, or of wrongful restraint,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to fourteen years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(7) Whoever, whilst committing lurking house-trespass or house-breaking, causes grievous hurt to`
  line `any person or attempts to cause death or grievous hurt to any person, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for life, or imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years,`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(8) If, at the time of the committing of lurking house-trespass or house-breaking after sunset and`
  line `before sunrise, any person guilty of such offence shall voluntarily cause or attempt to cause death or`
  line `grievous hurt to any person, every person jointly concerned in committing such lurking house-trespass or`
  line `house-breaking after sunset and before sunrise, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (90697)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 332
  title `House-trespass in order to commit offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90697&sectionno=332&orderno=332&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits house-trespass in order to the`
  line `committing of any offence---`
  line
  line `(a) punishable with death, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) punishable with imprisonment for life, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term not exceeding ten years, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(c) punishable with imprisonment, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to two years, and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the offence intended to be committed is theft, the term of the imprisonment may be`
  line `extended to seven years.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (90698)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 333
  title `House-trespass after preparation for hurt, assault or wrongful restraint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90698&sectionno=333&orderno=333&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `commits house-trespass, having made preparation for causing hurt to any person or for assaulting any`
  line `person, or for wrongfully restraining any person, or for putting any person in fear of hurt, or of assault, or`
  line `of wrongful restraint, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (90699)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 334
  title `Dishonestly breaking open receptacle containing property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90699&sectionno=334&orderno=334&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever dishonestly or`
  line `with intent to commit mischief, breaks open or unfastens any closed receptacle which contains or which`
  line `he believes to contain property, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being entrusted with any closed receptacle which contains or which he believes to`
  line `contain property, without having authority to open the same, dishonestly, or with intent to commit`
  line `mischief, breaks open or unfastens that receptacle, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (90700)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 335
  title `Making a false document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90700&sectionno=335&orderno=335&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `A person is said to make a false document or false electronic`
  line record---
  line
  line `(A) Who dishonestly or fraudulently---`
  line
  line `(i) makes, signs, seals or executes a document or part of a document;`
  line
  line `(ii) makes or transmits any electronic record or part of any electronic record;`
  line
  line `(iii) affixes any electronic signature on any electronic record;`
  line
  line `(iv) makes any mark denoting the execution of a document or the authenticity of the`
  line `electronic signature,`
  line
  line `with the intention of causing it to be believed that such document or part of document, electronic`
  line `record or electronic signature was made, signed, sealed, executed, transmitted or affixed by or by the`
  line `authority of a person by whom or by whose authority he knows that it was not made, signed, sealed,`
  line `executed or affixed; or`
  line
  line `(B) Who without lawful authority, dishonestly or fraudulently, by cancellation or otherwise,`
  line `alters a document or an electronic record in any material part thereof, after it has been made, executed`
  line `or affixed with electronic signature either by himself or by any other person, whether such person be`
  line `living or dead at the time of such alteration; or`
  line
  line `(C) Who dishonestly or fraudulently causes any person to sign, seal, execute or alter a document`
  line `or an electronic record or to affix his electronic signature on any electronic record knowing that such`
  line `person by reason of unsoundness of mind or intoxication cannot, or that by reason of deception`
  line `practised upon him, he does not know the contents of the document or electronic record or the nature`
  line `of the alteration.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A has a letter of credit upon B for rupees 10,000, written by Z. A, in order to defraud B, adds`
  line `cipher to the 10,000, and makes the sum 1,00,000 intending that it may be believed by B that Z so wrote`
  line `the letter. A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(b) A, without Z’s authority, affixes Z’s seal to a document purporting to be a conveyance of an`
  line `estate from Z to A, with the intention of selling the estate to B and thereby of obtaining from B the`
  line `purchase-money. A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(c) A picks up a cheque on a banker signed by B, payable to bearer, but without any sum having been`
  line `inserted in the cheque. A fraudulently fills up the cheque by inserting the sum of ten thousand rupees. A`
  line `commits forgery.`
  line
  line `(d) A leaves with B, his agent, a cheque on a banker, signed by A, without inserting the sum payable`
  line `and authorises B to fill up the cheque by inserting a sum not exceeding ten thousand rupees for the`
  line `purpose of making certain payments. B fraudulently fills up the cheque by inserting the sum of`
  line `twenty thousand rupees. B commits forgery.`
  line
  line `(e) A draws a bill of exchange on himself in the name of B without B’s authority, intending to`
  line `discount it as a genuine bill with a banker and intending to take up the bill on its maturity. Here, as A`
  line `draws the bill with intent to deceive the banker by leading him to suppose that he had the security of B,`
  line `and thereby to discount the bill, A is guilty of forgery.`
  line
  line `(f) Z’s will contains these words—"I direct that all my remaining property be equally divided`
  line `between A, B and C." A dishonestly scratches out B’s name, intending that it may be believed that the`
  line `whole was left to himself and C. A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(g) A endorses a Government promissory note and makes it payable to Z or his order by writing on`
  line `the bill the words "Pay to Z or his order" and signing the endorsement. B dishonestly erases the words`
  line `“Pay to Z or his order”, and thereby converts the special endorsement into a blank endorsement. B`
  line `commits forgery.`
  line
  line `(h) A sells and conveys an estate to Z. A afterwards, in order to defraud Z of his estate, executes a`
  line `conveyance of the same estate to B, dated six months earlier than the date of the conveyance to Z,`
  line `intending it to be believed that he had conveyed the estate to B before he conveyed it to Z. A has`
  line `committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(i) Z dictates his will to A. A intentionally writes down a different legatee from the legatee named`
  line `by Z, and by representing to Z that he has prepared the will according to his instructions, induces Z to`
  line `sign the will. A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(j) A writes a letter and signs it with B’s name without B’s authority, certifying that A is a man of`
  line `good character and in distressed circumstances from unforeseen misfortune, intending by means of such`
  line `letter to obtain alms from Z and other persons. Here, as A made a false document in order to induce Z to`
  line `part with property, A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(k) A without B’s authority writes a letter and signs it in B’s name certifying to A’s character,`
  line `intending thereby to obtain employment under Z. A has committed forgery in as much as he intended to`
  line `deceive Z by the forged certificate, and thereby to induce Z to enter into an express or implied contract`
  line `for service.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—A man’s signature of his own name may amount to forgery.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A signs his own name to a bill of exchange, intending that it may be believed that the bill was`
  line `drawn by another person of the same name. A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(b) A writes the word "accepted" on a piece of paper and signs it with Z’s name, in order that B may`
  line `afterwards write on the paper a bill of exchange drawn by B upon Z, and negotiate the bill as though it`
  line `had been accepted by Z. A is guilty of forgery; and if B, knowing the fact, draws the bill upon the paper`
  line `pursuant to A’s intention, B is also guilty of forgery.`
  line
  line `(c) A picks up a bill of exchange payable to the order of a different person of the same name. A`
  line `endorses the bill in his own name, intending to cause it to be believed that it was endorsed by the person`
  line `to whose order it was payable; here A has committed forgery.`
  line
  line `(d) A purchases an estate sold under execution of a decree against B. B, after the seizure of the estate,`
  line `in collusion with Z, executes a lease of the estate, to Z at a nominal rent and for a long period and dates`
  line `the lease six months prior to the seizure, with intent to defraud A, and to cause it to be believed that the`
  line `lease was granted before the seizure. B, though he executes the lease in his own name, commits forgery`
  line `by antedating it.`
  line
  line `(e) A, a trader, in anticipation of insolvency, lodges effects with B for A’s benefit, and with intent to`
  line `defraud his creditors; and in order to give a colour to the transaction, writes a promissory note binding`
  line `himself to pay to B a sum for value received, and antedates the note, intending that it may be believed to`
  line `have been made before A was on the point of insolvency. A has committed forgery under the first head of`
  line `the definition.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—The making of a false document in the name of a fictitious person, intending it to be`
  line `believed that the document was made by a real person, or in the name of a deceased person, intending it`
  line `to be believed that the document was made by the person in his lifetime, may amount to forgery.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A draws a bill of exchange upon a fictitious person, and fraudulently accepts the bill in the name of`
  line `such fictitious person with intent to negotiate it. A commits forgery.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.—For the purposes of this section, the expression "affixing electronic signature" shall`
  line `have the meaning assigned to it in clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (90701)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 336
  title Forgery.
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90701&sectionno=336&orderno=336&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever makes any false document or false electronic record or part of a`
  line `document or electronic record, with intent to cause damage or injury, to the public or to any person, or to`
  line `support any claim or title, or to cause any person to part with property, or to enter into any express or`
  line `implied contract, or with intent to commit fraud or that fraud may be committed, commits forgery.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits forgery shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits forgery, intending that the document or electronic record forged shall be used`
  line `for the purpose of cheating, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever commits forgery, intending that the document or electronic record forged shall harm the`
  line `reputation of any party, or knowing that it is likely to be used for that purpose, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (90702)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 337
  title `Forgery of record of Court or of public register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90702&sectionno=337&orderno=337&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `Whoever forges a document or an`
  line `electronic record, purporting to be a record or proceeding of or in a Court or an identity document issued`
  line `by Government including voter identity card or Aadhaar Card, or a register of birth, marriage or burial, or`
  line `a register kept by a public servant as such, or a certificate or document purporting to be made by a public`
  line `servant in his official capacity, or an authority to institute or defend a suit, or to take any proceedings`
  line `therein, or to confess judgment, or a power of attorney, shall be punished with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "register" includes any list, data or record of any`
  line `entries maintained in the electronic form as defined in clause (r) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the`
  line `Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (90703)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 338
  title `Forgery of valuable security, will, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90703&sectionno=338&orderno=338&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `Whoever forges a document which purports to be a`
  line `valuable security or a will, or an authority to adopt a son, or which purports to give authority to any`
  line `person to make or transfer any valuable security, or to receive the principal, interest or dividends thereon,`
  line `or to receive or deliver any money, movable property, or valuable security, or any document purporting`
  line `to be an acquittance or receipt acknowledging the payment of money, or an acquittance or receipt for the`
  line `delivery of any movable property or valuable security, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to ten years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (90763)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 339
  title `Having possession of document described in section 337 or section 338, knowing it to be forged and intending to use it as genuine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90763&sectionno=339&orderno=339&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `Whoever has in his possession any document or electronic`
  line `record, knowing the same to be forged and intending that the same shall fraudulently or dishonestly be`
  line `used as genuine, shall, if the document or electronic record is one of the description mentioned in section`
  line `337 of this Sanhita, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years, and shall also be liable to fine; and if the document is one of the description mentioned in`
  line `section 338, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either description, for`
  line `a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (90705)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 340
  title `Forged document or electronic record and using it as genuine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90705&sectionno=340&orderno=340&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `(1) A false document or`
  line `electronic record made wholly or in part by forgery is designated a forged document or electronic record.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever fraudulently or dishonestly uses as genuine any document or electronic record which he`
  line `knows or has reason to believe to be a forged document or electronic record, shall be punished in the`
  line `same manner as if he had forged such document or electronic record.`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (90764)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 341
  title `Making or possessing counterfeit seal, etc., with intent to commit forgery punishable under section 338.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90764&sectionno=341&orderno=341&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever makes or counterfeits any seal, plate or other instrument for making an`
  line `impression, intending that the same shall be used for the purpose of committing any forgery which would`
  line `be punishable under section 338 of this Sanhita, or, with such intent, has in his possession any such seal,`
  line `plate or other instrument, knowing the same to be counterfeit, shall be punished with imprisonment for`
  line `life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever makes or counterfeits any seal, plate or other instrument for making an impression,`
  line `intending that the same shall be used for the purpose of committing any forgery which would be`
  line `punishable under any section of this Chapter other than section 338, or, with such intent, has in his`
  line `possession any such seal, plate or other instrument, knowing the same to be counterfeit, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever possesses any seal, plate or other instrument knowing the same to be counterfeit, shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever fraudulently or dishonestly uses as genuine any seal, plate or other instrument knowing`
  line `or having reason to believe the same to be counterfeit, shall be punished in the same manner as if he had`
  line `made or counterfeited such seal, plate or other instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (90765)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 342
  title `Counterfeiting device or mark used for authenticating documents described in section 338, or possessing counterfeit marked material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90765&sectionno=342&orderno=342&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever counterfeits upon, or in the substance of,`
  line `any material, any device or mark used for the purpose of authenticating any document described in`
  line `section 338, intending that such device or mark shall be used for the purpose of giving the appearance of`
  line `authenticity to any document then forged or thereafter to be forged on such material, or who, with such`
  line `intent, has in his possession any material upon or in the substance of which any such device or mark has`
  line `been counterfeited, shall be punished with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment of either`
  line `description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever counterfeits upon, or in the substance of, any material, any device or mark used for the`
  line `purpose of authenticating any document or electronic record other than the documents described in`
  line `section 338, intending that such device or mark shall be used for the purpose of giving the appearance of`
  line `authenticity to any document then forged or thereafter to be forged on such material, or who with such`
  line `intent, has in his possession any material upon or in the substance of which any such device or mark has`
  line `been counterfeited, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (90708)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 343
  title `Fraudulent cancellation, destruction, etc., of will, authority to adopt, or valuable security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90708&sectionno=343&orderno=343&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fraudulently or dishonestly, or with intent to cause damage or injury to the public or`
  line `to any person, cancels, destroys or defaces, or attempts to cancel, destroy or deface, or secretes or`
  line `attempts to secrete any document which is or purports to be a will, or an authority to adopt a son, or any`
  line `valuable security, or commits mischief in respect of such document, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `for life, or with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (90709)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 344
  title `Falsification of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90709&sectionno=344&orderno=344&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a clerk, officer or servant, or employed or acting in`
  line `the capacity of a clerk, officer or servant, wilfully, and with intent to defraud, destroys, alters, mutilates`
  line `or falsifies any book, electronic record, paper, writing, valuable security or account which belongs to or is`
  line `in the possession of his employer, or has been received by him for or on behalf of his employer, or`
  line `wilfully, and with intent to defraud, makes or abets the making of any false entry in, or omits or alters or`
  line `abets the omission or alteration of any material particular from or in, any such book, electronic record,`
  line `paper, writing, valuable security or account, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for`
  line `a term which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—It shall be sufficient in any charge under this section to allege a general intent to`
  line `defraud without naming any particular person intended to be defrauded or specifying any particular sum`
  line `of money intended to be the subject of the fraud, or any particular day on which the offence was`
  line committed.
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (90710)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 345
  title `Property mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90710&sectionno=345&orderno=345&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `(1) A mark used for denoting that movable property belongs to a particular`
  line `person is called a property mark.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever marks any movable property or goods or any case, package or other receptacle`
  line `containing movable property or goods, or uses any case, package or other receptacle having any mark`
  line `thereon, in a manner reasonably calculated to cause it to be believed that the property or goods so`
  line `marked, or any property or goods contained in any such receptacle so marked, belong to a person to`
  line `whom they do not belong, is said to use a false property mark.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever uses any false property mark shall, unless he proves that he acted without intent to`
  line `defraud, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (90711)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 346
  title `Tampering with property mark with intent to cause injury.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90711&sectionno=346&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `Whoever removes, destroys,`
  line `defaces or adds to any property mark, intending or knowing it to be likely that he may thereby cause`
  line `injury to any person, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (90712)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 347
  title `Counterfeiting a property mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90712&sectionno=347&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever counterfeits any property mark used by any`
  line `other person shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to`
  line `two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever counterfeits any property mark used by a public servant, or any mark used by a public`
  line `servant to denote that any property has been manufactured by a particular person or at a particular time or`
  line `place, or that the property is of a particular quality or has passed through a particular office, or that it is`
  line `entitled to any exemption, or uses as genuine any such mark knowing the same to be counterfeit, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (90713)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 348
  title `Making or possession of any instrument for counterfeiting a property mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90713&sectionno=348&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `makes or has in his possession any die, plate or other instrument for the purpose of counterfeiting a`
  line `property mark, or has in his possession a property mark for the purpose of denoting that any goods belong`
  line `to a person to whom they do not belong, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (90714)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 349
  title `Selling goods marked with a counterfeit property mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90714&sectionno=349&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `Whoever sells, or exposes, or has`
  line `in possession for sale, any goods or things with a counterfeit property mark affixed to or impressed upon`
  line `the same or to or upon any case, package or other receptacle in which such goods are contained, shall,`
  line `unless he proves---`
  line
  line `(a) that, having taken all reasonable precautions against committing an offence against this section,`
  line `he had at the time of the commission of the alleged offence no reason to suspect the genuineness of the`
  line `mark; and`
  line
  line `(b) that, on demand made by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his power`
  line `with respect to the persons from whom he obtained such goods or things; or`
  line
  line `(c) that otherwise he had acted innocently,`
  line
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (90715)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 350
  title `Making a false mark upon any receptacle containing goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90715&sectionno=350&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever makes any false`
  line `mark upon any case, package or other receptacle containing goods, in a manner reasonably calculated to`
  line `cause any public servant or any other person to believe that such receptacle contains goods which it does`
  line `not contain or that it does not contain goods which it does contain, or that the goods contained in such`
  line `receptacle are of a nature or quality different from the real nature or quality thereof, shall, unless he`
  line `proves that he acted without intent to defraud, be punished with imprisonment of either description for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever makes use of any false mark in any manner prohibited under sub-section (1) shall,`
  line `unless he proves that he acted without intent to defraud,`
  line
  line `be punished as if he had committed the offence under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (90716)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 351
  title `Criminal intimidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90716&sectionno=351&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever threatens another by any means, with any injury to his`
  line `person, reputation or property, or to the person or reputation of any one in whom that person is interested,`
  line `with intent to cause alarm to that person, or to cause that person to do any act which he is not legally`
  line `bound to do, or to omit to do any act which that person is legally entitled to do, as the means of avoiding`
  line `the execution of such threat, commits criminal intimidation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---A threat to injure the reputation of any deceased person in whom the person`
  line `threatened is interested, is within this section.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A, for the purpose of inducing B to resist from prosecuting a civil suit, threatens to burn Bs house. A`
  line `is guilty of criminal intimidation.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits the offence of criminal intimidation shall be punished with imprisonment of`
  line `either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits the offence of criminal intimidation by threatening to cause death or grievous`
  line `hurt, or to cause the destruction of any property by fire, or to cause an offence punishable with death or`
  line `imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, or to impute`
  line `unchastity to a woman, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever commits the offence of criminal intimidation by an anonymous communication, or`
  line `having taken precaution to conceal the name or abode of the person from whom the threat comes, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, in addition`
  line `to the punishment provided for the offence under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (90717)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 352
  title `Intentional insult with intent to provoke breach of peace.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90717&sectionno=352&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line `Whoever intentionally insults in`
  line `any manner, and thereby gives provocation to any person, intending or knowing it to be likely that such`
  line `provocation will cause him to break the public peace, or to commit any other offence, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (90718)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 353
  title `Statements conducing to public mischief.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90718&sectionno=353&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever makes, publishes or circulates any`
  line `statement, false information, rumour, or report, including through electronic means---`
  line
  line `(a) with intent to cause, or which is likely to cause, any officer, soldier, sailor or airman in the`
  line `Army, Navy or Air Force of India to mutiny or otherwise disregard or fail in his duty as such; or`
  line
  line `(b) with intent to cause, or which is likely to cause, fear or alarm to the public, or to any section`
  line `of the public whereby any person may be induced to commit an offence against the State or against`
  line `the public tranquillity; or`
  line
  line `(c) with intent to incite, or which is likely to incite, any class or community of persons to commit`
  line `any offence against any other class or community,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever makes, publishes or circulates any statement or report containing false information,`
  line `rumour or alarming news, including through electronic means, with intent to create or promote, or which`
  line `is likely to create or promote, on grounds of religion, race, place of birth, residence, language, caste or`
  line `community or any other ground whatsoever, feelings of enmity, hatred or ill will between different`
  line `religious, racial, language or regional groups or castes or communities, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever commits an offence specified in sub-section (2) in any place of worship or in any`
  line `assembly engaged in the performance of religious worship or religious ceremonies, shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment which may extend to five years and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Exception.---It does not amount to an offence, within the meaning of this section, when the person`
  line `making, publishing or circulating any such statement, false information, rumour or report, has reasonable`
  line `grounds for believing that such statement, false information, rumour or report is true and makes,`
  line `publishes or circulates it in good faith and without any such intent as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (90766)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 354
  title `Act caused by inducing person to believe that he will be rendered an object of Divine displeasure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90766&sectionno=354&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `Whoever voluntarily causes or attempts to cause any person to do anything which that`
  line `person is not legally bound to do, or to omit to do anything which he is legally entitled to do, by inducing`
  line `or attempting to induce that person to believe that he or any person in whom he is interested will become`
  line `or will be rendered by some act of the offender an object of Divine displeasure if he does not do the thing`
  line `which it is the object of the offender to cause him to do, or if he does the thing which it is the object of`
  line `the offender to cause him to omit, shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A sits dharna at Z’s door with the intention of causing it to be believed that, by so sitting, he`
  line `renders Z an object of Divine displeasure. A has committed the offence defined in this section.`
  line
  line `(b) A threatens Z that, unless Z performs a certain act, A will kill one of A’s own children, under`
  line `such circumstances that the killing would be believed to render Z an object of Divine displeasure. A has`
  line `committed the offence defined in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (90720)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 355
  title `Misconduct in public by a drunken person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90720&sectionno=355&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in a state of intoxication, appears in`
  line `any public place, or in any place which it is a trespass in him to enter, and there conducts himself in such`
  line `a manner as to cause annoyance to any person, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to twenty-four hours, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with`
  line `both or with community service.`
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (90721)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 356
  title Defamation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90721&sectionno=356&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, by words either spoken or intended to be read, or by signs or by`
  line `visible representations, makes or publishes in any manner, any imputation concerning any person`
  line `intending to harm, or knowing or having reason to believe that such imputation will harm, the reputation`
  line `of such person, is said, except in the cases hereinafter excepted, to defame that person.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---It may amount to defamation to impute anything to a deceased person, if the`
  line `imputation would harm the reputation of that person if living, and is intended to be hurtful to the feelings`
  line `of his family or other near relatives.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---It may amount to defamation to make an imputation concerning a company or an`
  line `association or collection of persons as such.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.---An imputation in the form of an alternative or expressed ironically, may amount to`
  line defamation.
  line
  line `Explanation 4.---No imputation is said to harm a person’s reputation, unless that imputation directly`
  line `or indirectly, in the estimation of others, lowers the moral or intellectual character of that person, or`
  line `lowers the character of that person in respect of his caste or of his calling, or lowers the credit of that`
  line `person, or causes it to be believed that the body of that person is in a loathsome state, or in a state`
  line `generally considered as disgraceful.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A says---"Z is an honest man; he never stole B’s watch"; intending to cause it to be believed that`
  line `Z did steal B’s watch. This is defamation, unless it falls within one of the exceptions.`
  line
  line `(b) A is asked who stole B’s watch. A points to Z, intending to cause it to be believed that Z stole B’s`
  line `watch. This is defamation, unless it falls within one of the exceptions.`
  line
  line `(c) A draws a picture of Z running away with B’s watch, intending it to be believed that Z stole B’s`
  line `watch. This is defamation, unless it falls within one of the exceptions.`
  line
  line `Exception 1.---It is not defamation to impute anything which is true concerning any person, if it be`
  line `for the public good that the imputation should be made or published. Whether or not it is for the public`
  line `good is a question of fact.`
  line
  line `Exception 2.---It is not defamation to express in good faith any opinion whatever respecting the`
  line `conduct of a public servant in the discharge of his public functions, or respecting his character, so far as`
  line `his character appears in that conduct, and no further.`
  line
  line `Exception 3.---It is not defamation to express in good faith any opinion whatever respecting the`
  line `conduct of any person touching any public question, and respecting his character, so far as his character`
  line `appears in that conduct, and no further.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `It is not defamation in A to express in good faith any opinion whatever respecting Z’s conduct in`
  line `petitioning Government on a public question, in signing a requisition for a meeting on a public question,`
  line `in presiding or attending at such meeting, in forming or joining any society which invites the public`
  line `support, in voting or canvassing for a particular candidate for any situation in the efficient discharge of`
  line `the duties of which the public is interested.`
  line
  line `Exception 4.---It is not defamation to publish substantially true report of the proceedings of a Court,`
  line `or of the result of any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---A Magistrate or other officer holding an inquiry in open Court preliminary to a trial in`
  line `a Court, is a Court within the meaning of the above section.`
  line
  line `Exception 5.---It is not defamation to express in good faith any opinion whatever respecting the`
  line `merits of any case, civil or criminal, which has been decided by a Court, or respecting the conduct of any`
  line `person as a party, witness or agent, in any such case, or respecting the character of such person, as far as`
  line `his character appears in that conduct, and no further.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A says---"I think Z’s evidence on that trial is so contradictory that he must be stupid or`
  line `dishonest". A is within this exception if he says this in good faith, in as much as the opinion which he`
  line `expresses respects Z’s character as it appears in Z’s conduct as a witness, and no further.`
  line
  line `(b) But if A says---"I do not believe what Z asserted at that trial because I know him to be a man`
  line `without veracity"; A is not within this exception, in as much as the opinion which expresses of Z’s`
  line `character, is an opinion not founded on Z’s conduct as a witness.`
  line
  line `Exception 6.---It is not defamation to express in good faith any opinion respecting the merits of any`
  line `performance which its author has submitted to the judgment of the public, or respecting the character of`
  line `the author so far as his character appears in such performance, and no further.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---A performance may be submitted to the judgment of the public expressly or by acts on`
  line `the part of the author which imply such submission to the judgment of the public.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A person who publishes a book, submits that book to the judgment of the public.`
  line
  line `(b) A person who makes a speech in public, submits that speech to the judgment of the public.`
  line
  line `(c) An actor or singer who appears on a public stage, submits his acting or singing to the judgment of`
  line `the public.`
  line
  line `(d) A says of a book published by Z---"Z’s book is foolish; Z must be a weak man. Z’s book is`
  line `indecent; Z must be a man of impure mind". A is within the exception, if he says this in good faith, in as`
  line `much as the opinion which he expresses of Z respects Z’s character only so far as it appears in Z’s book,`
  line `and no further.`
  line
  line `(e) But if A says "I am not surprised that Z’s book is foolish and indecent, for he is a weak man and a`
  line `libertine". A is not within this exception, in as much as the opinion which he expresses of Z’s character is`
  line `an opinion not founded on Z’s book.`
  line
  line `Exception 7.---It is not defamation in a person having over another any authority, either conferred by`
  line `law or arising out of a lawful contract made with that other, to pass in good faith any censure on the`
  line `conduct of that other in matters to which such lawful authority relates.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A Judge censuring in good faith the conduct of a witness, or of an officer of the Court; a head of a`
  line `department censuring in good faith those who are under his orders, a parent censuring in good faith a`
  line `child in the presence of other children; a school master, whose authority is derived from a parent,`
  line `censuring in good faith a pupil in the presence of other pupils; a master censuring a servant in good faith`
  line `for remissness in service; a banker censuring in good faith the cashier of his bank for the conduct of such`
  line `cashier as such cashier are within this exception.`
  line
  line `Exception 8.---It is not defamation to prefer in good faith an accusation against any person to any of`
  line `those who have lawful authority over that person with respect to the subject-matter of accusation.`
  line
  line Illustration..
  line
  line `If A in good faith accuses Z before a Magistrate; if A in good faith complains of the conduct of Z, a`
  line `servant, to Z’s master; if A in good faith complains of the conduct of Z, a child, to Z’s father, A is within`
  line `this exception.`
  line
  line `Exception 9.---It is not defamation to make an imputation on the character of another provided that`
  line `the imputation be made in good faith for the protection of the interests of the person making it, or of any`
  line `other person, or for the public good.`
  line
  line Illustration..
  line
  line `(a) A, a shopkeeper, says to B, who manages his business---"Sell nothing to Z unless he pays you`
  line `ready money, for I have no opinion of his honesty". A is within the exception, if he has made this`
  line `imputation on Z in good faith for the protection of his own interests.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a Magistrate, in making a report to his own superior officer, casts an imputation on the`
  line `character of Z. Here, if the imputation is made in good faith, and for the public good, A is within the`
  line exception.
  line
  line `Exception 10.---It is not defamation to convey a caution, in good faith, to one person against another,`
  line `provided that such caution be intended for the good of the person to whom it is conveyed, or of some`
  line `person in whom that person is interested, or for the public good.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever defames another shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine, or with both, or with community service.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever prints or engraves any matter, knowing or having good reason to believe that such`
  line `matter is defamatory of any person, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever sells or offers for sale any printed or engraved substance containing defamatory matter,`
  line `knowing that it contains such matter, shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (90722)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 357
  title `Breach of contract to attend on and supply wants of helpless person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90722&sectionno=357&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being`
  line `bound by a lawful contract to attend on or to supply the wants of any person who, by reason of youth, or`
  line `of unsoundness of mind, or of a disease or bodily weakness, is helpless or incapable of providing for his`
  line `own safety or of supplying his own wants, voluntarily omits so to do, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (90723)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 358
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123&sectionId=90723&sectionno=358&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00048_2023-45_1719292564123
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Code referred to in sub-section (1), it shall not affect,---`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the Code so repealed or anything duly done or suffered thereunder;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the Code so`
  line `repealed; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, or punishment incurred in respect of any offences committed against the Code so`
  line `repealed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation or remedy in respect of any such penalty, or punishment; or`
  line
  line `(e) any proceeding, investigation or remedy in respect of any such penalty or punishment as`
  line `aforesaid, and any such proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any such`
  line `penalty may be imposed as if that Code had not been repealed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Code shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(4) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of`
  line `the repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
